{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486542946,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"skill","callID":"call_RnVrDMx31Sr5U5NhMi2JodaV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"name":"deep-research"},"output":"<skill_content name=\"deep-research\">\n# Skill: deep-research\n\n<!-- Keywords: autoresearch, deep-research, iterative-research, autonomous-loop, convergence-detection, externalized-state, fresh-context, research-agent, JSONL-state, strategy-file -->\n\n# Autonomous Deep Research Loop\n\nNote: `Task` is allowed for the command executor that manages the loop. The `@deep-research` agent itself is LEAF-only and does not dispatch sub-agents.\n\nIterative research protocol with fresh context per iteration, externalized state, and convergence detection for deep technical investigation.\n\nRuntime path resolution:\n- OpenCode/Copilot runtime: `.opencode/agents/*.md`\n- Claude runtime: `.claude/agents/*.md`\n\nOperator contract precedence for this skill surface:\n- Command entrypoint syntax in `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Convergence math in `references/convergence/convergence.md` and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- Runtime agent inventories from the checked-in runtime directories above\n\n### Convergence Threshold Semantics\n\n**Default:** 0.05 on newInfoRatio (fully-new=1.0, partially-new=0.5, +0.10 simplicity bonus, capped 1.0)\n\n**Semantic:** `convergenceThreshold` compares newly discovered information against accumulated research knowledge with negative-knowledge emphasis. Lower = more iterations / higher signal threshold.\n\n**NOT INTERCHANGEABLE with siblings:**\n- `deep-review` uses 0.10 default on weighted P0/P1/P2 severity ratio\n- `deep-ai-council` uses 0.20 default on adjudicator-verdict stability\n\nCarrying threshold expectations across siblings will cause unexpected iteration counts. See this skill's changelog and decision records for the cross-sibling threshold research and parity invariants that confirm thresholds do not carry across siblings.\n\n## 1. WHEN TO USE\n\n### Activation Triggers\n\nUse this skill when:\n- Deep investigation requiring multiple rounds of discovery\n- Topic spans 3+ technical domains or sources\n- Initial findings need progressive refinement\n- Overnight or unattended research sessions\n- Research where prior findings inform subsequent queries\n\nKeyword triggers:\n\n- `autoresearch`\n- `deep research`\n- `autonomous research`\n- `research loop`\n- `iterative research`\n- `multi-round research`\n- `deep investigation`\n- `comprehensive research`\n\n### Use Cases\n\nUse deep-research for multi-round technical investigation, source triangulation, repeated exploration with fresh context, and research sessions where prior findings should shape the next focus.\n\n### When NOT to Use\n\n- Simple, single-question research (use direct codebase search or `/speckit:plan`)\n- Known-solution documentation (use `/speckit:plan`)\n- Implementation tasks (use `/speckit:implement`)\n- Quick codebase searches (use `@context` or direct Grep/Glob)\n- Fewer than 3 sources needed (single-pass research suffices)\n\n---\n\n## 2. SMART ROUTING\n\n> Pattern: aligned with the [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](../../sk-doc/create-skill/assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md).\n\n### Resource Domains\n\nThe router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/`, then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP`. Keep routing domain-focused rather than hardcoding exhaustive inventories.\n\n- `references/guides/quick_reference.md` for the first-touch operator cheat sheet.\n- `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md` for lifecycle, dispatch, reducer sequencing, and command-owned state flow.\n- `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` for bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back.\n- `references/convergence*.md` for stop contracts, signals, recovery, graph gates, and reference-only convergence ideas.\n- `references/state*.md` for packet layout, JSONL records, markdown outputs, reducer ownership, and reconstruction.\n- `references/guides/capability_matrix.md` for runtime parity.\n- `assets/*.md` for markdown templates and prompt assets that are safe to route through guarded markdown loading.\n\n### Resource Loading Levels\n\n| Level | When to Load | Resources |\n|-------|--------------|-----------|\n| ALWAYS | Every skill invocation | Quick reference baseline |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match | Loop, convergence, state, spec anchoring, runtime parity references |\n| ON_DEMAND | Only on explicit request | Full reference set and markdown assets |\n\n### Phase Signals\n\n| Phase | Signal | Primary Resources |\n|-------|--------|-------------------|\n| Init | No JSONL exists or setup context | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_format.md`, `state_jsonl.md` |\n| Iteration | Dispatch context includes iteration number | `loop_protocol.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `convergence_signals.md` |\n| Stuck | Dispatch context includes recovery language | `convergence_recovery.md`, `state_reducer_registry.md` |\n| Synthesis | STOP candidate or final report | `convergence.md`, `state_outputs.md`, `spec_check_protocol.md` |\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, ambiguity handling, and graceful fallback.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively scans `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards paths, checks `inventory`, and suppresses repeats with `seen`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - intent labels route to loop resource families without static file inventories.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST` requests disambiguation and missing families return a helpful notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/guides/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"LOOP_SETUP\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"autoresearch\", \"deep research\", \"research loop\", \"autonomous research\", \"setup\", \"init\"]},\n    \"ITERATION\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"iteration\", \"next round\", \"continue research\", \"research cycle\", \"delta\", \"focus\"]},\n    \"CONVERGENCE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"convergence\", \"stop condition\", \"diminishing returns\", \"legal stop\", \"newInfoRatio\"]},\n    \"RECOVERY\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"recovery\", \"timeout\", \"reconstruct\", \"blocked stop\", \"blocked_stop\"]},\n    \"STATE\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"state file\", \"jsonl\", \"strategy\", \"dashboard\", \"registry\", \"lineage\"]},\n    \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"spec.md\", \"generated fence\", \"folder_state\", \"lock\", \"spec anchoring\"]},\n    \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"runtime\", \"capability\", \"parity\", \"opencode\", \"claude\"]},\n    \"RESOURCE_MAP\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"resource map\", \"resource-map\", \"inventory\", \"coverage gate\"]},\n}\n\nRESOURCE_MAP = {\n    \"LOOP_SETUP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"],\n    \"ITERATION\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\"],\n    \"CONVERGENCE\": [\"references/convergence/convergence.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\", \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\"],\n    \"RECOVERY\": [\"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"STATE\": [\"references/state/state_format.md\", \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\", \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\"],\n    \"SPEC_ANCHORING\": [\"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n    \"RUNTIME_PARITY\": [\"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\"],\n    \"RESOURCE_MAP\": [\"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\", \"references/state/state_outputs.md\"],\n}\n\nLOADING_LEVELS = {\n    \"ALWAYS\": [DEFAULT_RESOURCE],\n    \"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\": [\"full protocol\", \"all references\", \"complete reference\", \"resume deep research\", \"state log\", \"research/iterations\", \"deltas\", \"overnight research\", \"active lineage\", \"reference-only\", \"optimizer\"],\n    \"ON_DEMAND\": [\n        \"references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_signals.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_graph.md\",\n        \"references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_format.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_jsonl.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_outputs.md\",\n        \"references/state/state_reducer_registry.md\",\n        \"references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n    ],\n}\n\nUNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST = [\n    \"Confirm setup vs iteration vs convergence vs state recovery\",\n    \"Confirm the target spec folder and research packet\",\n    \"Provide the current phase, latest iteration, or failing state file\",\n    \"Confirm whether full references or quick routing guidance are needed\",\n]\n\ndef _task_text(task) -> str:\n    return \" \".join([\n        str(getattr(task, \"text\", \"\")),\n        str(getattr(task, \"query\", \"\")),\n        \" \".join(getattr(task, \"keywords\", []) or []),\n    ]).lower()\n\ndef _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:\n    resolved = (SKILL_ROOT / relative_path).resolve()\n    resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT)\n    if resolved.suffix.lower() != \".md\":\n        raise ValueError(f\"Only markdown resources are routable: {relative_path}\")\n    return resolved.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix()\n\ndef _guard_resource_map(resource_map: dict[str, list[str]]) -> None:\n    for intent, resources in resource_map.items():\n        for relative_path in resources:\n            guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n            if guarded.startswith(\"references/\"):\n                tail = guarded.removeprefix(\"references/\")\n                if \"/\" not in tail and \"-\" in Path(tail).stem:\n                    raise ValueError(f\"RESOURCE_MAP must target canonical references, not compatibility stubs: {intent} -> {guarded}\")\n\ndef discover_markdown_resources() -> set[str]:\n    docs = []\n    for base in RESOURCE_BASES:\n        if base.exists():\n            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob(\"*.md\") if path.is_file())\n    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}\n\ndef score_intents(task) -> dict[str, float]:\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    scores = {intent: 0.0 for intent in INTENT_SIGNALS}\n    for intent, cfg in INTENT_SIGNALS.items():\n        for keyword in cfg[\"keywords\"]:\n            if keyword in text:\n                scores[intent] += cfg[\"weight\"]\n    return scores\n\ndef select_intents(scores: dict[str, float], ambiguity_delta: float = 1.0, max_intents: int = 2) -> list[str]:\n    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda item: item[1], reverse=True)\n    if not ranked or ranked[0][1] <= 0:\n        return [\"LOOP_SETUP\"]\n    selected = [ranked[0][0]]\n    if len(ranked) > 1 and ranked[1][1] > 0 and (ranked[0][1] - ranked[1][1]) <= ambiguity_delta:\n        selected.append(ranked[1][0])\n    return selected[:max_intents]\n\ndef route_deep_research_resources(task):\n    _guard_resource_map(RESOURCE_MAP)\n    _guard_resource_map({\"ALWAYS\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"], \"ON_DEMAND\": LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]})\n    inventory = discover_markdown_resources()\n    scores = score_intents(task)\n    intents = select_intents(scores)\n    loaded = []\n    seen = set()\n\n    def load_if_available(relative_path: str) -> None:\n        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)\n        if guarded in inventory and guarded not in seen:\n            load(guarded)\n            loaded.append(guarded)\n            seen.add(guarded)\n\n    for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ALWAYS\"]:\n        load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    if max(scores.values() or [0]) < 0.5:\n        return {\n            \"intents\": intents,\n            \"intent_scores\": scores,\n            \"load_level\": \"UNKNOWN_FALLBACK\",\n            \"needs_disambiguation\": True,\n            \"disambiguation_checklist\": UNKNOWN_FALLBACK_CHECKLIST,\n            \"resources\": loaded,\n        }\n\n    matched_intents = []\n    for intent in intents:\n        before_count = len(loaded)\n        for relative_path in RESOURCE_MAP.get(intent, []):\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n        if len(loaded) > before_count:\n            matched_intents.append(intent)\n\n    text = _task_text(task)\n    if any(keyword in text for keyword in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND_KEYWORDS\"]):\n        for relative_path in LOADING_LEVELS[\"ON_DEMAND\"]:\n            load_if_available(relative_path)\n\n    result = {\"intents\": intents, \"intent_scores\": scores, \"resources\": loaded}\n    if not matched_intents:\n        result[\"notice\"] = f\"No knowledge base found for intent(s): {', '.join(intents)}\"\n    return result\n```\n\n---\n\n## 3. HOW IT WORKS\n\n### Invocation Contract\n\nThis skill is invoked exclusively through `/deep:research:auto` or `/deep:research:confirm`. The command YAML owns state, dispatch, convergence, and synthesis.\n\nNever simulate the loop with ad hoc shell dispatch, nested CLI loops, direct `@deep-research` Task dispatch, `/tmp` prompt files, or state outside the resolved local research packet.\n\n### Executor Selection Contract\n\nThe YAML workflow owns executor selection. Native `@deep-research` is the default path; CLI executors are routed through the workflow, not through ad hoc shell loops.\n\nCross-CLI delegation is possible inside each executor sandbox but discouraged. Do not invoke the same CLI from within itself, and do not assume auth from a parent executor propagates to child CLIs.\n\nExecutor invariants:\n\n1. Produce a non-empty iteration markdown file at `{state_paths.iteration_pattern}`.\n2. Append a JSONL delta record to `{state_paths.state_log}` with required fields: `type`, `iteration`, `newInfoRatio`, `status`, and `focus`.\n3. Respect the LEAF-agent constraint: no sub-dispatch, no nested loops, and max 12 tool calls per iteration.\n\nFailure modes include `iteration_file_missing`, `iteration_file_empty`, `jsonl_not_appended`, `jsonl_missing_fields`, and `jsonl_parse_error`. Three consecutive failures route to stuck recovery.\n\n### Lifecycle Contract\n\nRuntime-supported lifecycle modes:\n\n| Mode | Meaning |\n|------|---------|\n| `new` | First run against the spec folder |\n| `resume` | Continue the active lineage and append a typed `resumed` JSONL event |\n| `restart` | Archive the existing research tree, mint a fresh `sessionId`, increment `generation`, and append a typed `restarted` event |\n\nDeferred modes are `fork` and `completed-continue`. They are reserved but not runtime-supported.\n\n### Code-Graph Readiness TrustState Surface\n\nThe live code-graph readiness contract reaches four TrustState values: `live`, `stale`, `absent`, and `unavailable`.\n\n`cached`, `imported`, `rebuilt`, and `rehomed` remain declared in the shared TrustState type for compatibility, but the readiness helpers used here do not emit them today.\n\n### Resource Map Integration\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init, deep research promotes it from ad hoc context to canonical packet state.\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: true` in `deep-research-config.json`.\n- Read the map once during init and summarize it into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`.\n- The snapshot MUST include per-section entry counts across `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`.\n- The snapshot MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section so later iterations inherit the map's structure without rereading the entire file.\n- Per-iteration prompts surface `resource-map.md` as the exclusion set for previously inventoried files.\n- Treat files already listed on the map as known inventory, not as net-new discoveries.\n- Only flag files as gaps when they look relevant to the active investigation and are missing from the map.\n- Final synthesis cites `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in `research.md` References when the map was present at init.\n- Convergence also emits `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from research delta evidence unless the operator passes `--no-resource-map`.\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` is absent at init:\n\n- Persist `resource_map_present: false`.\n- Write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`.\n- Omit the exclusion-set hint from iteration guidance.\n- Continue the loop normally; absence is informational, not a failure.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot Replacement\n\nDuring initialization, capture a bounded, pointer-based context snapshot in `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context` when the target is codebase-scoped.\n\nThe snapshot must include:\n\n- Relevant source paths or symbols, cited as pointers rather than full file bodies.\n- Known integration points and likely reuse candidates.\n- Existing conventions or constraints that should shape the first iteration.\n- Gaps or unavailable context sources, including stale code graph or memory retrieval.\n\nThe snapshot must not create a separate context report loop. If quick lookup is enough, route the user to `@context`; if planning is the real goal, route to `/speckit:plan` after the snapshot is available.\n\n### Architecture: 3-Layer Integration\n\n`/deep:research` owns the YAML workflow, which initializes state, dispatches one LEAF iteration at a time, evaluates convergence, synthesizes `research/research.md`, and saves continuity. The `@deep-research` agent executes only one research cycle per dispatch.\n\n### State Packet Location\n\nThe research state packet always lives under the target spec's local `research/` folder. Root-spec targets use `{spec_folder}/research/` directly. Child-phase and sub-phase targets use **flat-first**: a first run with an empty `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`. A `pt-NN` subfolder (`{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-{NN}`) is allocated only when prior content already exists in `research/` for a non-matching target (continuation runs reuse the existing flat artifact or matching `pt-NN` packet). This avoids the unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\nExample (first run on a child phase): `.../026-graph.../019-system-hardening/001-initial-research/004-desc-regen/` writes to `004-desc-regen/research/` directly.\n\nExample (subsequent run with prior content for a different target): `004-desc-regen/research/004-desc-regen-pt-02/` (pt-NN allocated as a sibling to the prior content).\n\nState files include `deep-research-config.json`, `deep-research-state.jsonl`, `deep-research-strategy.md`, `deep-research-findings-registry.json`, `deep-research-dashboard.md`, `.deep-research-pause`, `.deep-research.lock`, `resource-map.md`, `research.md`, and `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`.\n\nv(next): `deep-research-findings-registry.json` is the canonical registry name for sibling-skill consistency.\n\n### Core Innovation: Fresh Context Per Iteration\n\nEach agent dispatch gets a fresh context window. State continuity comes from files, not memory. This solves context degradation in long research sessions.\n\nAdapted from: karpathy/autoresearch (loop concept), AGR (fresh context \"Ralph Loop\"), pi-autoresearch (JSONL state), autoresearch-opencode (context injection).\n\n### Data Flow\n\nInit creates config, strategy, and state logs. Each loop reads state, checks convergence, dispatches `@deep-research`, writes iteration markdown and JSONL deltas, refreshes reducer-owned state, and either continues or synthesizes and saves continuity.\n\nLate-INIT can also anchor the research run to `spec.md`: the workflow acquires the advisory lock, classifies `folder_state`, seeds or appends bounded context before LOOP, and then syncs one generated findings block back into `spec.md` during SYNTHESIS while keeping `research/research.md` canonical.\n\nThat contract is exact:\n- `folder_state` is always one of `no-spec`, `spec-present`, `spec-just-created-by-this-run`, or `conflict-detected`\n- the advisory lock lives at `research/.deep-research.lock` from late INIT through save, skip-save, or cancel cleanup\n- post-synthesis write-back replaces exactly one `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` ... `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->` fence under the chosen host anchor\n- the full bounded mutation rules live in [spec_check_protocol.md](references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md)\n\n### Key Concepts\n\nResearch continuity is externalized to files, each iteration starts fresh, convergence uses newInfoRatio/stuck/question signals, strategy and registry are reducer-owned, JSONL remains append-only, and final synthesis consolidates `research/research.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n1. **Read state first** -- Agent must read JSONL and strategy.md before any research action\n   - Init validates the research charter (Non-Goals + Stop Conditions in `deep-research-strategy.md`, Step 5a): appends empty placeholders if missing, presents the charter for review in confirm mode.\n2. **One focus per iteration** -- Pick ONE research sub-topic from strategy.md \"Next Focus\"\n3. **Externalize findings** -- Write to iteration-NNN.md, not held in agent context\n4. **Update strategy** -- Append to \"What Worked\"/\"What Failed\", update \"Next Focus\"\n5. **Report newInfoRatio** -- Every iteration JSONL record must include newInfoRatio\n6. **Respect exhausted approaches** -- Never retry approaches in the \"Exhausted\" list\n7. **Cite sources** -- Every finding must cite `[SOURCE: url]` or `[SOURCE: file:line]`\n8. **Use generate-context.js for memory saves** -- Never manually create memory files\n9. **Treat research/research.md as workflow-owned** -- Iteration findings feed synthesis; the workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md`\n10. **Document ruled-out directions per iteration** -- Every iteration must include what was tried and failed\n11. **Report newInfoRatio + 1-sentence novelty justification** -- Every JSONL iteration record must include both\n12. **Quality guards must pass before convergence** -- Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single-weak-source checks must pass before STOP can trigger\n13. **Respect reducer ownership** -- The workflow reducer, not the agent, is the source of truth for strategy machine-owned sections, dashboard metrics, and findings registry updates\n14. **Use canonical packet names only** -- Write `deep-research-*` artifacts and `research/.deep-research-pause`; legacy names are read-only migration aliases\n15. **Invoke through the command workflow** -- Use `/deep:research:auto` or `/deep:research:confirm`, and let the YAML workflow own dispatch\n\n### NEVER\n\n1. **Dispatch sub-agents** -- @deep-research is LEAF-only (NDP compliance)\n2. **Hold findings in context** -- Write everything to files\n3. **Exceed TCB** -- Target 8-11 tool calls per iteration (max 12)\n4. **Ask the user** -- Autonomous execution; make best-judgment decisions\n5. **Skip convergence checks** -- Every iteration must be evaluated\n6. **Modify config after init** -- Config is read-only after initialization\n7. **Overwrite prior findings** -- Append to research/research.md, never replace\n8. **Implement fixes during research** -- Report findings only; implementation is a separate follow-up step.\n9. **Simulate loop dispatch** -- Do not write custom shell loops, nested CLI loops, `/tmp` prompt dispatchers, or direct Task loops for `@deep-research`. **Command-driven fan-out via `step_fanout_spawn` in the YAML is SUPPORTED** — use `--executor`/`--executors`/`--concurrency` flags on the command; ad-hoc shell fan-out and intra-lineage wave orchestration remain forbidden.\n\n### Iteration Status Enum\n\n`complete | timeout | error | stuck | insight | thought`\n\n- `insight`: Low newInfoRatio but important conceptual breakthrough\n- `thought`: Analytical-only iteration, no evidence gathering\n\n### EXPERIMENTAL / REFERENCE-ONLY FEATURES\n\nThese concepts remain documented for future design work, but they are not part of the live executable contract for `/deep:research`:\n1. **Wave orchestration** -- parallel question fan-out and pruning within a single lineage remains reference-only (intra-lineage wave)\n2. **Checkpoint commits** -- per-iteration git commits\n3. **Multi-lineage fan-out** -- SUPPORTED via `--executor`/`--executors` flags on the command (see §8 EXAMPLES). Each lineage is an independent full loop in `{artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/`, converging independently. This is not \"wave orchestration\"; it is N independent loops.\n4. **Alternate CLI dispatch** -- process-isolated `claude -p` or similar dispatch modes are used internally by `fanout-run.cjs`; do not write them ad-hoc from within a research session\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n1. **3+ consecutive timeouts** -- Infrastructure issue, not research problem\n2. **State file corruption unrecoverable** -- Cannot reconstruct from JSONL or iteration files\n3. **All approaches exhausted with questions remaining** -- Research may need human guidance\n4. **Security concern in findings** -- Proprietary code or credentials discovered\n5. **All recovery tiers exhausted** -- No automatic recovery path remaining\n\n---\n\n## 5. REFERENCES\n\nCore documentation: `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, `references/protocol/loop_protocol.md`, `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, `references/convergence/convergence.md`, and `references/state/state_format.md`.\n\nFocused convergence references: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`, and `references/convergence/convergence_reference_only.md`.\n\nFocused state references: `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\nTemplates: `assets/deep_research_config.json`, `assets/deep_research_strategy.md`, `assets/deep_research_dashboard.md`, `assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl`, and `assets/runtime_capabilities.json`.\n\nCross-skill alignment: `deep-research` owns iterative investigation. Its shared resource family mirrors `deep-review` and `deep-ai-council`, but its vocabulary remains novelty, sources, negative knowledge, question coverage, and research synthesis rather than severity findings or council agreement.\n\n---\n\n## 6. SUCCESS CRITERIA\n\n### Loop Completion\n- Research loop ran to convergence or max iterations\n- All state files present and consistent (config, JSONL, strategy)\n- research/resource-map.md produced from converged deltas unless `config.resource_map.emit == false` (operator flag: `--no-resource-map`)\n- research/research.md produced with findings from all iterations\n- Canonical continuity surfaces updated via generate-context.js\n\n### Quality Gates\n\nBlocking gates: valid config/strategy/state before loop, iteration markdown plus JSONL plus reducer refresh per iteration, final `research/research.md` and convergence report after loop, and quality guards for source diversity/focus/no weak single source. Continuity save is expected but non-blocking.\n\n### Convergence Report\n\nEvery completed loop produces a convergence report:\n- Stop reason (converged, max_iterations, all_questions_answered, stuck_unrecoverable)\n- Total iterations completed\n- Questions answered ratio\n- Average newInfoRatio trend\n\n---\n\n## 7. INTEGRATION POINTS\n\n### Framework Integration\n\nThis skill operates within the behavioral framework defined in the active runtime's root doc (CLAUDE.md or AGENTS.md).\n\nKey integrations:\n- **Gate 2**: Skill routing via `skill_advisor.py` (keywords: autoresearch, deep research)\n- **Gate 3**: File modifications require spec folder question per the root doc Gate 3\n- **Continuity**: `/speckit:resume` is the operator-facing recovery surface; canonical packet continuity is written via `generate-context.js`\n- **Orchestrator**: @orchestrate dispatches @deep-research as LEAF agent\n\n### Continuity Integration\n\nBefore research, recover context with `/speckit:resume` using `handover.md -> _memory.continuity -> spec docs`. During each iteration, write `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, append JSONL, and let the reducer refresh strategy/registry/dashboard. After research, save continuity through `generate-context.js`.\n\n### Command Integration\n\n| Command | Relationship |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:research` | Primary invocation point |\n| `/speckit:resume` | Canonical recovery surface before resuming or extending an active packet |\n| `/speckit:plan` | Next step after deep research completes |\n| `/memory:save` | Manual memory save (deep research auto-saves) |\n\n---\n\n## 8. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n\nThe router discovers reference and markdown asset docs dynamically. Start with `references/guides/quick_reference.md`, then route to loop protocol, spec anchoring, convergence, state, runtime parity, or recovery references based on intent.\n\nScripts: `scripts/reduce-state.cjs`, `scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`.\n\nRelated skills: `deep-review` for iterative audit loops, `deep-loop-runtime` for shared executor/state/coverage-graph runtime, and `system-spec-kit` for command-owned state, packet anchoring, and continuity saves.\n\nBase directory for this skill: /Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research\nRelative paths in this skill (e.g., scripts/, reference/) are relative to this base directory.\nNote: file list is sampled.\n\n<skill_files>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/baselines/claude-baseline.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-005-orchestrate-handoff.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-004-concise-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-008-absorption-probe.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-006-auto-missing-inputs.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-001-auto-run-specified.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-007-delegation-route-proof.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-003-vague-natural-ask.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/scenarios/RSB-002-bare-command-halt.md</file>\n<file>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/behavior_benchmark/behavior_benchmark.md</file>\n</skill_files>\n</skill_content>","metadata":{"name":"deep-research","dir":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research","truncated":false},"title":"Loaded skill: deep-research","time":{"start":1783486542927,"end":1783486542942}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_07fc9ec0f23aeb52016a4dd84ed42881918e3e5196d9845b6f"}},"id":"prt_f4014f3f8001S2i26XLhfUNZzS","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40149ec50018ZJLYvvbAQJPOq"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486543630,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f4014f707001mCOfEeG9nXkj5N","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"9f16b65e914587e42dc339efd1a2e2417b8c70d6","messageID":"msg_f40149ec50018ZJLYvvbAQJPOq","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":20749,"input":15604,"output":21,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":4608}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486544633,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f4014faf7001gvWavQYffX7wNn","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","snapshot":"9f16b65e914587e42dc339efd1a2e2417b8c70d6","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Aq1oMyECl4FN5SMVMZKLylv0","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Quick Reference\n3: description: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research quick reference\"\n6:   - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n7:   - \"research iteration checklist\"\n8:   - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n9:   - \"research tuning guide\"\n10:   - \"research progress visualization\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: general\n13: version: 1.14.0.26\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Quick Reference\n17: \n18: One-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: Lookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n25: \n26: Operator contract source of truth for this page:\n27: - command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n28: - convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n29: - state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: ## 2. COMMANDS\n34: \n35: | Command | Description |\n36: |---------|-------------|\n37: | `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n38: | `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n39: | `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n40: \n41: ### Parameters\n42: \n43: | Parameter | Default | Description |\n44: |-----------|---------|-------------|\n45: | `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n46: | `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n47: | `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n48: | `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n49: \n50: ---\n51: \n52: ## 3. WHEN TO USE\n53: \n54: | Scenario | Use |\n55: |----------|-----|\n56: | Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n57: | Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n58: | Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n59: | Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n60: \n61: ---\n62: \n63: ## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n64: \n65: ```text\n66: /deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n67:     |                    |                      |\n68:     |                    |                      +-- Read state\n69:     |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n70:     |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n71:     |                    |                      +-- Update state\n72:     |                    |\n73:     |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n74:     |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n75:     |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n76:     |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ---\n80: \n81: ## 5. STATE FILES\n82: \n83: | File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n84: |------|----------|--------|---------|\n85: | Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n86: | State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n87: | Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n88: | Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n89: | Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n90: | Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n91: | Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n92: \n93: > **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n94: \n95: > **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n96: \n97: > **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n98: \n99: > **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n104: \n105: | Status | Meaning |\n106: |--------|---------|\n107: | `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n108: | `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n109: | `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n110: | `stuck` | No new information found |\n111: | `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n112: | `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n117: \n118: ```text\n119: Max iterations reached?\n120:   Yes --> STOP\n121: \n122: All questions answered?\n123:   Yes --> STOP\n124: \n125: stuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n126:   Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n127:     Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n128:     Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n129: \n130: Composite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n131:   Yes --> STOP (converged)\n132: \n133: Otherwise --> CONTINUE\n134: ```\n135: \n136: ### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n137: \n138: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n139: |--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n140: | Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n141: | MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n142: | Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n143: \n144: **Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n145: \n146: Quality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n151: \n152: Each @deep-research iteration:\n153: 1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n154: 2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n155: 3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n156: 4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n157: 5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n158: 6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n159: 7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n160: \n161: ---\n162: \n163: ## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n164: \n165: | Goal | Adjustment |\n166: |------|------------|\n167: | Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n168: | Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n169: | Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n170: | Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n171: \n172: ---\n173: \n174: ## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n175: \n176: | Problem | Fix |\n177: |---------|-----|\n178: | Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n179: | Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n180: | Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n181: | State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n182: | Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n183: \n184: ---\n185: \n186: ## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n187: \n188: After each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n189: \n190: ### Format\n191: \n192: | Element | Format | Example |\n193: |---------|--------|---------|\n194: | newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n195: | Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n196: | Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n197: | Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n198: \n199: ### Example Output\n200: \n201: ```text\n202: ITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n203: ─────────────────────\n204: newInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\n205: Questions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\n206: Composite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\n207: Noise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\n208: Stuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\n209: Signals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n210: ```\n211: \n212: ### When to Display\n213: \n214: - After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n215: - In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n216: - In confirm mode approval gates\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## 12. RELATED\n221: \n222: | Resource | Purpose |\n223: |----------|---------|\n224: | `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n225: | `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n226: | `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n227: | `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n228: | `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n229: | `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n230: \n231: ---\n232: \n233: ## 13. REVIEW MODE\n234: \n235: Review mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 235 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Quick Reference\ndescription: One-page cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research quick reference\"\n  - \"research loop cheat sheet\"\n  - \"research iteration checklist\"\n  - \"research loop troubleshooting\"\n  - \"research tuning guide\"\n  - \"research progress visualization\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.26\n---\n\n# Deep Research Quick Reference\n\nOne-page operator cheat sheet for the autonomous deep research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\nLookup surface during runs covering when to invoke the loop, what each phase produces, how convergence is computed, and where live state lives on disk. Defer to the full protocol and convergence references for deep reasoning.\n\nOperator contract source of truth for this page:\n- command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- convergence stop contract: `references/convergence/convergence.md`, `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`, and the deep-research YAML workflow\n- state packet contract: `references/state/state_format.md`, `references/state/state_jsonl.md`, `references/state/state_outputs.md`, and `references/state/state_reducer_registry.md`\n\n---\n\n## 2. COMMANDS\n\n| Command | Description |\n|---------|-------------|\n| `/deep:research:auto \"topic\"` | Run autonomous deep research (no approval gates) |\n| `/deep:research:confirm \"topic\"` | Run with approval gates at each iteration |\n| `/deep:research \"topic\"` | Ask which mode to use |\n\n### Parameters\n\n| Parameter | Default | Description |\n|-----------|---------|-------------|\n| `--max-iterations` | 10 | Maximum loop iterations |\n| `--convergence` | 0.05 | Stop when avg newInfoRatio below this |\n| `--spec-folder` | auto | Target spec folder path |\n| `progressiveSynthesis` | true | Allow incremental `research/research.md` updates before final synthesis |\n\n---\n\n## 3. WHEN TO USE\n\n| Scenario | Use |\n|----------|-----|\n| Deep unknown topic, multi-round needed | `/deep:research` |\n| Simple question, 1-2 sources | Direct search with `@context` |\n| Check prior work only | `memory_context()` |\n| Exhaustive critical research | `/deep:research --max-iterations 15 --convergence 0.02` |\n\n---\n\n## 4. ARCHITECTURE\n\n```text\n/deep:research  -->  YAML workflow  -->  @deep-research agent (LEAF)\n    |                    |                      |\n    |                    |                      +-- Read state\n    |                    |                      +-- Research (3-5 actions)\n    |                    |                      +-- Write findings\n    |                    |                      +-- Update state\n    |                    |\n    |                    +-- Init (config, strategy, state)\n    |                    +-- Loop (dispatch, evaluate, decide)\n    |                    +-- Synthesize (final research/research.md)\n    |                    +-- Save (memory context)\n```\n\n---\n\n## 5. STATE FILES\n\n| File | Location | Format | Purpose |\n|------|----------|--------|---------|\n| Config | `research/deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters |\n| State | `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Iteration log (append-only) |\n| Strategy | `research/deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | What worked/failed, next focus |\n| Registry | `research/findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned open/resolved questions and key findings |\n| Dashboard | `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Reducer-owned lifecycle and convergence summary |\n| Iterations | `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration findings |\n| Output | `research/research.md` | Markdown | Workflow-owned progressive synthesis output |\n\n> **Live lifecycle branches:** `resume`, `restart`. (`fork` and `completed-continue` are deferred and not runtime-wired.) `progressiveSynthesis` defaults to `true`, so `research/research.md` is updated during the loop and finalized at synthesis.\n\n> **Path contract:** root-spec runs write directly to `{spec_folder}/research/`; child-phase and sub-phase first runs use the local `{spec_folder}/research/` directory directly, with `{ownerSlug}-pt-NN` allocated only when prior non-matching content already exists.\n\n> **Canonical pause sentinel:** `research/.deep-research-pause`\n\n> **Runtime capability matrix:** `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md` and `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n---\n\n## 6. ITERATION STATUS LEGEND\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal iteration with findings |\n| `timeout` | Exceeded time/tool budget |\n| `error` | Failed to produce outputs |\n| `stuck` | No new information found |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only, no evidence |\n\n---\n\n## 7. CONVERGENCE DECISION TREE\n\n```text\nMax iterations reached?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nAll questions answered?\n  Yes --> STOP\n\nstuckThreshold consecutive no-progress?\n  Yes --> STUCK_RECOVERY\n    Recovery works? --> CONTINUE\n    Recovery fails? --> STOP (with gaps)\n\nComposite convergence (3-signal weighted > 0.60)?\n  Yes --> STOP (converged)\n\nOtherwise --> CONTINUE\n```\n\n### 3-Signal Convergence Model\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Votes STOP When |\n|--------|--------|---------------|-----------------|\n| Rolling Average | 0.30 | 3 | avg(last 3 newInfoRatios) < convergenceThreshold |\n| MAD Noise Floor | 0.35 | 4 | latest ratio <= MAD * 1.4826 |\n| Question Entropy | 0.35 | 1 | answered / total questions >= 0.85 |\n\n**Composite stop threshold:** 0.60 -- weighted stop score must exceed this before quality guards are evaluated.\n\nQuality guards (source diversity, focus alignment, no single-weak-source) must pass before STOP.\n\n---\n\n## 8. AGENT ITERATION CHECKLIST\n\nEach @deep-research iteration:\n1. Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` and `deep-research-strategy.md`\n2. Determine focus from reducer-owned strategy \"Next Focus\"\n3. Execute 3-5 research actions (WebFetch, Grep, Read, memory_search)\n4. Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md` with findings\n5. Append iteration record to `deep-research-state.jsonl`\n6. Let the workflow reducer update `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n7. Optionally update machine-owned sections in `research/research.md` when progressive synthesis is enabled\n\n---\n\n## 9. TUNING GUIDE\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower convergence (0.02), raise max iterations (15) |\n| Faster completion | Raise convergence (0.10), lower max iterations (5) |\n| Broader coverage | Start with broad topic, let iterations narrow |\n| Specific answer | Start with specific question, lower max iterations (5) |\n\n---\n\n## 10. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| Problem | Fix |\n|---------|-----|\n| Stops too early | Lower `--convergence` from 0.05 to 0.02 |\n| Repeats same research | Check strategy.md \"Exhausted Approaches\" is being read |\n| Agent ignores state | Verify file paths in dispatch prompt |\n| State file corrupt | Validate JSONL: `cat research/deep-research-state.jsonl \\| jq .` |\n| Loop runs too long | Set lower `--max-iterations` or higher `--convergence` |\n\n---\n\n## 11. PROGRESS VISUALIZATION\n\nAfter each iteration, the orchestrator can display a text-based convergence summary:\n\n### Format\n\n| Element | Format | Example |\n|---------|--------|---------|\n| newInfoRatio trend | ASCII sparkline | `[0.9 0.7 0.5 0.3 0.1]` |\n| Question coverage | Progress bar | `[=======>...] 7/10 (70%)` |\n| Composite score | Threshold bar | `[####----] 0.42 / 0.60` |\n| Noise floor | Comparison | `ratio: 0.12 > floor: 0.08` |\n\n### Example Output\n\n```text\nITERATION 5 PROGRESS\n─────────────────────\nnewInfoRatio: 0.9 -> 0.7 -> 0.5 -> 0.3 -> 0.1  trending down\nQuestions:   [========>..] 8/10 answered (80%)\nComposite:   [######--] 0.48 / 0.60 threshold\nNoise floor: 0.08 (ratio 0.10 ABOVE floor)\nStuck count: 0 | Segment: 1 | Recovery: none\nSignals: RollingAvg=STOP MAD=CONTINUE Entropy=CONTINUE\n```\n\n### When to Display\n\n- After each iteration evaluation (Step 4)\n- In the convergence report (synthesis phase)\n- In confirm mode approval gates\n\n---\n\n## 12. RELATED\n\n| Resource | Purpose |\n|----------|---------|\n| `@context` | Single-pass codebase search (not iterative) |\n| `@orchestrate` | Multi-agent coordination |\n| `memory_context()` | Prior work retrieval |\n| `generate-context.js` | Supported memory save script |\n| `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md` | Convergence signal details |\n| `references/state/state_jsonl.md` | JSONL state record details |\n\n---\n\n## 13. REVIEW MODE\n\nReview mode has been split into a separate skill. See `deep-review/references/protocol/quick_reference.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":235,"totalLines":235,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/quick_reference.md","time":{"start":1783486563418,"end":1783486563536}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd863614481919aa07510ecb30b0e"}},"id":"prt_f40154456001xYRtFjI5EM1vZU","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MofUhubej7La9ufo0hf6OprQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: State Format Reference\n3: description: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state format\"\n6:   - \"research state packet hub\"\n7:   - \"research file ownership model\"\n8:   - \"research file protection rules\"\n9:   - \"research packet location\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.29\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # State Format Reference\n16: \n17: Live state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Summarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n30: \n31: ### Routed Details\n32: \n33: - `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n34: - `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n35: - `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n36: \n37: For iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n38: \n39: ### Packet Summary\n40: \n41: The deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n42: \n43: | File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n44: |------|--------|---------|------------|\n45: | `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n46: | `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n47: | `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n48: | `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n49: | `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n50: | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n51: | `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n52: | `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n53: | `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n54: \n55: The artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n56: \n57: ---\n58: \n59: ## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n60: \n61: Root specs use:\n62: \n63: ```text\n64: {spec_folder}/research/\n65: ```\n66: \n67: Child-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n68: \n69: - first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n70: - a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n71: - continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n72: \n73: This avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n78: \n79: | Owner | Writes |\n80: |-------|--------|\n81: | Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n82: | Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n83: | Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n84: | Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n85: \n86: The reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n91: \n92: | Protection | Meaning |\n93: |------------|---------|\n94: | `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n95: | `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n96: | `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n97: | `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n98: | `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n99: \n100: The config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n105: \n106: | Resource | Use When |\n107: |----------|----------|\n108: | `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n109: | `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n110: | `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n111: | `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n112: | `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n113: \n114: ---\n115: \n116: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n117: \n118: - Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n119: - Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n120: - Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.\n\n(End of file - total 120 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","text":"---\ntitle: State Format Reference\ndescription: Live state packet hub for the deep-research loop.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state format\"\n  - \"research state packet hub\"\n  - \"research file ownership model\"\n  - \"research file protection rules\"\n  - \"research packet location\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# State Format Reference\n\nLive state packet hub for deep-research files, mutability, and routed state references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nSummarize the live deep-research packet files, mutability rules, and focused state references without carrying every JSON shape inline.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when navigating packet files, deciding file ownership, or choosing which detailed state reference to load next.\n\n### Routed Details\n\n- `state_jsonl.md` for config, iteration, event, lifecycle, graph, and blocked-stop records.\n- `state_outputs.md` for strategy, iteration markdown, `research.md`, dashboard, and resource-map output.\n- `state_reducer_registry.md` for reducer ownership, findings registry, validation, reconstruction, and file protection.\n\nFor iterative code review state, use `deep-review`. Review-mode state is not part of this skill's live state contract.\n\n### Packet Summary\n\nThe deep-research loop persists continuity in packet files so each iteration can run with fresh context.\n\n| File | Format | Purpose | Mutability |\n|------|--------|---------|------------|\n| `deep-research-config.json` | JSON | Loop parameters and lineage | Created at init; read-only after |\n| `deep-research-state.jsonl` | JSONL | Append-only structured log | Append-only |\n| `deep-research-strategy.md` | Markdown | Current research plan and next focus | Reducer-managed sections |\n| `deep-research-findings-registry.json` / `findings-registry.json` | JSON | Reducer-owned findings and question state | Auto-generated |\n| `deep-research-dashboard.md` | Markdown | Operator summary | Auto-generated |\n| `iterations/iteration-NNN.md` | Markdown | Per-iteration narrative | Write-once |\n| `deltas/iter-NNN.jsonl` | JSONL | Per-iteration structured delta | Write-once |\n| `research.md` | Markdown | Final/progressive synthesis | Workflow-owned |\n| `resource-map.md` | Markdown | Optional evidence-derived resource map | Workflow-owned |\n\nThe artifact directory is resolved by `resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research')` from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. PACKET LOCATION\n\nRoot specs use:\n\n```text\n{spec_folder}/research/\n```\n\nChild-phase and sub-phase targets use flat-first behavior:\n\n- first run with an empty local `research/` directory writes flat at `{spec_folder}/research/`;\n- a `{basename(spec_folder)}-pt-NN` subfolder is allocated only when prior content already exists for a non-matching target;\n- continuation runs reuse the existing matching packet.\n\nThis avoids an unnecessary `pt-01` wrapper on first runs.\n\n---\n\n## 3. OWNERSHIP MODEL\n\n| Owner | Writes |\n|-------|--------|\n| Agent iteration | `iterations/iteration-NNN.md`, JSONL iteration/event append, optional progressive synthesis contribution |\n| Workflow reducer | strategy machine-owned sections, findings registry, dashboard |\n| Workflow synthesis | `research.md`, lifecycle snapshots |\n| Spec anchoring protocol | bounded `spec.md` seed/context/fenced findings block |\n\nThe reducer is the source of truth for derived state. Manual edits to reducer-owned outputs are overwritten on the next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 4. FILE PROTECTION\n\n| Protection | Meaning |\n|------------|---------|\n| `immutable` | Created once and not modified after init |\n| `append-only` | New JSONL records may be appended; existing records are not rewritten |\n| `write-once` | Each iteration artifact is created once |\n| `mutable` | Workflow may update the file under defined ownership rules |\n| `auto-generated` | Reducer/workflow regenerates the full file |\n\nThe config file carries the protection map; details live in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `state_jsonl.md` | Need the JSONL config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, or blocked-stop schemas |\n| `state_outputs.md` | Need markdown output structure for strategy, iterations, dashboard, research synthesis, or resource map |\n| `state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer ownership, registry schema, validation, fault tolerance, or reconstruction |\n| `../convergence/convergence.md` | Need STOP contract and legal-stop semantics |\n| `../protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` | Need bounded `spec.md` anchoring and generated-fence write-back |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not document `deep-review` state here; route to the sibling skill.\n- Do not treat legacy aliases as write targets. The workflow reads legacy aliases only for migration windows and writes canonical `deep-research-*` names.\n- Do not manually edit reducer-owned dashboard or registry files.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":120,"totalLines":120,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md","time":{"start":1783486563478,"end":1783486563538}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd863615c8191b2073e54a431a029"}},"id":"prt_f40154494001pF2W6gl4E1JPnG","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_fgrQwHbrvhjktDd9fBUabvqW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Detection Reference\n3: description: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence detection\"\n6:   - \"research stop contract\"\n7:   - \"research stopreason values\"\n8:   - \"research legal stop gates\"\n9:   - \"research convergence decision order\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.20\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Convergence Detection Reference\n16: \n17: Live stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: \n25: Keep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n26: \n27: ### When to Use\n28: \n29: Load this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n30: \n31: ### Key Sources\n32: \n33: - Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n34: - Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n35: - Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n36: - Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n37: - Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n38: \n39: For iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n40: \n41: ### Live Decision Model\n42: \n43: Convergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n44: \n45: The live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n46: \n47: | Stage | Outcome |\n48: |-------|---------|\n49: | Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n50: | Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n51: | Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n52: | Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n53: | Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n54: \n55: ---\n56: \n57: ## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n58: \n59: ### stopReason Values\n60: \n61: | Value | When It Is Used |\n62: |-------|-----------------|\n63: | `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n64: | `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n65: | `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n66: | `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n67: | `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n68: | `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n69: \n70: ### Legacy Stop Labels\n71: \n72: Legacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n73: \n74: | Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n75: |------------------------|------------------|\n76: | `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n77: | `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n78: | `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n79: | `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n80: | `paused` | `userPaused` |\n81: | `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n82: | `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n83: \n84: ---\n85: \n86: ## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n87: \n88: ### Decision Order\n89: \n90: ```text\n91: 1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n92: 2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n93: 3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n94: 4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n95: 5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n96: 6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n97: 7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n98: 8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n99: ```\n100: \n101: ### Composite Signal Weights\n102: \n103: | Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n104: |--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n105: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n106: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n107: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n108: \n109: The weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n110: \n111: ---\n112: \n113: ## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n114: \n115: Every non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n116: \n117: | Gate | Rule | Failure |\n118: |------|------|---------|\n119: | Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n120: | Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n121: | Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n122: | Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n123: \n124: The reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n125: \n126: ---\n127: \n128: ## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n129: \n130: | Resource | Use When |\n131: |----------|----------|\n132: | `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n133: | `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n134: | `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n135: | `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n136: | `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n137: | `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n138: \n139: ---\n140: \n141: ## 6. NON-GOALS\n142: \n143: - Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n144: - Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n145: - Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.\n\n(End of file - total 145 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Detection Reference\ndescription: Live stop contract and navigation hub for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence detection\"\n  - \"research stop contract\"\n  - \"research stopreason values\"\n  - \"research legal stop gates\"\n  - \"research convergence decision order\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.20\n---\n\n# Convergence Detection Reference\n\nLive stop-contract hub for deep-research convergence and routed convergence references.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nKeep the executable deep-research stop contract short enough to load during routing while pointing detailed signal, recovery, and graph behavior to focused references.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this hub when deciding whether a deep-research loop should continue, recover, or stop.\n\n### Key Sources\n\n- Command syntax: `.opencode/commands/deep/research.md`\n- Workflow algorithm: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml`\n- Signal details: `references/convergence/convergence_signals.md`\n- Recovery details: `references/convergence/convergence_recovery.md`\n- Graph stop gates: `references/convergence/convergence_graph.md`\n\nFor iterative code review convergence, use `deep-review`. Review-mode algorithms and state are not part of the deep-research live contract.\n\n### Live Decision Model\n\nConvergence decides whether the loop should continue, recover from a stuck state, or stop. A STOP candidate is not legal until the legal-stop gate bundle passes. Novelty math can nominate STOP; gates authorize it.\n\nThe live deep-research algorithm evaluates:\n\n| Stage | Outcome |\n|-------|---------|\n| Hard stops | Stop on max iterations or all key questions answered |\n| Stuck detection | Enter recovery after configured consecutive no-progress iterations |\n| Composite convergence | Nominate STOP when weighted signal score is above `0.60` |\n| Legal-stop gates | Allow or block the STOP candidate |\n| Graph gates | Add STOP-blocking graph checks when `graphEvents` exist |\n\n---\n\n## 2. STOP CONTRACT\n\n### stopReason Values\n\n| Value | When It Is Used |\n|-------|-----------------|\n| `converged` | Legal-stop gates passed and the loop may exit normally |\n| `maxIterationsReached` | The loop hit the configured iteration cap |\n| `userPaused` | A pause sentinel or equivalent user pause request halted execution |\n| `blockedStop` | A STOP candidate was blocked by legal-stop or graph gates |\n| `stuckRecovery` | Stuck detection triggered or failed recovery |\n| `error` | The loop hit an unrecoverable workflow or state error |\n\n### Legacy Stop Labels\n\nLegacy labels are normalized before persistence:\n\n| Legacy label or phrase | New `stopReason` |\n|------------------------|------------------|\n| `composite_converged` | `converged` |\n| `novelty below threshold` | `converged` |\n| `all_questions_answered` | `converged` |\n| `max_iterations_reached` | `maxIterationsReached` |\n| `paused` | `userPaused` |\n| `stuck_detected` | `stuckRecovery` |\n| `stuck_unrecoverable` | `stuckRecovery` |\n\n---\n\n## 3. LIVE ALGORITHM\n\n### Decision Order\n\n```text\n1. If iteration count >= maxIterations, STOP with maxIterationsReached.\n2. If all key questions have evidence-backed answers, nominate STOP.\n3. If stuckCount >= stuckThreshold, enter stuck recovery.\n4. Compute composite convergence signals.\n5. If weighted stop score > 0.60, nominate STOP.\n6. Evaluate legal-stop gates for every STOP candidate except hard max-iteration stop.\n7. If graphEvents exist, evaluate graph-aware STOP blockers.\n8. If gates pass, STOP; otherwise emit blockedStop and CONTINUE with recovery focus.\n```\n\n### Composite Signal Weights\n\n| Signal | Weight | Min Iterations | Measures |\n|--------|--------|----------------|----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Recent information yield |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Signal vs noise in `newInfoRatio` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | 1 key question | Evidence-backed question coverage |\n\nThe weighted stop score is normalized over active signals. STOP is nominated only when the normalized score is greater than `0.60`. See `convergence_signals.md` for exact signal rules and reporting.\n\n---\n\n## 4. LEGAL STOP GATES\n\nEvery non-terminal STOP candidate must pass the gate bundle before the workflow exits.\n\n| Gate | Rule | Failure |\n|------|------|---------|\n| Convergence Gate | Low novelty holds for the required consecutive evidence iterations | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Coverage Gate | Every key question has an evidence-backed answer | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Quality Gate | Source diversity, focus alignment, and no single weak-source dominance pass | Emit `blocked_stop`, continue |\n| Graph Gate | When graph data exists, graph coverage has no STOP blockers | Emit `graph_convergence`/`blocked_stop`, continue |\n\nThe reducer surfaces legal-stop evidence through the findings registry and dashboard. The JSONL event shapes live in `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROUTED REFERENCES\n\n| Resource | Use When |\n|----------|----------|\n| `convergence_signals.md` | Need scoring, `newInfoRatio`, `stuckCount`, MAD, entropy, report fields, or threshold tuning |\n| `convergence_recovery.md` | Need stuck recovery, recovery strategy selection, tiered errors, or escalation behavior |\n| `convergence_graph.md` | Need graph-aware STOP gates, graph convergence events, or coverage graph fallback behavior |\n| `convergence_reference_only.md` | Need future/reference-only models such as segment filtering, semantic convergence, or optimizer metadata |\n| `../state/state_jsonl.md` | Need JSONL event shapes persisted by the convergence workflow |\n| `../state/state_reducer_registry.md` | Need reducer-owned registry/dashboard fields derived from convergence |\n\n---\n\n## 6. NON-GOALS\n\n- Do not copy `deep-review` convergence into this skill. Use the `deep-review` references for severity-weighted review convergence.\n- Do not treat reference-only semantic or segment models as executable contracts.\n- Do not change the YAML workflow by editing this document. This document describes and routes the live contract; workflow changes require command/YAML work.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":145,"totalLines":145,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md","time":{"start":1783486563511,"end":1783486563541}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd863617081919518083d80acf86b"}},"id":"prt_f401544b5001eRbcLp50ysJQv4","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_3C68QTUYpXYRaRXKwJGN8lfF","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Convergence Signals Reference\n3: description: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research convergence signals\"\n6:   - \"research new info ratio\"\n7:   - \"research stuck count\"\n8:   - \"mad noise floor\"\n9:   - \"question entropy\"\n10:   - \"research composite score\"\n11:   - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\n12: importance_tier: normal\n13: contextType: implementation\n14: version: 1.14.0.3\n15: ---\n16: \n17: # Convergence Signals Reference\n18: \n19: This reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n20: \n21: ---\n22: \n23: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n24: \n25: ### Purpose\n26: \n27: Define the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\n28: \n29: ### When to Use\n30: \n31: Load this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\n32: \n33: ### Core Principle\n34: \n35: Signals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\n36: \n37: ---\n38: \n39: ## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\n40: \n41: The live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\n42: \n43: | Signal | Weight | Requires | STOP Vote |\n44: |--------|--------|----------|-----------|\n45: | Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Average of last 3 `newInfoRatio` values is below `convergenceThreshold` |\n46: | MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Latest `newInfoRatio` is at or below `MAD * 1.4826` |\n47: | Question Entropy | `0.35` | At least 1 key question | Evidence-backed coverage is at least `0.85` |\n48: \n49: `thought` iterations are excluded from rolling average, MAD, and stuck counting because they are analytical-only. `insight` iterations are included in convergence signals but do not count as stuck.\n50: \n51: ---\n52: \n53: ## 3. NEW INFO RATIO\n54: \n55: `newInfoRatio` measures how much an iteration added relative to accumulated research knowledge.\n56: \n57: | Ratio | Meaning |\n58: |-------|---------|\n59: | `1.0` | Mostly new findings or first broad pass |\n60: | `0.7` | Several new findings plus some refinements |\n61: | `0.5` | Mixed new and repeated material |\n62: | `0.2` | Mostly confirmation or marginal novelty |\n63: | `0.0` | No new information |\n64: \n65: Agent assessment guidance:\n66: \n67: - Fully new finding: count as `1.0`.\n68: - Refinement of known finding: count as partial novelty.\n69: - Ruled-out direction: count as valuable negative knowledge when it removes a plausible path.\n70: - Tentative single-source finding: contribute less than verified or multi-source evidence.\n71: - Simplicity bonus may add up to `0.10`, capped at `1.0`, when an iteration materially reduces the search space.\n72: \n73: Every iteration record should include `newInfoRatio` and `noveltyJustification`; see `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 4. STUCK COUNT\n78: \n79: `stuckCount` is consecutive no-progress evidence iterations.\n80: \n81: ```text\n82: for each iteration from newest to oldest:\n83:   skip status == \"thought\"\n84:   stop counting when status == \"insight\"\n85:   count if status == \"stuck\" or newInfoRatio <= noProgressThreshold\n86:   stop counting on any productive evidence iteration\n87: ```\n88: \n89: Default threshold behavior:\n90: \n91: - `stuckThreshold`: `3`\n92: - `noProgressThreshold`: implementation default aligned with the workflow's recovery check\n93: - Recovery route: `convergence_recovery.md`\n94: \n95: ---\n96: \n97: ## 5. ROLLING AVERAGE\n98: \n99: Rolling average uses the last three evidence iterations.\n100: \n101: ```text\n102: evidenceIterations = iterations where status != \"thought\"\n103: recent = last 3 evidenceIterations\n104: rollingAvg = mean(recent.newInfoRatio)\n105: rollingStop = rollingAvg < convergenceThreshold\n106: ```\n107: \n108: This signal is unavailable before three evidence iterations. The composite vote normalizes over active signals, so early runs can still use question coverage without pretending the rolling signal exists.\n109: \n110: ---\n111: \n112: ## 6. MAD NOISE FLOOR\n113: \n114: MAD compares the latest ratio against the noise floor in the accumulated evidence ratios.\n115: \n116: ```text\n117: ratios = evidenceIterations.newInfoRatio\n118: medianRatio = median(ratios)\n119: mad = median(abs(ratio - medianRatio) for ratio in ratios)\n120: noiseFloor = mad * 1.4826\n121: madStop = latestEvidenceRatio <= noiseFloor\n122: ```\n123: \n124: Interpretation:\n125: \n126: | Condition | Meaning |\n127: |-----------|---------|\n128: | Latest ratio above floor | Signal still exceeds observed noise |\n129: | Latest ratio within floor | New findings may be indistinguishable from noise |\n130: | Very high floor | Iteration quality is unstable; narrow the focus before trusting STOP |\n131: \n132: ---\n133: \n134: ## 7. QUESTION ENTROPY\n135: \n136: Question entropy is evidence-backed key-question coverage.\n137: \n138: ```text\n139: answered = count(keyQuestions with evidence-backed answers)\n140: total = count(keyQuestions)\n141: coverage = answered / total\n142: entropyStop = coverage >= 0.85\n143: ```\n144: \n145: Tentative-only findings do not satisfy evidence-backed coverage. Graph events may add extra STOP blockers when graph coverage disagrees with inline question coverage; see `convergence_graph.md`.\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## 8. COMPOSITE SCORE\n150: \n151: ```text\n152: activeSignals = signals with enough data\n153: stopScore = sum(signal.weight for active STOP votes) / sum(active signal weights)\n154: stopCandidate = stopScore > 0.60\n155: ```\n156: \n157: The score nominates STOP only. `convergence.md` defines the legal-stop gates that decide whether the loop may exit.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 9. REPORTING\n162: \n163: Every completed loop should report:\n164: \n165: ```text\n166: CONVERGENCE REPORT\n167: ------------------\n168: Stop reason: converged | maxIterationsReached | userPaused | stuckRecovery | error\n169: Iterations completed: N\n170: Questions answered: X/Y\n171: Average newInfoRatio trend: [...]\n172: Composite stop score: 0.XX\n173: Signals:\n174:   Rolling Avg (w=0.30): STOP|CONTINUE\n175:   MAD Noise (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n176:   Entropy (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n177: Legal-stop gates: pass|blocked\n178: Graph gates: pass|blocked|not_applicable\n179: ```\n180: \n181: Dashboard and registry fields derived from these signals are documented in `../state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n182: \n183: ---\n184: \n185: ## 10. THRESHOLD TUNING\n186: \n187: | Goal | Adjustment |\n188: |------|------------|\n189: | Deeper research | Lower `convergenceThreshold`, raise `maxIterations` |\n190: | Faster completion | Raise `convergenceThreshold`, lower `maxIterations` |\n191: | More stuck recovery | Lower `stuckThreshold` cautiously |\n192: | Fewer false stops | Keep legal-stop and graph gates enabled |\n193: \n194: Optimizer-managed fields are described in `convergence_reference_only.md`. Optimizer proposals are advisory and do not override locked stop-contract fields.\n\n(End of file - total 194 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Convergence Signals Reference\ndescription: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence signals\"\n  - \"research new info ratio\"\n  - \"research stuck count\"\n  - \"mad noise floor\"\n  - \"question entropy\"\n  - \"research composite score\"\n  - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Convergence Signals Reference\n\nThis reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","text":"---\ntitle: Convergence Signals Reference\ndescription: Signal definitions, scoring rules, and reports for deep-research convergence.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research convergence signals\"\n  - \"research new info ratio\"\n  - \"research stuck count\"\n  - \"mad noise floor\"\n  - \"question entropy\"\n  - \"research composite score\"\n  - \"convergence threshold tuning\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Convergence Signals Reference\n\nThis reference defines the live deep-research convergence signals. The compact stop contract lives in `convergence.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the live convergence signals, scoring rules, threshold semantics, and reporting shape used by deep-research loops.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when calculating `newInfoRatio`, explaining a composite STOP vote, debugging stuck counts, or validating convergence dashboards.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nSignals nominate STOP; legal-stop and graph gates authorize or block it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. SIGNAL MODEL\n\nThe live model uses three weighted signals and normalizes by the weight of the signals that have enough data to run.\n\n| Signal | Weight | Requires | STOP Vote |\n|--------|--------|----------|-----------|\n| Rolling Average | `0.30` | 3 evidence iterations | Average of last 3 `newInfoRatio` values is below `convergenceThreshold` |\n| MAD Noise Floor | `0.35` | 4 evidence iterations | Latest `newInfoRatio` is at or below `MAD * 1.4826` |\n| Question Entropy | `0.35` | At least 1 key question | Evidence-backed coverage is at least `0.85` |\n\n`thought` iterations are excluded from rolling average, MAD, and stuck counting because they are analytical-only. `insight` iterations are included in convergence signals but do not count as stuck.\n\n---\n\n## 3. NEW INFO RATIO\n\n`newInfoRatio` measures how much an iteration added relative to accumulated research knowledge.\n\n| Ratio | Meaning |\n|-------|---------|\n| `1.0` | Mostly new findings or first broad pass |\n| `0.7` | Several new findings plus some refinements |\n| `0.5` | Mixed new and repeated material |\n| `0.2` | Mostly confirmation or marginal novelty |\n| `0.0` | No new information |\n\nAgent assessment guidance:\n\n- Fully new finding: count as `1.0`.\n- Refinement of known finding: count as partial novelty.\n- Ruled-out direction: count as valuable negative knowledge when it removes a plausible path.\n- Tentative single-source finding: contribute less than verified or multi-source evidence.\n- Simplicity bonus may add up to `0.10`, capped at `1.0`, when an iteration materially reduces the search space.\n\nEvery iteration record should include `newInfoRatio` and `noveltyJustification`; see `../state/state_jsonl.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STUCK COUNT\n\n`stuckCount` is consecutive no-progress evidence iterations.\n\n```text\nfor each iteration from newest to oldest:\n  skip status == \"thought\"\n  stop counting when status == \"insight\"\n  count if status == \"stuck\" or newInfoRatio <= noProgressThreshold\n  stop counting on any productive evidence iteration\n```\n\nDefault threshold behavior:\n\n- `stuckThreshold`: `3`\n- `noProgressThreshold`: implementation default aligned with the workflow's recovery check\n- Recovery route: `convergence_recovery.md`\n\n---\n\n## 5. ROLLING AVERAGE\n\nRolling average uses the last three evidence iterations.\n\n```text\nevidenceIterations = iterations where status != \"thought\"\nrecent = last 3 evidenceIterations\nrollingAvg = mean(recent.newInfoRatio)\nrollingStop = rollingAvg < convergenceThreshold\n```\n\nThis signal is unavailable before three evidence iterations. The composite vote normalizes over active signals, so early runs can still use question coverage without pretending the rolling signal exists.\n\n---\n\n## 6. MAD NOISE FLOOR\n\nMAD compares the latest ratio against the noise floor in the accumulated evidence ratios.\n\n```text\nratios = evidenceIterations.newInfoRatio\nmedianRatio = median(ratios)\nmad = median(abs(ratio - medianRatio) for ratio in ratios)\nnoiseFloor = mad * 1.4826\nmadStop = latestEvidenceRatio <= noiseFloor\n```\n\nInterpretation:\n\n| Condition | Meaning |\n|-----------|---------|\n| Latest ratio above floor | Signal still exceeds observed noise |\n| Latest ratio within floor | New findings may be indistinguishable from noise |\n| Very high floor | Iteration quality is unstable; narrow the focus before trusting STOP |\n\n---\n\n## 7. QUESTION ENTROPY\n\nQuestion entropy is evidence-backed key-question coverage.\n\n```text\nanswered = count(keyQuestions with evidence-backed answers)\ntotal = count(keyQuestions)\ncoverage = answered / total\nentropyStop = coverage >= 0.85\n```\n\nTentative-only findings do not satisfy evidence-backed coverage. Graph events may add extra STOP blockers when graph coverage disagrees with inline question coverage; see `convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. COMPOSITE SCORE\n\n```text\nactiveSignals = signals with enough data\nstopScore = sum(signal.weight for active STOP votes) / sum(active signal weights)\nstopCandidate = stopScore > 0.60\n```\n\nThe score nominates STOP only. `convergence.md` defines the legal-stop gates that decide whether the loop may exit.\n\n---\n\n## 9. REPORTING\n\nEvery completed loop should report:\n\n```text\nCONVERGENCE REPORT\n------------------\nStop reason: converged | maxIterationsReached | userPaused | stuckRecovery | error\nIterations completed: N\nQuestions answered: X/Y\nAverage newInfoRatio trend: [...]\nComposite stop score: 0.XX\nSignals:\n  Rolling Avg (w=0.30): STOP|CONTINUE\n  MAD Noise (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\n  Entropy (w=0.35): STOP|CONTINUE\nLegal-stop gates: pass|blocked\nGraph gates: pass|blocked|not_applicable\n```\n\nDashboard and registry fields derived from these signals are documented in `../state/state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 10. THRESHOLD TUNING\n\n| Goal | Adjustment |\n|------|------------|\n| Deeper research | Lower `convergenceThreshold`, raise `maxIterations` |\n| Faster completion | Raise `convergenceThreshold`, lower `maxIterations` |\n| More stuck recovery | Lower `stuckThreshold` cautiously |\n| Fewer false stops | Keep legal-stop and graph gates enabled |\n\nOptimizer-managed fields are described in `convergence_reference_only.md`. Optimizer proposals are advisory and do not override locked stop-contract fields.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":194,"totalLines":194,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence_signals.md","time":{"start":1783486563515,"end":1783486563543}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd863617481918205d221374e4317"}},"id":"prt_f401544b8001yYm9MI29ZI0drG","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_Xe2uEPItHFqp5qdmVab93J0E","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Output Files Reference\n3: description: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research output files\"\n6:   - \"research iteration files\"\n7:   - \"research synthesis document\"\n8:   - \"research resource map\"\n9:   - \"research strategy file\"\n10:   - \"spec anchoring output\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Output Files Reference\n17: \n18: This reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Human-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n39: \n40: `deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n41: \n42: Required sections:\n43: \n44: - Research Topic\n45: - Known Context\n46: - Key Questions\n47: - Answered Questions\n48: - What Worked\n49: - What Failed\n50: - Exhausted Approaches\n51: - Ruled-Out Directions\n52: - Next Focus\n53: \n54: Update protocol:\n55: \n56: - read strategy before each iteration;\n57: - choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n58: - append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n59: - update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n60: - when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n61: \n62: ---\n63: \n64: ## 3. ITERATION FILES\n65: \n66: Iteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n67: \n68: ```text\n69: research/iterations/iteration-001.md\n70: research/iterations/iteration-002.md\n71: research/iterations/iteration-003.md\n72: ```\n73: \n74: Required shape:\n75: \n76: | Markdown Element | Required Content |\n77: |------------------|------------------|\n78: | H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n79: | `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n80: | `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n81: | `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n82: | `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n83: | `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n84: | `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n85: \n86: Every finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n87: \n88: ---\n89: \n90: ## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n91: \n92: `research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n93: \n94: Rules:\n95: \n96: - progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n97: - final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n98: - prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n99: - generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n100: - when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n101: \n102: ---\n103: \n104: ## 5. DASHBOARD\n105: \n106: `deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n107: \n108: Expected sections:\n109: \n110: | Section | Source |\n111: |---------|--------|\n112: | Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n113: | Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n114: | Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n115: | Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n116: | Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n117: | Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n118: | Next Focus | Strategy |\n119: \n120: Generation rules:\n121: \n122: - regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n123: - compute derived values from raw state;\n124: - overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n125: - if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n126: - agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: ## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n131: \n132: When `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n133: \n134: - persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n135: - summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n136: - treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n137: - cite the map in final synthesis references;\n138: - emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n139: \n140: When absent:\n141: \n142: - persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n143: - write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n144: - continue normally.\n145: \n146: ---\n147: \n148: ## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n149: \n150: `references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n151: \n152: - acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n153: - classify `folder_state`;\n154: - seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n155: - replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n156: \n157: This output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.\n\n(End of file - total 157 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Output Files Reference\ndescription: Markdown output structures for strategy, iterations, dashboard, synthesis, and resource-map artifacts.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research output files\"\n  - \"research iteration files\"\n  - \"research synthesis document\"\n  - \"research resource map\"\n  - \"research strategy file\"\n  - \"spec anchoring output\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research Output Files Reference\n\nThis reference covers human-readable packet outputs. JSONL records live in `state_jsonl.md`; reducer ownership lives in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the human-readable deep-research packet outputs: strategy, iteration markdown, synthesis, dashboard, resource map, and bounded spec anchoring.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when writing or validating markdown outputs rather than JSONL records.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nHuman-readable outputs must stay synchronized with raw state and respect reducer ownership.\n\n---\n\n## 2. STRATEGY FILE\n\n`deep-research-strategy.md` is the persistent research plan. The reducer owns machine-managed sections.\n\nRequired sections:\n\n- Research Topic\n- Known Context\n- Key Questions\n- Answered Questions\n- What Worked\n- What Failed\n- Exhausted Approaches\n- Ruled-Out Directions\n- Next Focus\n\nUpdate protocol:\n\n- read strategy before each iteration;\n- choose one focus from `Next Focus`;\n- append what worked, failed, and was ruled out;\n- update answered/open questions through reducer-owned sections;\n- when a STOP candidate is blocked, override `Next Focus` with the blocker recovery focus.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION FILES\n\nIteration files are write-once markdown narratives.\n\n```text\nresearch/iterations/iteration-001.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-002.md\nresearch/iterations/iteration-003.md\n```\n\nRequired shape:\n\n| Markdown Element | Required Content |\n|------------------|------------------|\n| H1 title | `Iteration N: Focus Area` |\n| `Focus` section | What this iteration investigated |\n| `Findings` section | Evidence-backed findings with source citations |\n| `Sources Consulted` section | Files, URLs, memory hits, or commands used |\n| `Assessment` section | `newInfoRatio`, novelty justification, and confidence notes |\n| `Reflection` section | What worked, failed, or was ruled out |\n| `Recommended Next Focus` section | One concrete next focus |\n\nEvery finding must cite a source such as `[SOURCE: file:path:line]` or `[SOURCE: https://example.test]`.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RESEARCH SYNTHESIS\n\n`research.md` is the workflow-owned synthesis output at `{artifact_dir}/research.md`.\n\nRules:\n\n- progressive synthesis may update the file during the loop;\n- final synthesis consolidates duplicate findings and unresolved gaps;\n- prior findings are not silently overwritten;\n- generated or machine-owned sections must be marked explicitly when the workflow uses them;\n- when `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References.\n\n---\n\n## 5. DASHBOARD\n\n`deep-research-dashboard.md` is auto-generated from JSONL, strategy, and registry state.\n\nExpected sections:\n\n| Section | Source |\n|---------|--------|\n| Iteration Table | JSONL iteration records |\n| Question Status | Strategy + registry |\n| Convergence Trend | `convergenceSignals` + reducer |\n| Dead Ends | JSONL `ruledOut` + strategy |\n| Blocked Stops | Registry blocked-stop history |\n| Graph Convergence | Graph convergence registry fields |\n| Next Focus | Strategy |\n\nGeneration rules:\n\n- regenerate after each iteration evaluation;\n- compute derived values from raw state;\n- overwrite the full dashboard rather than appending;\n- if state is missing, write a minimal \"No iteration data available\" dashboard;\n- agent writes are discarded on next refresh.\n\n---\n\n## 6. RESOURCE MAP\n\nWhen `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` exists at init:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: true` in config;\n- summarize section counts and themes into strategy `Known Context`;\n- treat listed files as known inventory, not net-new discoveries;\n- cite the map in final synthesis references;\n- emit `{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md` from converged deltas unless disabled.\n\nWhen absent:\n\n- persist `resource_map_present: false`;\n- write `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` into `Known Context`;\n- continue normally.\n\n---\n\n## 7. SPEC ANCHORING OUTPUT\n\n`references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` defines bounded `spec.md` writes:\n\n- acquire `research/.deep-research.lock`;\n- classify `folder_state`;\n- seed or append bounded context during init when allowed;\n- replace exactly one generated findings fence during synthesis.\n\nThis output path is protocol-owned, not iteration-agent owned.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":157,"totalLines":157,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_outputs.md","time":{"start":1783486563507,"end":1783486563544}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd86361688191a86f9072365e006b"}},"id":"prt_f401544af001z5DajFWKji00AR","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_rwIW6xGZ4brZtpNcQDOmqYXz","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n3: description: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research state jsonl\"\n6:   - \"research config record\"\n7:   - \"research iteration records\"\n8:   - \"research negative knowledge\"\n9:   - \"research graph events\"\n10:   - \"research event records\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.3\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n17: \n18: `deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: Raw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n35: \n36: ---\n37: \n38: ## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n39: \n40: The config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n41: \n42: ```json\n43: {\n44:   \"type\": \"config\",\n45:   \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n46:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n47:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n48:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n49:   \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n50:   \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n51: }\n52: ```\n53: \n54: The full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: ## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n59: \n60: ```json\n61: {\n62:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n63:   \"run\": 1,\n64:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n65:   \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n66:   \"findingsCount\": 5,\n67:   \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n68:   \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n69:   \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n70:   \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n71:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n72:   \"durationMs\": 45000\n73: }\n74: ```\n75: \n76: | Field | Required | Notes |\n77: |-------|----------|-------|\n78: | `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n79: | `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n80: | `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n81: | `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n82: | `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n83: | `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n84: | `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n85: | `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n86: | `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n87: | `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n88: | `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n89: \n90: Status values:\n91: \n92: | Status | Meaning |\n93: |--------|---------|\n94: | `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n95: | `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n96: | `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n97: | `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n98: | `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n99: | `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n104: \n105: When the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n106: \n107: ```json\n108: {\n109:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n110:   \"run\": 5,\n111:   \"convergenceSignals\": {\n112:     \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n113:     \"madScore\": 0.08,\n114:     \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n115:     \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n116:   }\n117: }\n118: ```\n119: \n120: Signal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n121: \n122: ---\n123: \n124: ## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n125: \n126: Use `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n127: \n128: ```json\n129: {\n130:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n131:   \"run\": 3,\n132:   \"status\": \"complete\",\n133:   \"ruledOut\": [\n134:     {\n135:       \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n136:       \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n137:       \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n138:     }\n139:   ]\n140: }\n141: ```\n142: \n143: Ruled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n144: \n145: ---\n146: \n147: ## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n148: \n149: `graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n150: \n151: ```json\n152: {\n153:   \"type\": \"iteration\",\n154:   \"run\": 4,\n155:   \"graphEvents\": [\n156:     {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n157:     {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n158:     {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n159:   ]\n160: }\n161: ```\n162: \n163: Valid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n164: \n165: ---\n166: \n167: ## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n168: \n169: Lifecycle event:\n170: \n171: ```json\n172: {\n173:   \"type\": \"event\",\n174:   \"event\": \"resumed\",\n175:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n176:   \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n177:   \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n178:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n179:   \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n180:   \"generation\": 1,\n181:   \"archivedPath\": null,\n182:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n183: }\n184: ```\n185: \n186: Blocked stop event:\n187: \n188: ```json\n189: {\n190:   \"type\": \"event\",\n191:   \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n192:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n193:   \"run\": 7,\n194:   \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n195:   \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n196:   \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n197:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: Pause event:\n202: \n203: ```json\n204: {\n205:   \"type\": \"event\",\n206:   \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n207:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n208:   \"run\": 7,\n209:   \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n210:   \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n211:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n212: }\n213: ```\n214: \n215: Stuck recovery event:\n216: \n217: ```json\n218: {\n219:   \"type\": \"event\",\n220:   \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n221:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n222:   \"run\": 7,\n223:   \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n224:   \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n225:   \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n226:   \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n227:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n228: }\n229: ```\n230: \n231: Idea observation event:\n232: \n233: ```json\n234: {\n235:   \"type\": \"event\",\n236:   \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n237:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n238:   \"run\": 7,\n239:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n240:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n241:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n242:   \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n243:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n244: }\n245: ```\n246: \n247: Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n248: \n249: Idea promotion event:\n250: \n251: ```json\n252: {\n253:   \"type\": \"event\",\n254:   \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n255:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n256:   \"run\": 8,\n257:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n258:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n259:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n260:   \"observationCount\": 2,\n261:   \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n262:   \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n263:   \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n264:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n265: }\n266: ```\n267: \n268: The reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n269: \n270: Rejected idea event:\n271: \n272: ```json\n273: {\n274:   \"type\": \"event\",\n275:   \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n276:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n277:   \"run\": 7,\n278:   \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n279:   \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n280:   \"category\": \"ideas\",\n281:   \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n282:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n283: }\n284: ```\n285: \n286: `idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n287: \n288: Rejected idea removal event:\n289: \n290: ```json\n291: {\n292:   \"type\": \"event\",\n293:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n294:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n295:   \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n296:   \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n297:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n298: }\n299: ```\n300: \n301: Rejected idea reset event:\n302: \n303: ```json\n304: {\n305:   \"type\": \"event\",\n306:   \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n307:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n308:   \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n309:   \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n310: }\n311: ```\n312: \n313: The reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n314: \n315: Candidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n316: \n317: Graph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n318: \n319: ---\n320: \n321: ## 8. NORMALIZATION\n322: \n323: Emission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n324: \n325: Malformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.\n\n(End of file - total 325 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research JSONL State Reference\ndescription: Config, iteration, event, lineage, graph, and blocked-stop records for deep-research state logs.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research state jsonl\"\n  - \"research config record\"\n  - \"research iteration records\"\n  - \"research negative knowledge\"\n  - \"research graph events\"\n  - \"research event records\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.3\n---\n\n# Deep Research JSONL State Reference\n\n`deep-research-state.jsonl` is append-only. Each line is one JSON object. The first line is normally the config record, followed by iteration and event records.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the append-only JSONL records used by deep-research config, iteration, lifecycle, graph, pause, stuck-recovery, and blocked-stop state.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when validating state logs, adding event records, reconstructing a packet, or mapping legacy stop labels to current values.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nRaw JSONL is append-only evidence. Reducer-owned files derive from it, but they do not replace it.\n\n---\n\n## 2. CONFIG RECORD\n\nThe config record captures the initialized loop contract.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"config\",\n  \"topic\": \"API response time optimization\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"specFolder\": \"028-auto-deep-research\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe full config file also stores executor, lineage, reducer, capability matrix, pause sentinel, archive, and file-protection settings.\n\n---\n\n## 3. ITERATION RECORDS\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 1,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"focus\": \"Initial broad survey\",\n  \"findingsCount\": 5,\n  \"newInfoRatio\": 1.0,\n  \"noveltyJustification\": \"First pass; all findings are new to this packet\",\n  \"keyQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"answeredQuestions\": [\"What causes latency?\"],\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:05:00Z\",\n  \"durationMs\": 45000\n}\n```\n\n| Field | Required | Notes |\n|-------|----------|-------|\n| `type` | Yes | `iteration` |\n| `run` | Yes | 1-indexed iteration number |\n| `status` | Yes | See status values below |\n| `focus` | Yes | Single focus investigated |\n| `findingsCount` | Yes | Number of findings reported |\n| `newInfoRatio` | Yes | Novelty score used by convergence |\n| `noveltyJustification` | Recommended | One-sentence explanation of the ratio |\n| `keyQuestions` | Recommended | Questions considered during this iteration |\n| `answeredQuestions` | Recommended | Questions answered by evidence |\n| `ruledOut` | Optional | Negative knowledge entries |\n| `graphEvents` | Optional | Coverage graph mutations |\n\nStatus values:\n\n| Status | Meaning |\n|--------|---------|\n| `complete` | Normal evidence-gathering iteration |\n| `timeout` | Time/tool budget exceeded |\n| `error` | Tool, parse, or unexpected failure |\n| `stuck` | No new information and no clear next direction |\n| `insight` | Low ratio but important conceptual breakthrough |\n| `thought` | Analytical-only iteration; excluded from stuck and signal math |\n\n---\n\n## 4. CONVERGENCE SIGNAL FIELDS\n\nWhen the composite algorithm runs, the iteration may include signal values:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 5,\n  \"convergenceSignals\": {\n    \"rollingAvg\": 0.12,\n    \"madScore\": 0.08,\n    \"entropyCoverage\": 0.71,\n    \"compositeStop\": 0.42\n  }\n}\n```\n\nSignal rules live in `../convergence/convergence_signals.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. NEGATIVE KNOWLEDGE\n\nUse `ruledOut` to preserve eliminated approaches.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 3,\n  \"status\": \"complete\",\n  \"ruledOut\": [\n    {\n      \"approach\": \"HTTP/3 multiplexing\",\n      \"reason\": \"No server-side support in target environment\",\n      \"evidence\": \"file:docs/protocols.md:42\"\n    }\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nRuled-out directions should also appear in strategy and synthesis outputs.\n\n---\n\n## 6. GRAPH EVENTS\n\n`graphEvents` records coverage graph mutations from an iteration.\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"iteration\",\n  \"run\": 4,\n  \"graphEvents\": [\n    {\"type\": \"question\", \"id\": \"q-reconnect\", \"label\": \"How should reconnect work?\"},\n    {\"type\": \"finding\", \"id\": \"f-backoff\", \"label\": \"Exponential backoff is required\"},\n    {\"type\": \"edge\", \"from\": \"f-backoff\", \"to\": \"q-reconnect\", \"relation\": \"ANSWERS\"}\n  ]\n}\n```\n\nValid node types are `question`, `finding`, `claim`, and `source`; `edge` records connect nodes. IDs must be unique within a single `(specFolder, loopType, sessionId)` namespace. Reusing the same logical ID across independent sessions is allowed because the coverage graph uses a composite key.\n\n---\n\n## 7. EVENT RECORDS\n\nLifecycle event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"dr-2026-05-24T00-00-00Z\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume\",\n  \"continuedFromRun\": 4,\n  \"generation\": 1,\n  \"archivedPath\": null,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nBlocked stop event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"blocked_stop\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"blockedStop\",\n  \"blockedBy\": [\"keyQuestionCoverage\", \"sourceDiversity\"],\n  \"recoveryStrategy\": \"focus_pivot\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nPause event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"userPaused\",\n  \"sentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nStuck recovery event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"stopReason\": \"stuckRecovery\",\n  \"fromFocus\": \"Connection pooling\",\n  \"toFocus\": \"Transport alternatives\",\n  \"strategy\": \"try_opposites\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nIdea observation event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_observed\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"source\": \"iteration-007.md\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nLeaf agents may append `idea_observed` for promising tangents. They must not append `idea_promoted`; promotion is reducer-owned.\n\nIdea promotion event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_promoted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 8,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"observationCount\": 2,\n  \"minIdeaObservations\": 2,\n  \"firstObservedRun\": 6,\n  \"lastObservedRun\": 7,\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer emits `idea_promoted` once per idea after replay shows `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to the inclusive range `1..10`.\n\nRejected idea event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"idea_rejected\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"run\": 7,\n  \"ideaId\": \"idea-cache-stampede\",\n  \"idea\": \"Investigate cache stampede mitigation as a follow-up focus\",\n  \"category\": \"ideas\",\n  \"reason\": \"Already rejected by environment evidence\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\n`idea_rejected` durably suppresses the matching promoted idea and also enters the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache. Use `category: \"general\"` only when the rejection should suppress matching text across next-focus, recovery, and ideas candidates.\n\nRejected idea removal event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedRemoved\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"pattern\": \"Retry HTTP/3 as the primary latency fix\",\n  \"category\": \"next-focus\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nRejected idea reset event:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"ideaRejectedReset\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"reason\": \"Operator wants previously rejected ideas eligible again\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"\n}\n```\n\nThe reducer derives a bounded active rejected-pattern cache from these events. `idea_rejected` adds or refreshes one pattern, `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single matching pattern or id, and `ideaRejectedReset` clears the active cache. Legacy `ideaRejected`, `ideaRejectedRemoved`, and `ideaRejectedReset` rows remain replayable for existing state logs. The active cache is capped at 100 entries; when more are added, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning.\n\nCandidate checks compare normalized exact text first, then apply fuzzy matching only when the candidate category is compatible with the rejected category. Omit `category` for a general rejection that can suppress candidates across next-focus, recovery, or ideas surfaces.\n\nGraph convergence event shape lives in `../convergence/convergence_graph.md`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. NORMALIZATION\n\nEmission-time normalization maps legacy labels into canonical `stopReason` values before persistence. The mapping lives in `../convergence/convergence.md`.\n\nMalformed lines are handled by the reducer according to its strict/lenient mode. Fault tolerance and reconstruction are documented in `state_reducer_registry.md`.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":325,"totalLines":325,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_jsonl.md","time":{"start":1783486563484,"end":1783486563545}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd86361608191a28dc1a6c54ae5c3"}},"id":"prt_f40154498001bI4lSzRkU6riqi","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_VtShcg9bbRaHwtA4BJ2t5YmK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Spec Check Protocol\n3: description: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"spec check protocol\"\n6:   - \"research advisory lock\"\n7:   - \"spec folder state classification\"\n8:   - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n9:   - \"research spec conflict detection\"\n10: importance_tier: important\n11: contextType: implementation\n12: version: 1.14.0.9\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Spec Check Protocol\n16: \n17: Canonical contract for how `/deep:research` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n18: \n19: ---\n20: \n21: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n22: \n23: ### Purpose\n24: Define the bounded `spec.md` integration points for deep-research:\n25: - Late-INIT lock acquisition and folder-state detection\n26: - Pre-init seed or context mutation before LOOP starts\n27: - Post-synthesis generated-fence write-back before save or cancellation cleanup\n28: \n29: ### Scope\n30: This protocol applies only to deep-research-owned `spec.md` mutations:\n31: - Seeded Level 1 `spec.md` creation when no spec exists\n32: - Anchor-bounded pre-init context updates to an existing `spec.md`\n33: - One generated findings block written after synthesis\n34: \n35: This protocol does not own the shared intake contract in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`, nor `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` delegation behavior.\n36: \n37: ### Relation to the Deep-Research Loop\n38: The workflow remains four-phase:\n39: 1. INIT resolves canonical paths, acquires the advisory lock, and classifies `folder_state`\n40: 2. LOOP runs only after the pre-init spec branch is complete\n41: 3. SYNTHESIS compiles `research/research.md` and then performs bounded write-back\n42: 4. SAVE handles continuity refresh and lock release\n43: \n44: `research/research.md` remains the source of truth. `spec.md` receives only the bounded seed markers, pre-init context note, and the generated findings block described below.\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: ## 2. ADVISORY LOCK LIFECYCLE\n49: \n50: ### Lock File\n51: - Path: `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock`\n52: - Scope: one live deep-research writer per spec folder\n53: - Ownership: acquired by the deep-research workflow, not by the leaf agent\n54: \n55: ### Lifecycle\n56: 1. Resolve canonical research packet paths.\n57: 2. Acquire the lock in late INIT before `folder_state` classification.\n58: 3. Hold the lock through:\n59:    - pre-init seed or append work\n60:    - every LOOP iteration\n61:    - synthesis compilation\n62:    - post-synthesis generated-block replacement\n63: 4. Release the lock only after the save, skip-save, or cancel path has resolved.\n64: \n65: ### Semantics\n66: - Locking is advisory, not mandatory.\n67: - macOS and BSD follow POSIX advisory lock semantics for `flock()` and `fcntl()` style coordination.\n68: - Lock contention is fail-closed. A second live writer does not merge or override.\n69: - Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\n70: \n71: ### Required Audit Behavior\n72: - Successful acquisition records the resolved lock path and session lineage.\n73: - Release records whether the workflow ended with save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup.\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 3. FOLDER STATE CLASSIFICATION\n78: \n79: `step_detect_spec_present` outputs exactly one `folder_state` value:\n80: \n81: | `folder_state` | Meaning | Expected next action |\n82: |----------------|---------|----------------------|\n83: | `no-spec` | `spec.md` does not exist yet | Seed a Level 1 `spec.md` before LOOP |\n84: | `spec-present` | `spec.md` exists and approved host anchors are available | Apply bounded pre-init context updates |\n85: | `spec-just-created-by-this-run` | This run already seeded `spec.md` and can verify the DR seed markers | Do not reseed or duplicate pre-init context |\n86: | `conflict-detected` | Host anchors, markers, or human-authored content make mutation ambiguous | Emit typed audit and halt fail-closed |\n87: \n88: ### Detection Inputs\n89: - `spec_folder`\n90: - `research_topic`\n91: - `normalized_topic`\n92: - resolved host anchors in `spec.md`\n93: - existing `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers\n94: - existing generated findings fence markers\n95: \n96: ### Detection Guarantees\n97: - Classification happens after config, JSONL, strategy, and registry exist.\n98: - The result is passed into INIT and SYNTHESIS.\n99: - The workflow records a typed `spec_check_result` audit event before any mutation branch executes.\n100: \n101: ---\n102: \n103: ## 4. PRE-INIT BRANCHES\n104: \n105: ### `no-spec`\n106: - Create a Level 1 `spec.md` seeded from the research ask.\n107: - Insert tracked seed markers:\n108:   - `<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->` under Requirements\n109:   - `<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->` under Scope\n110: - Emit `spec_seed_created`.\n111: - Set `folder_state = spec-just-created-by-this-run` before LOOP begins.\n112: \n113: ### `spec-present`\n114: - Normalize the research topic before any append.\n115: - Append the topic only at bounded host locations:\n116:   - `Open Questions`\n117:   - a compact `Research Context` note\n118: - Do not rewrite adjacent prose or broaden the scope of the packet.\n119: - Emit `spec_preinit_context_added`.\n120: \n121: ### `spec-just-created-by-this-run`\n122: - Re-check the DR seed markers and continue without reseeding.\n123: - Treat marker verification as a no-op guard, not as another mutation.\n124: \n125: ### `conflict-detected`\n126: - Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n127: - Halt before LOOP.\n128: - Do not attempt fallback rewrites or inferred merges.\n129: \n130: ---\n131: \n132: ## 5. POST-SYNTHESIS WRITE-BACK\n133: \n134: ### Timing\n135: Run after `research/research.md` compilation during SYNTHESIS and before config completion or any memory-save branch.\n136: \n137: ### Write-Back Shape\n138: The workflow writes or replaces exactly one machine-owned fence nested under the chosen host anchor:\n139: \n140: ```md\n141: <!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n142: [abridged findings derived from research/research.md]\n143: <!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n144: ```\n145: \n146: ### Contract\n147: - `research/research.md` remains the source of truth.\n148: - The generated block is an abridged sync, not a second canonical narrative.\n149: - The workflow replaces the full block atomically when content changes.\n150: - Interrupted synthesis does not leave a partial block behind; emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead.\n151: \n152: ### Host Anchor Rules\n153: - The host anchor must already exist or be deterministically created by the seed path.\n154: - The generated block must be nested under that one chosen host anchor only.\n155: - The workflow must not create duplicate generated blocks in sibling sections.\n156: \n157: ---\n158: \n159: ## 6. AUDIT EVENTS\n160: \n161: All protocol events are appended to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`.\n162: \n163: Every audit payload is typed. At minimum, emit:\n164: - `type`\n165: - `event`\n166: - `timestamp`\n167: - `specPath` or `specFolder`\n168: - the contextual discriminator for the event (`folder_state`, `normalized_topic`, `generatedFence`, `packetIds`, `conflictKind`, or similar)\n169: \n170: | Event | Minimum payload schema |\n171: |-------|------------------------|\n172: | `spec_check_result` | `{ \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"spec_check_result\", \"folder_state\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n173: | `spec_seed_created` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_seed_created\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Scope\", \"Requirements\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"seed_markers\": [\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\", \"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\"], \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n174: | `spec_preinit_context_added` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_added\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\", \"Research Context\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n175: | `spec_preinit_context_deduped` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_deduped\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n176: | `spec_mutation` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation\", \"phase\": \"post-synthesis\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"<chosen host anchor>\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n177: | `spec_mutation_conflict` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation_conflict\", \"folder_state\": \"conflict-detected\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"conflictKind\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n178: | `spec_synthesis_deferred` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_synthesis_deferred\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n179: \n180: ### Audit Requirements\n181: - Every real `spec.md` mutation records `anchors_touched` and `diff_summary`.\n182: - The protocol never relies on prose logs alone.\n183: - Conflict exits and deferred write-back are auditable from JSONL without opening the mutated file.\n184: \n185: ---\n186: \n187: ## 7. IDEMPOTENCY RULES\n188: \n189: ### Topic Dedupe\n190: - Lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse whitespace, and trim before comparing research topics.\n191: - Re-running with the same `normalized_topic` must no-op instead of appending another pre-init note.\n192: - The shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md` §5-§6) applies the same normalization before writing `feature_description` into `spec.md` Problem Statement or Purpose; equivalent normalized phrases emit `intake_topic_deduped` instead of overwriting the existing prose.\n193: \n194: ### Marker-Based Placeholder Detection\n195: - Seed behavior depends on deterministic `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers, not fuzzy prose matching.\n196: - If the required seed markers already exist, treat the seed path as already satisfied.\n197: - The shared intake contract used by `/speckit:plan --intake-only`, `/speckit:plan`, and `/speckit:complete` classifies any retained DR seed marker as `placeholder-upgrade` and persists `resume_question_id` plus `reentry_reason` for REQ-011 re-entry.\n198: \n199: ### Relation-Object Dedupe\n200: - Manual relationship arrays dedupe by `packet_id` within each relation type (`depends_on`, `related_to`, `supersedes`) before emitting `graph-metadata.json`.\n201: - Dedupe outcomes emit `relationship_deduped` with typed payload fields such as `dedupedCount` and `packetIds`.\n202: \n203: ### Generated-Block Replacement\n204: - The generated findings block is matched by the exact marker pair:\n205:   - `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n206:   - `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n207: - Same host anchor plus same generated content resolves to a no-op.\n208: - If the existing generated block fails checksum validation or carries an explicit manual-edit marker, emit `spec_mutation_conflict` and halt instead of overwriting.\n209: \n210: ### Cross-Command Compatibility\n211: - Relation objects shared with sibling intake flows dedupe by `packet_id`.\n212: - This protocol does not create manual relationship edges itself, but it must not reintroduce duplicate relation objects if that metadata is surfaced during a future delegated sync.\n213: \n214: ---\n215: \n216: ## 8. CONFLICT EXITS\n217: \n218: Fail closed when any of the following is true:\n219: - The chosen host anchor is missing.\n220: - Duplicate DR seed markers are present.\n221: - Duplicate generated fence markers are present.\n222: - Human edits are detected inside the machine-owned generated block.\n223: - The generated block checksum drifts or an explicit manual-edit marker is present inside the existing fence.\n224: - Pre-init append intent conflicts with the semantic purpose of the host section.\n225: \n226: ### Exit Behavior\n227: 1. Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n228: 2. Keep existing `spec.md` content unchanged.\n229: 3. Stop before LOOP or before SAVE, depending on the phase.\n230: 4. Surface the exact blocking reason to the operator.\n231: \n232: No silent merge, overwrite, or best-effort repair is allowed on a conflict path.\n\n(End of file - total 232 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Spec Check Protocol\ndescription: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"spec check protocol\"\n  - \"research advisory lock\"\n  - \"spec folder state classification\"\n  - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n  - \"research spec conflict detection\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.9\n---\n\n# Spec Check Protocol\n\nCanonical contract for how `/deep:research` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n\n---\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Spec Check Protocol\ndescription: Canonical contract for late-INIT spec.md detection, bounded mutation, advisory locking, and post-synthesis write-back in deep-research.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"spec check protocol\"\n  - \"research advisory lock\"\n  - \"spec folder state classification\"\n  - \"post-synthesis write-back\"\n  - \"research spec conflict detection\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.9\n---\n\n# Spec Check Protocol\n\nCanonical contract for how `/deep:research` inspects and mutates `spec.md` without turning that work into an unbounded side effect.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\nDefine the bounded `spec.md` integration points for deep-research:\n- Late-INIT lock acquisition and folder-state detection\n- Pre-init seed or context mutation before LOOP starts\n- Post-synthesis generated-fence write-back before save or cancellation cleanup\n\n### Scope\nThis protocol applies only to deep-research-owned `spec.md` mutations:\n- Seeded Level 1 `spec.md` creation when no spec exists\n- Anchor-bounded pre-init context updates to an existing `spec.md`\n- One generated findings block written after synthesis\n\nThis protocol does not own the shared intake contract in `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`, nor `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` delegation behavior.\n\n### Relation to the Deep-Research Loop\nThe workflow remains four-phase:\n1. INIT resolves canonical paths, acquires the advisory lock, and classifies `folder_state`\n2. LOOP runs only after the pre-init spec branch is complete\n3. SYNTHESIS compiles `research/research.md` and then performs bounded write-back\n4. SAVE handles continuity refresh and lock release\n\n`research/research.md` remains the source of truth. `spec.md` receives only the bounded seed markers, pre-init context note, and the generated findings block described below.\n\n---\n\n## 2. ADVISORY LOCK LIFECYCLE\n\n### Lock File\n- Path: `{spec_folder}/research/.deep-research.lock`\n- Scope: one live deep-research writer per spec folder\n- Ownership: acquired by the deep-research workflow, not by the leaf agent\n\n### Lifecycle\n1. Resolve canonical research packet paths.\n2. Acquire the lock in late INIT before `folder_state` classification.\n3. Hold the lock through:\n   - pre-init seed or append work\n   - every LOOP iteration\n   - synthesis compilation\n   - post-synthesis generated-block replacement\n4. Release the lock only after the save, skip-save, or cancel path has resolved.\n\n### Semantics\n- Locking is advisory, not mandatory.\n- macOS and BSD follow POSIX advisory lock semantics for `flock()` and `fcntl()` style coordination.\n- Lock contention is fail-closed. A second live writer does not merge or override.\n- Stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\n\n### Required Audit Behavior\n- Successful acquisition records the resolved lock path and session lineage.\n- Release records whether the workflow ended with save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup.\n\n---\n\n## 3. FOLDER STATE CLASSIFICATION\n\n`step_detect_spec_present` outputs exactly one `folder_state` value:\n\n| `folder_state` | Meaning | Expected next action |\n|----------------|---------|----------------------|\n| `no-spec` | `spec.md` does not exist yet | Seed a Level 1 `spec.md` before LOOP |\n| `spec-present` | `spec.md` exists and approved host anchors are available | Apply bounded pre-init context updates |\n| `spec-just-created-by-this-run` | This run already seeded `spec.md` and can verify the DR seed markers | Do not reseed or duplicate pre-init context |\n| `conflict-detected` | Host anchors, markers, or human-authored content make mutation ambiguous | Emit typed audit and halt fail-closed |\n\n### Detection Inputs\n- `spec_folder`\n- `research_topic`\n- `normalized_topic`\n- resolved host anchors in `spec.md`\n- existing `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers\n- existing generated findings fence markers\n\n### Detection Guarantees\n- Classification happens after config, JSONL, strategy, and registry exist.\n- The result is passed into INIT and SYNTHESIS.\n- The workflow records a typed `spec_check_result` audit event before any mutation branch executes.\n\n---\n\n## 4. PRE-INIT BRANCHES\n\n### `no-spec`\n- Create a Level 1 `spec.md` seeded from the research ask.\n- Insert tracked seed markers:\n  - `<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->` under Requirements\n  - `<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->` under Scope\n- Emit `spec_seed_created`.\n- Set `folder_state = spec-just-created-by-this-run` before LOOP begins.\n\n### `spec-present`\n- Normalize the research topic before any append.\n- Append the topic only at bounded host locations:\n  - `Open Questions`\n  - a compact `Research Context` note\n- Do not rewrite adjacent prose or broaden the scope of the packet.\n- Emit `spec_preinit_context_added`.\n\n### `spec-just-created-by-this-run`\n- Re-check the DR seed markers and continue without reseeding.\n- Treat marker verification as a no-op guard, not as another mutation.\n\n### `conflict-detected`\n- Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n- Halt before LOOP.\n- Do not attempt fallback rewrites or inferred merges.\n\n---\n\n## 5. POST-SYNTHESIS WRITE-BACK\n\n### Timing\nRun after `research/research.md` compilation during SYNTHESIS and before config completion or any memory-save branch.\n\n### Write-Back Shape\nThe workflow writes or replaces exactly one machine-owned fence nested under the chosen host anchor:\n\n```md\n<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n[abridged findings derived from research/research.md]\n<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->\n```\n\n### Contract\n- `research/research.md` remains the source of truth.\n- The generated block is an abridged sync, not a second canonical narrative.\n- The workflow replaces the full block atomically when content changes.\n- Interrupted synthesis does not leave a partial block behind; emit `spec_synthesis_deferred` instead.\n\n### Host Anchor Rules\n- The host anchor must already exist or be deterministically created by the seed path.\n- The generated block must be nested under that one chosen host anchor only.\n- The workflow must not create duplicate generated blocks in sibling sections.\n\n---\n\n## 6. AUDIT EVENTS\n\nAll protocol events are appended to `research/deep-research-state.jsonl`.\n\nEvery audit payload is typed. At minimum, emit:\n- `type`\n- `event`\n- `timestamp`\n- `specPath` or `specFolder`\n- the contextual discriminator for the event (`folder_state`, `normalized_topic`, `generatedFence`, `packetIds`, `conflictKind`, or similar)\n\n| Event | Minimum payload schema |\n|-------|------------------------|\n| `spec_check_result` | `{ \"type\": \"event\", \"event\": \"spec_check_result\", \"folder_state\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_seed_created` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_seed_created\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Scope\", \"Requirements\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"seed_markers\": [\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\", \"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\"], \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_preinit_context_added` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_added\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\", \"Research Context\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_preinit_context_deduped` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_preinit_context_deduped\", \"folder_state\": \"spec-present\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"Open Questions\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"normalized_topic\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_mutation` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation\", \"phase\": \"post-synthesis\", \"anchors_touched\": [\"<chosen host anchor>\"], \"diff_summary\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_mutation_conflict` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_mutation_conflict\", \"folder_state\": \"conflict-detected\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"hostAnchor\": \"...\", \"specPath\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"conflictKind\": \"...\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n| `spec_synthesis_deferred` | `{ \"type\": \"spec_mutation\", \"event\": \"spec_synthesis_deferred\", \"reason\": \"...\", \"generatedFence\": \"deep-research/spec-findings\", \"timestamp\": \"...\" }` |\n\n### Audit Requirements\n- Every real `spec.md` mutation records `anchors_touched` and `diff_summary`.\n- The protocol never relies on prose logs alone.\n- Conflict exits and deferred write-back are auditable from JSONL without opening the mutated file.\n\n---\n\n## 7. IDEMPOTENCY RULES\n\n### Topic Dedupe\n- Lowercase, strip punctuation, collapse whitespace, and trim before comparing research topics.\n- Re-running with the same `normalized_topic` must no-op instead of appending another pre-init note.\n- The shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md` §5-§6) applies the same normalization before writing `feature_description` into `spec.md` Problem Statement or Purpose; equivalent normalized phrases emit `intake_topic_deduped` instead of overwriting the existing prose.\n\n### Marker-Based Placeholder Detection\n- Seed behavior depends on deterministic `<!-- DR-SEED:... -->` markers, not fuzzy prose matching.\n- If the required seed markers already exist, treat the seed path as already satisfied.\n- The shared intake contract used by `/speckit:plan --intake-only`, `/speckit:plan`, and `/speckit:complete` classifies any retained DR seed marker as `placeholder-upgrade` and persists `resume_question_id` plus `reentry_reason` for REQ-011 re-entry.\n\n### Relation-Object Dedupe\n- Manual relationship arrays dedupe by `packet_id` within each relation type (`depends_on`, `related_to`, `supersedes`) before emitting `graph-metadata.json`.\n- Dedupe outcomes emit `relationship_deduped` with typed payload fields such as `dedupedCount` and `packetIds`.\n\n### Generated-Block Replacement\n- The generated findings block is matched by the exact marker pair:\n  - `<!-- BEGIN GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n  - `<!-- END GENERATED: deep-research/spec-findings -->`\n- Same host anchor plus same generated content resolves to a no-op.\n- If the existing generated block fails checksum validation or carries an explicit manual-edit marker, emit `spec_mutation_conflict` and halt instead of overwriting.\n\n### Cross-Command Compatibility\n- Relation objects shared with sibling intake flows dedupe by `packet_id`.\n- This protocol does not create manual relationship edges itself, but it must not reintroduce duplicate relation objects if that metadata is surfaced during a future delegated sync.\n\n---\n\n## 8. CONFLICT EXITS\n\nFail closed when any of the following is true:\n- The chosen host anchor is missing.\n- Duplicate DR seed markers are present.\n- Duplicate generated fence markers are present.\n- Human edits are detected inside the machine-owned generated block.\n- The generated block checksum drifts or an explicit manual-edit marker is present inside the existing fence.\n- Pre-init append intent conflicts with the semantic purpose of the host section.\n\n### Exit Behavior\n1. Emit `spec_mutation_conflict`.\n2. Keep existing `spec.md` content unchanged.\n3. Stop before LOOP or before SAVE, depending on the phase.\n4. Surface the exact blocking reason to the operator.\n\nNo silent merge, overwrite, or best-effort repair is allowed on a conflict path.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":232,"totalLines":232,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md","time":{"start":1783486563518,"end":1783486563546}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd8636178819195c998b90f463621"}},"id":"prt_f401544bc001MesItxevBsbCc0","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486563551,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_ArAPoI2pKU5pLLQJLPWcB3A1","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Loop Protocol Reference\n3: description: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"research loop protocol\"\n6:   - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n7:   - \"research loop initialization\"\n8:   - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n9:   - \"research pause sentinel\"\n10:   - \"research synthesis phase\"\n11: importance_tier: important\n12: contextType: implementation\n13: version: 1.14.0.29\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Loop Protocol Reference\n17: \n18: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n19: \n20: ---\n21: \n22: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n23: \n24: ### Purpose\n25: \n26: Define the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n27: \n28: ### When to Use\n29: \n30: Load this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n31: \n32: ### Core Principle\n33: \n34: The YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n35: \n36: ### Phase Model\n37: \n38: The deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n39: \n40: Runtime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n41: - Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n42: - Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n43: \n44: ```text\n45: ┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n46: │  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n47: │          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n48: │ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n49: │ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n50: │ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n51: │          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n52: │          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n53: │          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n54: │          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n55: └──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n56: ```\n57: \n58: ---\n59: \n60: ## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n61: \n62: ### Purpose\n63: Set up all state files for a new research session.\n64: \n65: ### Steps\n66: \n67: 1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n68:    - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n69:    - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n70:    - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n71:    - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n72: 2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n73:    - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n74:    - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n75:    - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n76: 3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n77: 4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n78: 5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n79: 6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n80:    - Topic from user input\n81:    - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n82:    - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n83:    - Research boundaries from config\n84: 6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n85:    - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n86:    - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n87:    - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n88:    - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n89:    - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n90:    - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n91: 7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n92: 7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n93:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n94:    - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n95:    - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n96:    - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n97:    - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n98: 8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n99: \n100: ### Outputs\n101: - `research/deep-research-config.json`\n102: - `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n103: - `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n104: \n105: ### Auto-Resume Protocol\n106: If state files already exist from a prior session:\n107: 1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n108: 2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n109: 3. Read strategy.md for current state\n110: 4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n111: 5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n112: \n113: ```json\n114: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n115: ```\n116: \n117: 6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n118: \n119: ### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n120: \n121: The runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n122: \n123: | Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n124: |------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n125: | `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n126: | `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n127: | `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n128: \n129: **Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n130: \n131: ```json\n132: {\n133:   \"type\": \"event\",\n134:   \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n135:   \"mode\": \"research\",\n136:   \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n137:   \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n138:   \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n139:   \"generation\": <number>,\n140:   \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n141:   \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n142:   \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n143: }\n144: ```\n145: \n146: Every field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n147: \n148: ---\n149: \n150: ## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n151: \n152: ### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n153: \n154: #### Step 1: Read State\n155: - Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n156: - Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n157: \n158: #### Step 2: Check Convergence\n159: Run the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n160: - Max iterations reached? STOP\n161: - Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n162: - Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n163: - All questions answered? STOP\n164: - Otherwise: CONTINUE\n165: \n166: #### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n167: \n168: When the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n169: 1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n170: 2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n171: 3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n172: 4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n173:    - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n174:    - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n175:    - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n176: 5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n177: 6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n178: \n179: If the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n180: \n181: #### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n182: \n183: Before dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n184: \n185: 1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n186: 2. If present:\n187:    - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n188:    - Halt the loop with message:\n189:      ```text\n190:      Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n191:      Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n192:      ```\n193:    - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n194: 3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n195:    - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n196:    - Continue from step_read_state\n197: \n198: Pause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n199: \n200: **Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n201: \n202: #### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n203: \n204: Generate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n205: \n206: ```text\n207: STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n208: Segment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\n209: Questions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\n210: Last 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\n211: Recovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\n212: Next focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n213: ```\n214: \n215: This summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n216: \n217: #### Step 2d: Rejected Pattern Cache Check\n218: \n219: Before selecting the next-focus, recovery, or ideas-backed candidate for dispatch, read the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache and promoted ideas backlog from the findings registry.\n220: \n221: Rejected-cache lifecycle:\n222: \n223: 1. `idea_rejected` appends one rejected pattern to JSONL with `ideaId`, `idea` or `pattern`, optional `category`, optional `reason`, and normal lifecycle fields.\n224: 2. The reducer derives the active cache from JSONL events; generated registry and dashboard files expose `rejectedPatterns`, `rejectedPatternIndex`, and `suppressedCandidates`.\n225: 3. Exact suppression compares normalized candidate text against normalized rejected text.\n226: 4. Fuzzy suppression uses `rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold` from config when present, otherwise `0.85`, and only applies when the rejected category is compatible with the candidate category.\n227: 5. `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single active pattern by id or by pattern/category.\n228: 6. `ideaRejectedReset` clears all active rejected patterns for the current replay.\n229: \n230: The active cache is capped at 100 entries. When the replay would exceed that cap, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning. Operators can re-add an evicted pattern with another `idea_rejected` event if it remains relevant. Existing `ideaRejected` replay rows are legacy aliases and remain accepted for backward compatibility.\n231: \n232: Ideas lifecycle:\n233: \n234: 1. Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` events only. They must not append `idea_promoted`.\n235: 2. The reducer accumulates observations by `ideaId` or a normalized text-derived id.\n236: 3. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to `1..10`.\n237: 4. When an idea reaches `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`, the reducer appends one idempotent `idea_promoted` event and ranks promoted ideas by observation count, latest observation, then first observation.\n238: 5. `idea_rejected` removes the matching idea from `promotedIdeas` and from ideas-backed next-focus candidates until a reset/removal event clears the active rejected pattern.\n239: \n240: Candidate categories:\n241: \n242: | Category | Candidate source |\n243: |----------|------------------|\n244: | `next-focus` | Strategy next-focus, carried-forward open questions, open questions, and follow-up findings |\n245: | `recovery` | Stuck and blocked-stop recovery strategies |\n246: | `ideas` | Reducer-promoted ideas backlog entries |\n247: | `general` | Cross-category fallback when a narrower category is not known |\n248: \n249: When all candidates in a category are suppressed, continue with the next eligible category or halt for operator input rather than reusing the rejected idea.\n250: \n251: #### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\n252: Dispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n253: ```text\n254: {state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n255: \n256: Research Topic: {config.topic}\n257: Iteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\n258: Focus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\n259: Remaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\n260: Last 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\n261: Resource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\n262: State Files:\n263:   - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n264:   - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n265:   - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\n266: Output: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n267: CONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n268: ```\n269: \n270: #### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n271: \n272: Before dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n273: \n274: - `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n275: - `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n276: - `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n277: \n278: All branches share:\n279: 1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n280: 2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n281: 3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n282: \n283: Per-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n284: \n285: Cross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n286: \n287: Failure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n288: \n289: The dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n290: \n291: #### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n292: \n293: After dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n294: - **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n295: - **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n296: - If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n297:   1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n298:   2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n299:   3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n300: - Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n301: \n302: #### Step 4: Evaluate Results\n303: After agent completes:\n304: 1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n305: 2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n306: 3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n307:    - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n308:    - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n309: 4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n310: 5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n311: 6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n312: 7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n313: \n314: #### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n315: \n316: After evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n317: \n318: 1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n319: 2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n320:    - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n321:    - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n322:    - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n323:    - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n324:    - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n325:    - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n326: 3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n327: 4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n328: 5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n329: 6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n330: \n331: In **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n332: \n333: #### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n334: \n335: This checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n336: \n337: After each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n338: \n339: 1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n340:    ```bash\n341:    git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n342:    git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n343:    git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n344:    git add research/findings-registry.json\n345:    git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n346:    git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n347:    ```\n348: 2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n349: 3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n350: 4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n351: \n352: Checkpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n353: \n354: #### Step 5: Loop Decision\n355: - If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n356: - If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n357: - Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n358: \n359: ### Ideas Backlog Convention\n360: \n361: The canonical ideas backlog is reducer-owned and derived from JSONL lifecycle events. A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` may still exist as operator-authored context, but leaf agents record new machine-discovered tangents with `idea_observed` events.\n362: \n363: #### Check Points\n364: \n365: The orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n366: \n367: 1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it as operator-authored context and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n368: 2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check reducer-promoted ideas before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Promoted ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n369: 3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read JSONL, registry, strategy.md, and any operator-authored ideas file to restore full context\n370: \n371: #### Event Format\n372: \n373: ```json\n374: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_observed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"source\":\"iteration-004.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"}\n375: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_promoted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":5,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"observationCount\":2,\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"firstObservedRun\":4,\"lastObservedRun\":5,\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:01:00Z\"}\n376: {\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_rejected\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":6,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"reason\":\"Operator rejected this direction\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"}\n377: ```\n378: \n379: Users can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents do not promote ideas directly; they emit observations, and the reducer owns promotion, ranking, rejection filtering, and dashboard projection.\n380: \n381: ### Stuck Recovery Protocol\n382: When stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n383: \n384: **Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\n385: Before selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n386: 1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n387: 2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n388:    - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n389:    - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n390:    - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n391:    - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n392:    - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n393: 3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n394: 4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n395: \n396: **Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n397: 1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n398: 2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n399: 3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n400: 4. Reset stuck counter\n401: 5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n402: \n403: ### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n404: \n405: When agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n406: \n407: 1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n408: 2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n409: 3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n410:    - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n411:    - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n412:    - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n413:    - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n414:    - Update strategy.md\n415:    - Append iteration record to JSONL\n416: 4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n417: 5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n418: \n419: **Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n420: \n421: ---\n422: \n423: ## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n424: \n425: An optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n426: \n427: ### When to Use Waves\n428: \n429: - 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n430: - Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n431: - Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n432: \n433: ### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n434: \n435: ```text\n436: Wave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n437:   |\n438:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n439:   +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n440:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n441:   |\n442: Scoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n443:   |\n444: Wave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n445:   +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n446:   +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n447:   |\n448: Repeat until convergence\n449: ```\n450: \n451: ### Scoring and Pruning\n452: \n453: In a future wave-enabled runtime:\n454: 1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n455: 2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n456: 3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n457: 4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n458: 5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n459: \n460: ### Breakthrough Detection\n461: \n462: When any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n463: \n464: 1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n465: 2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n466: 3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n467: 4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n468: \n469: ### Wave JSONL Records\n470: \n471: Wave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n472: \n473: ### Integration with Sequential Loop\n474: \n475: - Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n476: - The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n477: - A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n478: - The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n479: \n480: ---\n481: \n482: ## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n483: \n484: An alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n485: \n486: ### Motivation\n487: \n488: The standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n489: \n490: ### Dispatch Mechanism\n491: \n492: Replace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n493: \n494: 1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n495:    - Strategy.md (current state)\n496:    - Config.json (parameters)\n497:    - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n498:    - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n499:    - Full agent protocol instructions\n500: 2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n501: 3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n502: 4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n503: 5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n504: 6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n505: \n506: ### Trade-offs\n507: \n508: | Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n509: |--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n510: | Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n511: | Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n512: | Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n513: | Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n514: | Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n515: \n516: ### When to Use\n517: \n518: - Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n519: - Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n520: - Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n521: \n522: **Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n523: \n524: ---\n525: \n526: ## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n527: \n528: ### Purpose\n529: Compile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n530: \n531: ### Steps\n532: \n533: 1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n534: 2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n535: 3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n536:    - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n537:    - Organize by section topic\n538:    - Add citations from iteration files\n539:    - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n540:    - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n541:    - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n542:    - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n543:      - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n544:      - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n545:      - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n546:      - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n547:      - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n548:      - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n549: 4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n550: 5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n551: 6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n552: \n553: ### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n554: - If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n555: - If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n556: \n557: ---\n558: \n559: ## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n560: \n561: ### Purpose\n562: Preserve research context to memory system.\n563: \n564: ### Steps\n565: \n566: 1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n567: 2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n568: 3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n569: \n570: ---\n571: \n572: ## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n573: \n574: ```text\n575: [INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n576:     |\n577: [ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n578:     |\n579: [EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n580:     |\n581:     |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n582:     |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n583:     |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n584: \n585: [STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n586:     |\n587:     |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n588:     |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n589: \n590: [SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n591:     |\n592: [SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n593:     |\n594: [COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n595: ```\n596: \n597: Hook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n598: \n599: ---\n600: \n601: ## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n602: \n603: | Error | Phase | Action |\n604: |-------|-------|--------|\n605: | Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n606: | WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n607: | State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n608: | JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n609: | 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n610: | Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n611: | Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n612: \n613: ### State Recovery Protocol\n614: \n615: When state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n616: \n617: | Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n618: |----------|-----------|----------------|\n619: | 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n620: | 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n621: | 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n622: | 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n623: | 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n624: \n625: Each priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n626: \n627: ---\n628: \n629: ## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n630: \n631: In confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n632: \n633: | Gate Location | Behavior |\n634: |---------------|----------|\n635: | After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n636: | After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n637: | Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n638: | After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n639: \n640: ---\n641: \n642: ## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n643: \n644: Deep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n645: \n646: This reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.\n\n(End of file - total 646 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","text":"---\ntitle: Loop Protocol Reference\ndescription: Canonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle with 4 phases, reference-only wave orchestration, and error handling.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"research loop protocol\"\n  - \"research loop lifecycle\"\n  - \"research loop initialization\"\n  - \"research auto resume protocol\"\n  - \"research pause sentinel\"\n  - \"research synthesis phase\"\nimportance_tier: important\ncontextType: implementation\nversion: 1.14.0.29\n---\n\n# Loop Protocol Reference\n\nCanonical specification for the deep research loop lifecycle. Use it as the lifecycle map for initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, and recovery.\n\n---\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nDefine the lifecycle contract for deep-research initialization, iteration, synthesis, save, reference-only dispatch concepts, and error handling.\n\n### When to Use\n\nLoad this reference when running or validating the research loop lifecycle. Use `../convergence/convergence.md` for STOP decisions and `../state/state_format.md` for packet file schemas.\n\n### Core Principle\n\nThe YAML workflow owns lifecycle orchestration, `@deep-research` executes LEAF iterations, and the reducer synchronizes packet state after each iteration and lifecycle transition.\n\n### Phase Model\n\nThe deep research loop has 4 phases: initialization, iteration (repeated), synthesis, and save.\n\nRuntime capability matrix references for parity-sensitive loop behavior:\n- Human-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Machine-readable matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n\n```text\n┌──────────┐     ┌──────────────────────────┐     ┌───────────────────────┐     ┌──────────┐\n│  INIT    │────>│  LOOP                    │────>│  SYNTHESIS            │────>│  SAVE    │\n│          │     │  ┌────────────────────┐  │     │                       │     │          │\n│ Config    │     │  │ Read State         │  │     │ Final                 │     │ Memory   │\n│ Strategy │     │  │ Check Convergence  │  │     │ research/research.md  │     │ Context  │\n│ State    │     │  │ Dispatch Agent     │  │     │ compilation           │     │ Save     │\n│          │     │  │ Evaluate Results   │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  │ Loop Decision      │  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │  └────────┬───────────┘  │     │                       │     │          │\n│          │     │           │ repeat       │     │                       │     │          │\n└──────────┘     └──────────────────────────┘     └───────────────────────┘     └──────────┘\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. PHASE: INITIALIZATION\n\n### Purpose\nSet up all state files for a new research session.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Classify session state before writing**:\n   - `fresh`: no config/state/strategy files exist\n   - `resume`: config + state + strategy all exist and agree\n   - `completed-session`: consistent prior state with `config.status == \"complete\"`\n   - `invalid-state`: partial or contradictory artifacts\n2. **Resolve canonical artifact names**:\n   - Read legacy aliases during the migration window if needed\n   - Write only canonical `deep-research-*` names\n   - Emit a `migration` event for every legacy alias consumed\n3. **Resolve local artifact owner**: `artifact_dir = resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, 'research').artifactDir`, then `mkdir -p {artifact_dir}/iterations`\n4. **Write config**: `research/deep-research-config.json` from template + user parameters\n5. **Initialize state log**: First line of `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` with config record\n6. **Initialize strategy**: `research/deep-research-strategy.md` from template with:\n   - Topic from user input\n   - Initial key questions (3-5, from topic analysis)\n   - Known context from `memory_context()` results (if any), injected only after the strategy file exists\n   - Research boundaries from config\n6a. **Detect resource-map integration state**:\n   - Check `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` once during init\n   - If present: set `resource_map_present = true` in `deep-research-config.json`\n   - Summarize the map into `deep-research-strategy.md` `Known Context`\n   - The summary MUST include per-section entry counts for `READMEs`, `Documents`, `Commands`, `Agents`, `Skills`, `Specs`, `Scripts`, `Tests`, `Config`, and `Meta`\n   - The summary MUST also include a one-line theme summary for each resource-map section\n   - If absent: set `resource_map_present = false` and append `resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate` to `Known Context`\n7. **Initialize findings registry**: `research/findings-registry.json` with empty `openQuestions`, `resolvedQuestions`, `keyFindings`, and `ruledOutDirections`\n7a. **Validate Research Charter**:\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Non-Goals\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - Verify strategy.md contains a \"Stop Conditions\" section (may be empty but must exist)\n   - If either section is missing, append it as an empty placeholder before proceeding\n   - In **confirm mode**: present the charter (topic, key questions, non-goals, stop conditions) for user review before proceeding\n   - In **auto mode**: accept the charter automatically and continue\n8. **Resume only if config, JSONL, and strategy agree**; otherwise halt for repair instead of guessing\n\n### Outputs\n- `research/deep-research-config.json`\n- `research/deep-research-state.jsonl` (1 line)\n- `research/deep-research-strategy.md`\n\n### Auto-Resume Protocol\nIf state files already exist from a prior session:\n1. Verify config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder\n2. Read JSONL, count iteration records\n3. Read strategy.md for current state\n4. Set iteration counter to last completed + 1\n5. Append the canonical resume event to `deep-research-state.jsonl` (all fields below are required by the reducer):\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"parentSessionId\":\"rsr-2026-03-18T10-00-00Z\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":4,\"generation\":1,\"timestamp\":\"2026-03-18T14:05:00Z\"}\n```\n\n6. Continue loop from `step_read_state`.\n\n### Lifecycle Branch Contract (current release)\n\nThe runtime supports three lineage modes today. `fork` and `completed-continue` were described in earlier drafts but have no workflow wiring in this release, so they MUST NOT be exposed to operators. If the long-form lineage feature is picked up later it will arrive with first-class event emission, reducer ancestry handling, and replay fixtures; until then treat the contract below as canonical.\n\n| Mode | Session id | Generation | Archive | JSONL event | When to pick |\n|------|-----------|-----------|---------|-------------|--------------|\n| `new` | fresh | 1 | n/a | implicit (config record) | no existing state |\n| `resume` | same | same | none | `resumed` (see example above) | operator wants to continue the current lineage boundary |\n| `restart` | fresh | `prior + 1` | prior `research/` tree moved under `research_archive/{timestamp}/` | `restarted` (same field set plus `archivedPath`) | operator wants to clear the workspace and replay with a new angle |\n\n**Contract for every persisted lifecycle event**:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"type\": \"event\",\n  \"event\": \"resumed | restarted\",\n  \"mode\": \"research\",\n  \"sessionId\": \"<session id of the new or continuing lineage>\",\n  \"parentSessionId\": \"<session id of the prior lineage (equals sessionId on resume)>\",\n  \"lineageMode\": \"resume | restart\",\n  \"generation\": <number>,\n  \"continuedFromRun\": <number or null>,\n  \"archivedPath\": \"<path or null>\",\n  \"timestamp\": \"<ISO 8601>\"\n}\n```\n\nEvery field in the contract MUST be present on every persisted lifecycle event. `archivedPath` is null for `resumed` and set to the archive destination for `restarted`. `continuedFromRun` is the number of completed iteration records before the lifecycle boundary. Reducer parity tests ensure the dashboard `Lifecycle` section reads exactly those fields.\n\n---\n\n## 3. PHASE: ITERATION LOOP\n\n### Loop Steps (repeated until convergence)\n\n#### Step 1: Read State\n- Read `deep-research-state.jsonl` -- count iterations, get last newInfoRatio\n- Read `deep-research-strategy.md` -- get next focus, remaining questions\n\n#### Step 2: Check Convergence\nRun the convergence algorithm (see convergence.md):\n- Max iterations reached? STOP\n- Stuck count >= threshold? STUCK_RECOVERY\n- Average newInfoRatio < threshold? STOP\n- All questions answered? STOP\n- Otherwise: CONTINUE\n\n#### Step 2c: Quality Guard Check\n\nWhen the convergence algorithm returns STOP:\n1. Run quality guard checks (see convergence.md §2.4)\n2. Verify minimum coverage, source diversity, and question resolution thresholds\n3. If **all guards pass**: proceed with STOP, exit to synthesis\n4. If **any guard fails**: override decision to CONTINUE\n   - Log each violation: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"guard_violation\",\"guard\":\"<name>\",\"iteration\":N,\"detail\":\"<reason>\"}`\n   - Persist the blocked legal-stop outcome: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"blockedBy\":[\"<gate>\"],\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":true,\"score\":0.0},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":false,\"answered\":X,\"total\":Y},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":false,\"sources\":N},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":true}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"<one-line hint>\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Append failed guard details to strategy.md \"Active Risks\" section\n5. The loop continues until BOTH convergence AND quality guards pass simultaneously\n6. Guard checks apply only to STOP decisions - CONTINUE and STUCK_RECOVERY bypass this step\n\nIf the legal-stop decision tree returns `blocked`, the workflow MUST append the `blocked_stop` JSONL event before continuing. Reducers and dashboards consume the persisted event; they must not infer blocked-stop state solely from prose logs.\n\n#### Step 2a: Check Pause Sentinel\n\nBefore dispatching, check for a pause sentinel file:\n\n1. Check if `research/.deep-research-pause` exists\n2. If present:\n   - Log event to JSONL: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":N,\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\",\"timestamp\":\"<ISO8601>\",\"sessionId\":\"<sid>\",\"generation\":G}`\n   - Halt the loop with message:\n     ```text\n     Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\n     Current state: Iteration {N}, {remaining} questions remaining.\n     ```\n   - Do NOT exit to synthesis -- the loop is suspended, not stopped\n3. On resume (file deleted and loop restarted):\n   - Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"fromIteration\":N}`\n   - Continue from step_read_state\n\nPause and recovery events use the frozen stop-reason enum on the live path. Raw `paused` and `stuck_recovery` labels are legacy aliases and MUST be normalized to `userPaused` and `stuckRecovery` at emission time.\n\n**Use case**: In autonomous mode, this provides the only graceful intervention mechanism short of killing the process. Users can create the sentinel file at any time to pause research between iterations.\n\n#### Step 2b: Generate State Summary\n\nGenerate a compact state summary (~200 tokens) for injection into the dispatch prompt:\n\n```text\nSTATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\nSegment: {current_segment} | Iteration: {N} of {max}\nQuestions: {answered}/{total} answered | Last focus: {last_focus}\nLast 2 ratios: {ratio_N-1} -> {ratio_N} | Stuck count: {stuck_count}\nRecovery: {active_recovery_strategy or \"none\"}\nNext focus: {strategy.nextFocus}\n```\n\nThis summary is prepended to the dispatch context (Step 3) to ensure the agent has baseline context even if detailed strategy.md reading fails or is incomplete. It serves as a redundant context channel.\n\n#### Step 2d: Rejected Pattern Cache Check\n\nBefore selecting the next-focus, recovery, or ideas-backed candidate for dispatch, read the reducer-owned rejected-pattern cache and promoted ideas backlog from the findings registry.\n\nRejected-cache lifecycle:\n\n1. `idea_rejected` appends one rejected pattern to JSONL with `ideaId`, `idea` or `pattern`, optional `category`, optional `reason`, and normal lifecycle fields.\n2. The reducer derives the active cache from JSONL events; generated registry and dashboard files expose `rejectedPatterns`, `rejectedPatternIndex`, and `suppressedCandidates`.\n3. Exact suppression compares normalized candidate text against normalized rejected text.\n4. Fuzzy suppression uses `rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold` from config when present, otherwise `0.85`, and only applies when the rejected category is compatible with the candidate category.\n5. `ideaRejectedRemoved` removes a single active pattern by id or by pattern/category.\n6. `ideaRejectedReset` clears all active rejected patterns for the current replay.\n\nThe active cache is capped at 100 entries. When the replay would exceed that cap, the oldest active entry is evicted and the reducer emits a warning. Operators can re-add an evicted pattern with another `idea_rejected` event if it remains relevant. Existing `ideaRejected` replay rows are legacy aliases and remain accepted for backward compatibility.\n\nIdeas lifecycle:\n\n1. Leaf agents may append `idea_observed` events only. They must not append `idea_promoted`.\n2. The reducer accumulates observations by `ideaId` or a normalized text-derived id.\n3. `minIdeaObservations` defaults to `2` and is clamped to `1..10`.\n4. When an idea reaches `observationCount >= minIdeaObservations`, the reducer appends one idempotent `idea_promoted` event and ranks promoted ideas by observation count, latest observation, then first observation.\n5. `idea_rejected` removes the matching idea from `promotedIdeas` and from ideas-backed next-focus candidates until a reset/removal event clears the active rejected pattern.\n\nCandidate categories:\n\n| Category | Candidate source |\n|----------|------------------|\n| `next-focus` | Strategy next-focus, carried-forward open questions, open questions, and follow-up findings |\n| `recovery` | Stuck and blocked-stop recovery strategies |\n| `ideas` | Reducer-promoted ideas backlog entries |\n| `general` | Cross-category fallback when a narrower category is not known |\n\nWhen all candidates in a category are suppressed, continue with the next eligible category or halt for operator input rather than reusing the rejected idea.\n\n#### Step 3: Dispatch Agent\nDispatch `@deep-research` with explicit context:\n```text\n{state_summary}  // Auto-generated (Step 2b)\n\nResearch Topic: {config.topic}\nIteration: {N} of {maxIterations}\nFocus Area: {strategy.nextFocus}\nRemaining Questions: {strategy.remainingQuestions}\nLast 3 Iterations Summary: {brief summaries}\nResource Map: if `config.resource_map_present == true`, prior-inventoried files are listed in `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md`; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.\nState Files:\n  - Config: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\n  - State: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\n  - Strategy: {artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\nOutput: Write findings to {artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\nCONSTRAINT: LEAF agent -- do NOT dispatch sub-agents\n```\n\n#### Executor Resolution (spec 018 + 019)\n\nBefore dispatching, the YAML resolves the executor via `parseExecutorConfig` from `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/executor-config.ts`. The resolved `config.executor.kind` selects the dispatch branch:\n\n- `native` (spec 018): dispatch `@deep-research` agent with model Opus.\n- `cli-opencode` (spec 018): pipe rendered prompt via stdin to `opencode run --model X -c model_reasoning_effort=Y -c service_tier=Z -c approval_policy=never --sandbox workspace-write`.\n- `cli-claude-code` (spec 019): `claude -p \"$(cat prompt)\" --model X --permission-mode acceptEdits --output-format text` with optional `--effort Y`. Default permission-mode is `plan` (read-only); we override to `acceptEdits` so iteration writes succeed.\n\nAll branches share:\n1. Pre-dispatch prompt rendering via `renderPromptPack` (writes to `{artifact_dir}/prompts/iteration-{n}.md`).\n2. Post-dispatch validation via `validateIterationOutputs` (asserts iteration file + JSONL delta + required fields).\n3. Executor audit append via `appendExecutorAuditToLastRecord` (skipped when kind=='native').\n\nPer-kind flag-compatibility is enforced at config parse time by `EXECUTOR_KIND_FLAG_SUPPORT` in `executor-config.ts`. Setting a flag that the chosen kind does not support throws `ExecutorConfigError` before dispatch.\n\nCross-CLI delegation (a running executor invoking other CLIs via its shell) is documented design intent. Runtime recursion detection is out of scope; see the SKILL.md Cross-CLI Delegation subsection.\n\nFailure handling remains unchanged from spec 018: `schema_mismatch` → conflict event → 3 consecutive failures → `stuck_recovery`.\n\nThe dispatch context may include a suggested `focusTrack` label (e.g., `\"focusTrack\": \"performance\"`, `\"focusTrack\": \"security\"`). Agents may tag their iteration with this track label for post-hoc grouping and analysis. Track labels are metadata only - the orchestrator does not use them for loop decisions.\n\n#### Step 3a: Per-Iteration Budget\n\nAfter dispatch, the orchestrator monitors the running iteration against budget limits:\n- **Tool call count**: tracked against `config.maxToolCallsPerIteration` (default: 12)\n- **Elapsed time**: tracked against `config.maxMinutesPerIteration` (default: 10)\n- If either limit is exceeded and no iteration file has been written yet:\n  1. Mark the iteration as `\"status\": \"timeout\"` in the JSONL record\n  2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"iteration_timeout\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"tool_calls|elapsed_time\"}`\n  3. Continue to the next iteration (do not retry the timed-out iteration)\n- Budget limits are soft caps - if the agent is actively writing its iteration file when the limit is reached, allow completion\n\n#### Step 4: Evaluate Results\nAfter agent completes:\n1. Verify `{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md` was created\n2. Verify JSONL was appended with iteration record\n3. Run reducer with `{ latestJSONLDelta, newIterationFile, priorReducedState }`\n   - This is a **delta refresh**, not a full replay of every historical JSONL row on each iteration.\n   - The reducer consumes only the newest JSONL slice plus the latest iteration artifact against the previously reduced packet state.\n4. Verify reducer refreshed `deep-research-strategy.md`, `findings-registry.json`, and `deep-research-dashboard.md`\n5. Verify the refreshed packet surfaces reflect the new iteration evidence\n6. Extract `newInfoRatio` from JSONL record\n7. Track stuck count: skip if `status == \"thought\"` (no change), reset to 0 if `status == \"insight\"` (breakthrough counts as progress), increment if `newInfoRatio < config.convergenceThreshold`, reset otherwise\n\n#### Step 4a: Generate Dashboard\n\nAfter evaluating iteration results, generate a human-readable dashboard:\n\n1. Read JSONL state log, findings registry, and strategy.md\n2. Generate or regenerate `research/deep-research-dashboard.md` with the following sections:\n   - **Iteration table**: `| run | focus | newInfoRatio | findings count | status |`\n   - **Question status**: `X/Y answered` with itemized list (answered vs remaining)\n   - **Trend**: Last 3 newInfoRatio values with direction indicator (ascending, descending, flat)\n   - **Dead ends**: Consolidated from all iteration `ruledOut` data\n   - **Next focus**: Current value from strategy.md\n   - **Active risks**: Guard violations, stuck count, budget warnings\n3. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"dashboard_generated\",\"iteration\":N}`\n4. The dashboard is **auto-generated only** - never manually edited\n5. The dashboard file is overwritten each iteration (not appended)\n6. Dashboard generation is non-blocking: if it fails, log a warning and continue the loop\n\nIn **confirm mode**, the dashboard is displayed to the user at each iteration approval gate. In **auto mode**, it is written silently for post-hoc review.\n\n#### Step 4b: Checkpoint Commit (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nThis checkpointing pattern is documented for reference, but current runtimes should not assume it is available.\n\nAfter each iteration is verified (JSONL appended, iteration file written, reducer outputs refreshed):\n\n1. **Stage targeted files only** (never `git add -A`):\n   ```bash\n   git add research/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\n   git add research/deep-research-state.jsonl\n   git add research/deep-research-strategy.md\n   git add research/findings-registry.json\n   git add research/deep-research-dashboard.md\n   git add research/research.md  # if it exists\n   ```\n2. **Sanitize**: Exclude `.env`, credentials, large binaries from staging\n3. **Commit**: `git commit -m \"chore(deep-research): iteration {NNN} complete\"`\n4. **On commit failure**: Log warning and continue (checkpoint is non-blocking)\n\nCheckpoint commits provide rollback points: `git log -- research/` shows the last good state for the research packet. If state corruption occurs, `git checkout HEAD~1 -- research/deep-research-state.jsonl` restores the previous version.\n\n#### Step 5: Loop Decision\n- If convergence check returns STOP: exit to synthesis\n- If STUCK_RECOVERY: modify focus directive, reset stuck count, continue\n- Otherwise: increment iteration counter, go to Step 1\n\n### Ideas Backlog Convention\n\nThe canonical ideas backlog is reducer-owned and derived from JSONL lifecycle events. A persistent ideas file at `research/research-ideas.md` may still exist as operator-authored context, but leaf agents record new machine-discovered tangents with `idea_observed` events.\n\n#### Check Points\n\nThe orchestrator checks the ideas backlog at three points:\n\n1. **Init**: During strategy initialization, if `research/research-ideas.md` exists from a prior session, read it as operator-authored context and incorporate relevant ideas into the initial key questions or \"Next Focus\"\n2. **Stuck**: During stuck recovery (Step 2a of the recovery protocol in convergence.md), check reducer-promoted ideas before defaulting to generic recovery strategies. Promoted ideas often provide the best escape from stuck states\n3. **Resume**: On auto-resume, read JSONL, registry, strategy.md, and any operator-authored ideas file to restore full context\n\n#### Event Format\n\n```json\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_observed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":4,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"source\":\"iteration-004.md\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:00:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_promoted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":5,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"observationCount\":2,\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"firstObservedRun\":4,\"lastObservedRun\":5,\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:01:00Z\"}\n{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"idea_rejected\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":6,\"ideaId\":\"idea-cache-stampede\",\"idea\":\"Investigate cache stampede mitigation\",\"category\":\"ideas\",\"reason\":\"Operator rejected this direction\",\"timestamp\":\"2026-05-24T00:02:00Z\"}\n```\n\nUsers can edit `research-ideas.md` between sessions to steer future iterations. Agents do not promote ideas directly; they emit observations, and the reducer owns promotion, ranking, rejection filtering, and dashboard projection.\n\n### Stuck Recovery Protocol\nWhen stuckThreshold consecutive iterations show no progress (default: 3, configurable via config.json):\n\n**Step 0: Classify Failure Mode**\nBefore selecting a recovery strategy, classify why progress stalled:\n1. Read the last N iteration files (where N = stuckThreshold) to determine the failure pattern\n2. Classify into one of the following modes:\n   - `shallow_sources` - iterations find content but lack depth or authoritative sources\n   - `contradictory` - iterations return conflicting information without resolution\n   - `too_broad` - focus area is too wide, producing scattered low-value findings\n   - `repetitive` - iterations keep rediscovering the same information\n   - `exhausted` - the topic area has been thoroughly explored with diminishing returns\n3. Select a targeted recovery prompt based on the classification (see convergence.md §4 for category-specific strategies)\n4. Log classification: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuck_classified\",\"mode\":\"<classification>\",\"iteration\":N}`\n\n**Steps 1-5: Execute Recovery**\n1. Read strategy.md \"What Worked\" section\n2. Identify least-explored question from \"Key Questions\"\n3. Set next focus to: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope to {least-explored-area}. Try a fundamentally different approach.\" (refined by classification)\n4. Reset stuck counter\n5. If recovery iteration also shows no progress: exit to synthesis with gaps documented\n\n### Step 3b: Direct Mode Fallback (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nWhen agent dispatch fails after the earlier recovery tiers are exhausted:\n\n1. Detect dispatch failure: Task tool timeout, API overload (529), or agent crash\n2. Log event: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"direct_mode\",\"iteration\":N,\"reason\":\"dispatch_failure\"}`\n3. Orchestrator absorbs the iteration work:\n   - Read state files (JSONL + strategy.md)\n   - Determine focus from strategy \"Next Focus\"\n   - Execute 3-5 research actions directly\n   - Write `research/iterations/iteration-NNN.md`\n   - Update strategy.md\n   - Append iteration record to JSONL\n4. Continue loop normally after direct-mode iteration completes\n5. If direct mode also fails, escalate to the final user-escalation tier\n\n**Note**: Direct mode iterations are logged with `\"directMode\": true` in their JSONL record for diagnostic tracking.\n\n---\n\n## 4. WAVE ORCHESTRATION PROTOCOL (REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn optional parallel execution concept for research topics with multiple independent questions. Treat this as reference guidance only; the live workflow remains sequential and does **not** emit wave-specific JSONL events or routing today.\n\n### When to Use Waves\n\n- 3+ independent key questions identified during initialization\n- Questions do not depend on each other's answers\n- Parallelism is beneficial (time-constrained research, broad survey)\n\n### Wave Execution Model (conceptual only)\n\n```text\nWave 1: Dispatch N agents on independent questions\n  |\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 --> iteration-001.md (newInfoRatio: 0.8)\n  +-- Agent B: Question 2 --> iteration-002.md (newInfoRatio: 0.3)\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 --> iteration-003.md (newInfoRatio: 0.7)\n  |\nScoring: Rank by newInfoRatio, prune below median only in a future runtime that explicitly adds wave support\n  |\nWave 2: Follow-up on top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2))\n  +-- Agent A: Question 1 follow-up --> iteration-004.md\n  +-- Agent C: Question 3 follow-up --> iteration-005.md\n  |\nRepeat until convergence\n```\n\n### Scoring and Pruning\n\nIn a future wave-enabled runtime:\n1. Rank all wave iterations by `newInfoRatio`\n2. Compute wave median: `median([i.newInfoRatio for i in wave_iterations])`\n3. **Prune**: Questions with newInfoRatio below median would be deprioritized\n4. **Promote**: Top-K questions (K = ceil(N/2)) would get follow-up iterations\n5. Pruned questions would move to the ideas backlog, not be discarded\n\n### Breakthrough Detection\n\nWhen any single iteration in a wave achieves `newInfoRatio > 2x wave_average`:\n\n1. Flag as **breakthrough**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"breakthrough\",\"iteration\":N,\"ratio\":X.XX}`\n2. Generate 2-3 adjacent questions from the breakthrough findings\n3. Prioritize these adjacent questions in the next wave\n4. Breakthrough iterations are NEVER pruned\n\n### Wave JSONL Records\n\nWave-specific fields and events are **not part of the current persisted contract**. Until a runtime explicitly ships wave support, keep iteration records and events on the standard sequential schema only.\n\n### Integration with Sequential Loop\n\n- Waves are an ALTERNATIVE to sequential iteration, not a replacement\n- The convergence algorithm applies identically (uses all iteration records)\n- A future wave-capable runtime could transition back to sequential mode when questions narrow to 1-2\n- The current runtime never spawns a wave automatically\n\n---\n\n## 5. CONTEXT ISOLATION DISPATCH (EXPERIMENTAL, REFERENCE-ONLY)\n\nAn alternative dispatch mechanism that guarantees fresh context per iteration by launching a new OS process. Treat this as reference-only unless the runtime explicitly implements alternate CLI dispatch.\n\n### Motivation\n\nThe standard dispatch (Task tool) shares the parent session's token budget. In long research sessions (10+ iterations), this may cause context compression that degrades reasoning quality. Process-level isolation eliminates this risk.\n\n### Dispatch Mechanism\n\nReplace Task tool dispatch with shell-level `claude -p` invocation:\n\n1. **Generate prompt**: Orchestrator builds a self-contained prompt from:\n   - Strategy.md (current state)\n   - Config.json (parameters)\n   - Last N iteration summaries (from JSONL)\n   - Compact state summary (Step 2b)\n   - Full agent protocol instructions\n2. **Write to temp file**: `scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md`\n3. **Execute**: `claude -p \"$(cat scratch/.dispatch-prompt-{NNN}.md)\" --max-turns 50 --output-format json`\n4. **Collect output**: Agent writes iteration file directly to disk\n5. **Verify**: Orchestrator checks iteration file and JSONL were created\n6. **Cleanup**: Remove temp prompt file\n\n### Trade-offs\n\n| Aspect | Task Tool Dispatch | `claude -p` Dispatch |\n|--------|-------------------|---------------------|\n| Context freshness | Shared budget, may degrade | Guaranteed fresh |\n| Token cost | Lower (cached context) | Higher (full context per call) |\n| Latency | Lower (in-process) | Higher (new process startup) |\n| Context size | Limited by parent budget | Full model context available |\n| Error handling | In-process exceptions | Process exit codes |\n\n### When to Use\n\n- Autonomous/unattended research sessions (overnight runs)\n- Research past iteration 8+ where context degradation is measurable\n- Critical research where reasoning quality must not degrade\n\n**Status**: Reference-only. Track adoption based on need for fully autonomous overnight research sessions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. PHASE: SYNTHESIS\n\n### Purpose\nCompile all iteration findings into final research/research.md. The synthesis workflow owns the canonical `research/research.md` output.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Read all iteration files**: `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`\n2. **Read strategy.md**: Final state of questions, approaches\n3. **Compile research/research.md**: Merge findings into 17-section format\n   - Deduplicate overlapping findings\n   - Organize by section topic\n   - Add citations from iteration files\n   - Cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in the References section when `config.resource_map_present == true`\n   - Do not synthesize a placeholder reference when `resource-map.md` was absent at init\n   - Note unanswered questions in Section 12 (Open Questions)\n   - **Include a mandatory \"## Eliminated Alternatives\" section** as primary research output:\n     - Consolidate all `ruledOut` entries from iteration JSONL records\n     - Consolidate all `## Dead Ends` sections from iteration files\n     - Format as a table: `| Approach | Reason Eliminated | Evidence | Iteration(s) |`\n     - This section documents negative knowledge (what was tried and why it failed)\n     - Treat as primary research output - not an appendix or afterthought\n     - Place after Section 11 (Recommendations) and before Section 12 (Open Questions)\n4. **If reopening a completed packet later**: snapshot this file as `research/synthesis-v{generation}.md` before any `completed-continue` flow\n5. **Update config status**: Set `status: \"complete\"` in config.json\n6. **Final JSONL entry**: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"synthesis_complete\",\"totalIterations\":N,\"answeredCount\":A,\"totalQuestions\":Q,\"stopReason\":\"converged\"}`\n\n### Progressive vs Final Synthesis\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: true` (default): research/research.md was updated each iteration. Final synthesis is a cleanup pass.\n- If `progressiveSynthesis: false`: research/research.md is created from scratch during synthesis.\n\n---\n\n## 7. PHASE: SAVE\n\n### Purpose\nPreserve research context to memory system.\n\n### Steps\n\n1. **Generate context**: `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js {spec_folder}`\n2. **No extra indexing step in the live contract**: `generate-context.js` is the supported save boundary for this workflow\n3. **Verify**: Confirm memory/*.md file created with proper anchors\n\n---\n\n## 8. STATE TRANSITIONS\n\n```text\n[INITIALIZED] --> config + strategy + state created\n    |\n[ITERATING] --> agent dispatched, executing research\n    |\n[EVALUATING] --> iteration complete, checking convergence\n    |\n    |-- newInfoRatio >= threshold --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- stuck_count >= stuckThreshold --> [STUCK_RECOVERY]\n    |-- converged or max_iterations --> [SYNTHESIZING]\n\n[STUCK_RECOVERY] --> widen focus, try different approach\n    |\n    |-- recovered (newInfoRatio > 0) --> [ITERATING]\n    |-- still stuck --> [SYNTHESIZING] (gaps documented)\n\n[SYNTHESIZING] --> final research/research.md compilation\n    |\n[SAVING] --> memory context preservation\n    |\n[COMPLETE] --> all artifacts created, loop finished\n```\n\nHook-capable and non-hook runtimes must follow the same state machine. Hooks may pre-prime context, but they must not change which lifecycle branch the packet selects.\n\n---\n\n## 9. ERROR HANDLING\n\n| Error | Phase | Action |\n|-------|-------|--------|\n| Agent dispatch timeout | Loop | Retry once with reduced scope. If second timeout, mark iteration as \"timeout\" and continue |\n| WebFetch fails | Loop | Log URL in iteration file, try alternative source, continue with available data |\n| State file missing | Init/Loop | If JSONL missing: re-initialize. If strategy missing: reconstruct from JSONL |\n| JSONL malformed | Loop | Skip malformed lines, reconstruct from valid entries |\n| 3+ consecutive failures | Loop | Halt loop, enter synthesis with partial findings |\n| Agent dispatch failure (API overload, timeout) | Loop | Escalate through the documented recovery ladder in order. Direct mode fallback is reference-only unless the runtime explicitly supports it. |\n| Memory save fails | Save | Preserve the current `{artifact_dir}` packet as backup, then log the error |\n\n### State Recovery Protocol\n\nWhen state files are missing or corrupted, apply this 5-priority cascade:\n\n| Priority | Condition | Recovery Action |\n|----------|-----------|----------------|\n| 1 (Primary) | JSONL exists and parseable | Normal operation (with fault-tolerant parsing) |\n| 2 (Strategy rebuild) | JSONL exists, strategy.md missing | Reconstruct strategy from JSONL: extract questions, focus areas, newInfoRatio trend. Create minimal strategy.md |\n| 3 (JSONL reconstruction) | JSONL missing/corrupt, iteration files exist | Scan `research/iterations/iteration-*.md`, parse Assessment sections, reconstruct JSONL with `status: \"reconstructed\"` |\n| 4 (Config-only restart) | Only config.json remains | Restart from initialization phase using config parameters. Log: `{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"fresh_restart\",\"reason\":\"state_files_missing\"}` |\n| 5 (Abort) | Config.json also missing | Cannot recover. Report error and halt. |\n\nEach priority level is attempted in order. If a level fails, fall through to the next. See state_format.md for JSONL reconstruction details.\n\n---\n\n## 10. CONFIRM MODE ADDITIONS\n\nIn confirm mode, the YAML workflow adds approval gates:\n\n| Gate Location | Behavior |\n|---------------|----------|\n| After initialization | Show config and initial strategy. Wait for approval |\n| After each iteration | Show iteration findings and convergence status. Options: Continue, Adjust Focus, Stop |\n| Before synthesis | Show summary of all iterations. Wait for approval to synthesize |\n| After synthesis | Show final research/research.md summary. Approve or request revisions |\n\n---\n\n## 11. REVIEW MODE ROUTING\n\nDeep-review lifecycle, convergence, state schemas, traceability protocols, and report contracts live in the sibling `deep-review` skill.\n\nThis reference keeps only the routing rule: do not document or execute review-mode loop behavior from `deep-research`. Route review requests to `deep-review/SKILL.md` and its references.","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":646,"totalLines":646,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md","time":{"start":1783486563462,"end":1783486563548}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09753fc99b3c65c6016a4dd86361588191ba7df4e0f9f3a8ad"}},"id":"prt_f4015445c001SNL1rMtFRhl687","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6"}}
{"type":"step_finish","timestamp":1783486564051,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f401546d1001QiOBdOUHo3mz3t","reason":"tool-calls","snapshot":"c6d101db0e4553dfd780695c86ca401b2aba19e2","messageID":"msg_f4014f70d001PFNGBRhHtOaWZ6","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","type":"step-finish","tokens":{"total":28889,"input":7899,"output":506,"reasoning":516,"cache":{"write":0,"read":19968}},"cost":0}}
{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783486566195,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f40154f32001uKhyWztJx7iE5W","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","snapshot":"c6d101db0e4553dfd780695c86ca401b2aba19e2","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486574794,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_VPJNnmAn2wMU7E1nxugBTEtU","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1,"limit":2400},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n2: # DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n3: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n4: # YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n5: # - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n6: #   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n7: #   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n8: # - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n9: #   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n10: #   free-form narrative prose.\n11: # - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n12: #   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n13: #\n14: # GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n15: # - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n16: #   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n17: #   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n18: #   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n19: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n20: role: Deep Research Loop Manager\n21: purpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\n22: action: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\n23: operating_mode:\n24:   workflow: iterative_loop\n25:   workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n26:   workflow_execution: autonomous\n27:   approvals: none\n28:   tracking: progressive_research_state\n29:   validation: convergence_detection\n30: \n31: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n32: # OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n33: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n34: operating_principles:\n35:   core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n36:   approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n37:   mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n38: \n39: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n40: # USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n41: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n42: user_inputs:\n43:   research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n44:   spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n45:   max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n46:   convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n47: \n48: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n49: # CONTEXT LOADING\n50: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n51: context_loading:\n52:   trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n53:   purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n54:   mcp_integration:\n55:     tool: memory_context\n56:     note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n57:     parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n58:   when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n59:   behavior:\n60:     if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n61:     if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n62: \n63: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n64: # SKILL REFERENCE\n65: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n66: skill_reference:\n67:   skill: deep-loop-workflows\n68:   skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n69:   references:\n70:     loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n71:     spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n72:     state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n73:     convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n74:   templates:\n75:     config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n76:     strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n77: \n78: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n79: # AGENT CONFIGURATION\n80: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n81: agent_config:\n82:   agent: deep-research\n83:   agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n84:   # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n85:   model: opus\n86:   leaf_only: true\n87:   tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n88:   mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n89:   tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n90: \n91: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: # STATE FILE PATHS\n93: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: state_paths:\n95:   # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n96:   # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n97:   # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n98:   packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n99:   config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n100:   state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n101:   status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n102:   strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n103:   registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n104:   dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n105:   pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n106:   run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n107:   lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n108:   prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n109:   iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n110:   iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n111:   # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n112:   # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n113:   # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n114:   # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n115:   # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n116:   delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n117:   delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n118:   research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n119:   resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n120:   archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n121:   synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n122: \n123: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n124: # WORKFLOW\n125: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n126: workflow:\n127: \n128:   step_resolve_artifact_root:\n129:     description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n130:     note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n131:     branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n132:     if_present:\n133:       bind:\n134:         artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n135:         artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n136:         artifact_subfolder: null\n137:         artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n138:     if_absent:\n139:       command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n140:       outputs:\n141:         - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n142:         - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n143:         - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n144:         - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n145: \n146:   step_fanout_spawn:\n147:     description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n148:     skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n149:     instructions: |\n150:       Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n151:       isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n152:       After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n153:       phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n154:       phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n155:     sub_steps:\n156:       step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n157:         description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n158:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n159:         command: |\n160:           node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n161:             --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n162:             --loop-type research \\\n163:             --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n164:             --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n165:             --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n166:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n167:         wait_for_completion: true\n168:       step_fanout_spawn_native:\n169:         description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n170:         skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n171:         for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n172:         dispatch:\n173:           agent: deep-research\n174:           model: opus\n175:           context: |\n176:             Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n177:               spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n178:               config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n179:               session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n180:               executor: native\n181:             Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n182:         wait_for_completion: true\n183: \n184:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n185:   # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n186:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n187:   phase_init:\n188:     purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n189:     steps:\n190: \n191:       step_preflight_contract:\n192:         action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n193:         verify:\n194:           - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n195:           - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n196:           - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n197:           - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n198:         on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n199: \n200:       step_create_directories:\n201:         action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n202:         command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n203: \n204:       step_detect_resource_map:\n205:         action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n206:         inspect:\n207:           - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n208:         classify:\n209:           present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n210:           absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n211:         outputs:\n212:           - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n213:           - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n214: \n215:       step_resolve_canonical_names:\n216:         action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n217:         inspect_legacy:\n218:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n219:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n220:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n221:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n222:           - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n223:         migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n224:         on_legacy_read:\n225:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n226: \n227:       step_acquire_lock:\n228:         action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n229:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n230:         on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n231:         note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n232:         # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n233:         # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n234:         on_halt:\n235:           action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n236:           applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n237:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n238:         on_cancel:\n239:           action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n240:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n241:         on_workflow_exit:\n242:           action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n243:           command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n244: \n245:       step_classify_session:\n246:         action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n247:         inspect:\n248:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n249:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n250:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n251:         classify:\n252:           fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n253:           resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n254:           completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n255:           invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n256:         outputs:\n257:           - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n258:         on_resume:\n259:           # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n260:           # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n261:           gate3_classification: write-path\n262:           gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n263:           log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n264:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n265:           skip_to: phase_loop\n266:         on_restart:\n267:           action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n268:           command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n269:           set:\n270:             lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n271:             parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n272:             generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n273:           append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n274:           skip_to: step_create_config\n275:         note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n276:         on_completed_session:\n277:           log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n278:           halt: true\n279:           message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n280:         on_invalid_state:\n281:           halt: true\n282:           message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n283:         on_fresh:\n284:           action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n285: \n286:       step_resolve_session_id:\n287:         action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n288:         branch_on: \"session_id\"\n289:         if_present:\n290:           bind:\n291:             session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n292:         if_absent:\n293:           bind:\n294:             session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n295: \n296:       step_create_config:\n297:         action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n298:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n299:         populate:\n300:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n301:           maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n302:           minIterations: 3\n303:           # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n304:           convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n305:           convergenceMode: \"default\"\n306:           stuckThreshold: 3\n307:           minIdeaObservations: 2\n308:           maxDurationMinutes: 120\n309:           specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n310:           resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n311:           # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n312:           # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n313:           resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n314:           createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n315:           status: \"initialized\"\n316:           executionMode: \"auto\"\n317:           lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n318:           lineage.parentSessionId: null\n319:           lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n320:           lineage.generation: 1\n321:           lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n322:           nextRunAt: null\n323:           remainingDelayMs: null\n324:         output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n325: \n326:       step_create_state_log:\n327:         action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n328:         # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n329:         content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n330:         output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n331: \n332:       step_create_strategy:\n333:         action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n334:         template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n335:         populate:\n336:           topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n337:           key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n338:           known_context: \"None\"\n339:           known_context_summary: \"None\"\n340:           max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n341:           convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n342:         output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n343: \n344:       step_create_registry:\n345:         action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n346:         content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n347:         output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n348: \n349:       step_enrich_strategy_context:\n350:         action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n351:         condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n352:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n353:         note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n354: \n355:       step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n356:         action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n357:         edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n358:         note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n359: \n360:       step_detect_spec_present:\n361:         action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n362:         inspect:\n363:           - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n364:           - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n365:         classify:\n366:           no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n367:           spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n368:           spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n369:           conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n370:         outputs:\n371:           - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n372:           - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n373:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n374: \n375:       step_preinit_spec_branch:\n376:         action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n377:         protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n378:         branches:\n379:           no-spec:\n380:             create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n381:             seed_markers:\n382:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n383:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n384:             requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n385:             scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n386:             set:\n387:               folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n388:               validate_spec_doc: true\n389:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n390:           spec-present:\n391:             edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n392:             set:\n393:               validate_spec_doc: true\n394:             idempotency_check:\n395:               host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n396:               normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n397:               if_match:\n398:                 skip_append: true\n399:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n400:               if_no_match:\n401:                 append_only:\n402:                   - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n403:                     content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n404:                   - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n405:                     content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n406:                 append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n407:           spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n408:             verify_markers:\n409:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n410:               - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n411:             set:\n412:               validate_spec_doc: false\n413:             note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n414:           conflict-detected:\n415:             append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n416:             halt: true\n417: \n418:       step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n419:         action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n420:         condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n421:         command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n422:         note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n423: \n424:       step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n425:         action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n426:         skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n427:         canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n428:         command: |\n429:           node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n430:           import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n431: \n432:           import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n433:           import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n434: \n435:           const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n436:           const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n437:           const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n438:           const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n439:           const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n440:           const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n441:           const row = {\n442:             event: 'started',\n443:             label: 'single',\n444:             at: timestamp,\n445:             duration_ms: 0,\n446:             loop_type: 'research',\n447:             sessionId,\n448:             generation,\n449:             gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n450:           };\n451: \n452:           const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n453:             diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n454:             diffField: 'state_hash',\n455:           });\n456:           if (appended) {\n457:             try {\n458:               appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n459:                 producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n460:                 stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n461:                 subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n462:                 event: row.event,\n463:                 status: 'running',\n464:               });\n465:             } catch {}\n466:           }\n467:           EOF\n468:         working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n469:         outputs:\n470:           - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n471: \n472:       step_init_complete:\n473:         log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n474:         set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n475: \n476:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n477:   # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n478:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n479:   phase_loop:\n480:     purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n481:     repeat: true\n482:     max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n483:     steps:\n484: \n485:       step_read_state:\n486:         action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n487:         read:\n488:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n489:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n490:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n491:         extract:\n492:           - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n493:           - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n494:           - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n495:           - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n496:           - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n497:           - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n498:           - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n499:           - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n500:           - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n501:           - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n502:           - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n503:           - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n504:           - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n505:           - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n506:           - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n507:           - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n508:           - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n509:           - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n510:           - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n511:           - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n512:           - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n513:           - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n514:           - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n515:           - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n516:           - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n517:           - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n518:           - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n519:           - convergence_mode: \"Extract convergenceMode when it is 'default' or 'off'; default to 'default'\"\n520:           - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n521:           - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n522:           - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n523:           - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n524:           - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n525:           - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n526:           - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n527:           - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n528:           - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n529: \n530:       step_run_now_check:\n531:         action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n532:         command: |\n533:           node <<'EOF'\n534:           const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n535: \n536:           const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n537:           const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n538:           const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n539:           const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n540:           const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n541:           const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n542:           const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n543: \n544:           function append(event) {\n545:             appendFileSync(\n546:               stateLogPath,\n547:               `${JSON.stringify({\n548:                 type: \"event\",\n549:                 mode: \"research\",\n550:                 run,\n551:                 timestamp,\n552:                 sessionId,\n553:                 generation,\n554:                 ...event,\n555:               })}\\n`,\n556:               \"utf8\",\n557:             );\n558:           }\n559: \n560:           if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n561:             append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n562:             if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n563:               append({\n564:                 event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n565:                 reason: \"loop_paused\",\n566:                 sentinelPath,\n567:                 pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n568:               });\n569:             } else {\n570:               const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n571:               try {\n572:                 renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n573:                 unlinkSync(claimPath);\n574:                 append({\n575:                   event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n576:                   sentinelPath,\n577:                   dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n578:                 });\n579:               } catch (error) {\n580:                 if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n581:                   throw error;\n582:                 }\n583:               }\n584:             }\n585:           }\n586:           EOF\n587:         outputs:\n588:           - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n589:           - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n590:           - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n591: \n592:       step_check_pause_sentinel:\n593:         action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n594:         check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n595:         if_exists:\n596:           log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n597:           message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n598:           halt: true\n599:         if_not_exists:\n600:           proceed: true\n601: \n602:       step_validate_convergence_config:\n603:         action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n604:         if_min_iterations_missing:\n605:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n606:           log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n607:         if_min_iterations_clamped:\n608:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n609:           log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n610:         if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n611:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n612:           log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n613: \n614:       step_graph_convergence:\n615:         action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n616:         bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n617:         note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n618:         outputs:\n619:           - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n620:           - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n621:           - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n622:           - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n623:           - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n624:           - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n625:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n626: \n627:       step_check_convergence:\n628:         action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n629:         algorithm: |\n630:           1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n631:           2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n632:           3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n633:           4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n634:           5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n635:                step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n636:                The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n637:                signals = []\n638:                Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n639:                a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n640:                   avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n641:                   stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n642:                b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n643:                   noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n644:                   stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n645:                c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n646:                   coverage = answered / total questions\n647:                   stop if coverage >= 0.85\n648:                Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n649:                if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n650:                Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n651:                if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n652:                  decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n653:                  reason = \"blockedStop\"\n654:                  stop_blocked = true\n655:                  blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n656:                  blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n657:                  gate_convergence_pass = false\n658:                  gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n659:                  gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n660:                  gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n661:                  gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n662:                  gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n663:                  recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n664:                else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n665:                  decision = \"STOP\"\n666:                  reason = \"composite_converged\"\n667:                  stop_blocked = false\n668:           6. else: CONTINUE\n669:           7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n670:                decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n671:                reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n672:                min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n673:                min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n674:           8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n675:                min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n676:           9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n677:                guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n678:                if not guardResult.passed:\n679:                  log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n680:                  decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n681:           See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n682:           Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n683:         outputs:\n684:           - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n685:           - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n686:           - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n687:           - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n688:           - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n689:           - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n690:           - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n691:           - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n692:           - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n693:           - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n694:           - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n695:           - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n696:           - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n697:           - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n698: \n699:       step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n700:         action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n701:         if_pass:\n702:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n703:           log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n704: \n705:       step_emit_blocked_stop:\n706:         action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n707:         if_blocked:\n708:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n709:           log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n710:           set:\n711:             decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n712:             reason: \"blockedStop\"\n713:             stop_blocked: false\n714: \n715:       step_handle_convergence:\n716:         action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n717:         if_stop:\n718:           log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n719:           skip_to: phase_synthesis\n720:         if_stuck_recovery:\n721:           append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n722:           log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n723:           set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n724:           reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n725:         if_continue:\n726:           log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n727: \n728:       step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n729:         action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n730:         read:\n731:           - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n732:           - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n733:           - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n734:         candidate_sources:\n735:           next_focus:\n736:             category: \"next-focus\"\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-736. Use offset=737 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# DEEP RESEARCH: AUTONOMOUS DEEP RESEARCH LOOP (AUTO MODE)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# YAML PREDICATE GRAMMAR CONTRACT (S7 / M11):\n# - This asset does not currently use typed BooleanExpr predicates under\n#   `when:`; flow control is branch-label-driven (`on_resume`, `on_fresh`,\n#   `on_restart`, etc.). Retain the existing shape.\n# - `after:` carries prose timing / narrative notes if needed; `when:` in\n#   this file is reserved for future typed predicates and must NOT carry\n#   free-form narrative prose.\n# - See `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/predicates/boolean-expr.ts`\n#   for the canonical BooleanExpr grammar.\n#\n# GATE 3 CLASSIFICATION (T-YML-DPR-01 / paired with T-DOC-03 R50-001):\n# - `resume` is a tested WRITE-PATH that produces `iteration-NNN.md` files\n#   and JSONL state-log appends. The workflow classifies resume as\n#   write-path below (see `gate3_classification` fields) so Gate 3 trigger\n#   extraction can surface resume correctly rather than false-negative.\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrole: Deep Research Loop Manager\npurpose: Iterative deep research with convergence detection\naction: Run deep-research loop from initialization through synthesis\noperating_mode:\n  workflow: iterative_loop\n  workflow_compliance: MANDATORY\n  workflow_execution: autonomous\n  approvals: none\n  tracking: progressive_research_state\n  validation: convergence_detection\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# OPERATING PRINCIPLES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\noperating_principles:\n  core: \"Fresh context per iteration + externalized state = no context degradation\"\n  approach: \"Dispatch focused agent, evaluate convergence, repeat or stop\"\n  mandate: \"Never hold findings in memory; write everything to files\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# USER INPUTS (from setup phase)\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nuser_inputs:\n  research_topic: \"[RESEARCH_TOPIC] - Topic to investigate deeply. REQUIRED.\"\n  spec_folder: \"[SPEC_FOLDER] - Spec folder path. REQUIRED.\"\n  max_iterations: \"[MAX_ITERATIONS] - Maximum loop iterations. Default: 10.\"\n  convergence_threshold: \"[CONVERGENCE_THRESHOLD] - Stop threshold. Default: 0.05.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# CONTEXT LOADING\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\ncontext_loading:\n  trigger: \"At workflow START, before phase_init\"\n  purpose: \"Load prior research context for the topic and buffer it until strategy.md exists\"\n  mcp_integration:\n    tool: memory_context\n    note: \"Call MCP tools directly - NEVER through Code Mode\"\n    parameters: { input: \"{research_topic}\", mode: \"focused\", intent: \"understand\", includeContent: true }\n  when_to_skip: [\"User says 'skip context' or 'fresh start'\"]\n  behavior:\n    if_context_found: \"Store full results as prior_context plus a concise prior_context_summary; inject after strategy.md is created.\"\n    if_no_context: \"Set prior_context and prior_context_summary to 'None' and continue.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# SKILL REFERENCE\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nskill_reference:\n  skill: deep-loop-workflows\n  skill_md: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\n  references:\n    loop_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\n    spec_check_protocol: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\n    state_format: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\n    convergence: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\n  templates:\n    config: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n    strategy: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# AGENT CONFIGURATION\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nagent_config:\n  agent: deep-research\n  agent_file: \".opencode/agents/deep-research.md\"\n  # Canonical path. Runtime-specific directories (e.g. .claude/agents/) reference this source.\n  model: opus\n  leaf_only: true\n  tools: [Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, WebFetch]\n  mcp_servers: [mk-spec-memory]\n  tool_call_budget: { target: 8, max: 12 }\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# STATE FILE PATHS\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nstate_paths:\n  # Template paths document the canonical packet layout. Runtime resolution happens via\n  # step_resolve_artifact_root plus the shared resolver, so root specs keep root-local\n  # research/ and child phases keep local research/ packet directories.\n  packet_dir: \"{artifact_dir}\"\n  config: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-config.json\"\n  state_log: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-state.jsonl\"\n  status_ledger: \"{artifact_dir}/orchestration-status.log\"\n  strategy: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-strategy.md\"\n  registry: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-findings-registry.json\"\n  dashboard: \"{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md\"\n  pause_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-pause\"\n  run_now_sentinel: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research-run-now\"\n  lock_file: \"{artifact_dir}/.deep-research.lock\"\n  prompt_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/prompts\"\n  iteration_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations\"\n  iteration_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/iterations/iteration-{NNN}.md\"\n  # Per-iteration structured delta stream (one file per iteration) — complement to the\n  # canonical state_log append. The delta file MUST contain at least one record whose\n  # `type === \"iteration\"` so the reducer can rehydrate iteration state after a partial\n  # run. Variants like `\"iteration_delta\"` are silently dropped by the reducer; the\n  # post_dispatch_validate step enforces the canonical type below.\n  delta_dir: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas\"\n  delta_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/deltas/iter-{NNN}.jsonl\"\n  research_output: \"{artifact_dir}/research.md\"\n  resource_map_output: \"{artifact_dir}/resource-map.md\"\n  archive_root: \"{artifact_archive_root}\"\n  synthesis_snapshot_pattern: \"{artifact_dir}/synthesis-v{generation}.md\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# WORKFLOW\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nworkflow:\n\n  step_resolve_artifact_root:\n    description: \"Resolve artifact directory — use fan-out lineage override when provided, else resolve from spec_folder\"\n    note: \"Root specs keep research artifacts directly in {spec_folder}/research/. Child phases and sub-phases keep local packet directories in {spec_folder}/research/{packet}/, and archives stay local at {spec_folder}/research_archive/{packet}/.\"\n    branch_on: \"config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir\"\n    if_present:\n      bind:\n        artifact_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_root_dir: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}\"\n        artifact_subfolder: null\n        artifact_archive_root: \"{config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir}/_archive\"\n    if_absent:\n      command: \"node -e \\\"const { resolveArtifactRoot } = require('.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs'); console.log(JSON.stringify(resolveArtifactRoot('{spec_folder}', 'research')));\\\"\"\n      outputs:\n        - artifact_root_dir: \"Resolved local research owner directory\"\n        - artifact_subfolder: \"Local packet subfolder ({ownerSlug}-pt-{NN}), else null\"\n        - artifact_dir: \"Resolved research packet directory for this target\"\n        - artifact_archive_root: \"Resolved local research archive directory for this target\"\n\n  step_fanout_spawn:\n    description: \"Spawn fan-out lineages; skip and proceed to phase_init normally when single-executor\"\n    skip_when: \"config.fanout is absent\"\n    instructions: |\n      Fan-out mode is active. Spawn all lineages. Each lineage runs the full loop in its own\n      isolated sub-packet under {artifact_dir}/lineages/{label}/.\n      After all lineages complete, jump directly to phase_synthesis — skip phase_init and\n      phase_main_loop entirely (those are the single-executor path). The merge step in\n      phase_synthesis will consolidate results across all lineages.\n    sub_steps:\n      step_fanout_spawn_cli:\n        description: \"Spawn all CLI lineages in capped worker pool\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind != 'native'\"\n        command: |\n          node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs \\\n            --spec-folder {spec_folder} \\\n            --loop-type research \\\n            --research-topic \"{research_topic}\" \\\n            --fanout-config-json '{config.fanout_json}' \\\n            --base-artifact-dir {artifact_dir}\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        wait_for_completion: true\n      step_fanout_spawn_native:\n        description: \"Dispatch each native lineage as a sequential deep-research sub-agent\"\n        skip_when: \"no entries in config.fanout.executors with kind == 'native'\"\n        for_each: \"lineage in expanded native entries of config.fanout\"\n        dispatch:\n          agent: deep-research\n          model: opus\n          context: |\n            Execute the deep-research loop with these parameters:\n              spec_folder: {spec_folder}\n              config.fanout_lineage_artifact_dir: {artifact_dir}/lineages/{lineage.label}\n              session_id: fanout-{lineage.label}-{fanout_run_id}\n              executor: native\n            Run to convergence. Write all outputs to the override directory.\n        wait_for_completion: true\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 1: INITIALIZATION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_init:\n    purpose: Create all state files for the research session\n    steps:\n\n      step_preflight_contract:\n        action: \"Validate required setup bindings and executable workflow contract before any file writes\"\n        verify:\n          - required_values_present: [research_topic, spec_folder, max_iterations, convergence_threshold]\n          - spec_folder_is_within: \"specs/ or .opencode/specs/ (canonicalize alias roots before validation)\"\n          - unresolved_placeholders: \"FAIL if any user-facing template references placeholders not produced by earlier steps\"\n          - tool_contract: \"FAIL if executable steps reference tools outside the command allowlist\"\n        on_fail: \"Halt with STATUS=FAIL and report the missing binding or unsupported contract reference\"\n\n      step_create_directories:\n        action: \"Create spec folder and research packet directories if they don't exist\"\n        command: \"mkdir -p {state_paths.prompt_dir} {state_paths.iteration_dir} {state_paths.delta_dir}\"\n\n      step_detect_resource_map:\n        action: \"Detect resource-map.md before config creation so init can persist the flag and seed Known Context\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/resource-map.md\"\n        classify:\n          present: \"resource-map.md exists at init\"\n          absent: \"resource-map.md does not exist at init\"\n        outputs:\n          - resource_map_present: \"Boolean true when {spec_folder}/resource-map.md exists, else false\"\n          - resource_map_known_context: \"When present: summarize the map by section with entry counts across READMEs, Documents, Commands, Agents, Skills, Specs, Scripts, Tests, Config, and Meta, plus a one-line theme summary for each section. When absent: 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_resolve_canonical_names:\n        action: \"Resolve canonical research packet artifact names before classification\"\n        inspect_legacy:\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/config.json\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/state.jsonl\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/strategy.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/dashboard.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.packet_dir}/.pause\"\n        migration_policy: \"dual-read / single-write for 4 weeks\"\n        on_legacy_read:\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"migration\",\"legacyPath\":\"{legacy_path}\",\"canonicalPath\":\"{canonical_path}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_acquire_lock:\n        action: \"Acquire the single-writer advisory lock before session classification\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs acquire --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --packet-id {spec_folder}\"\n        on_acquire: \"Capture ownerPid from the JSON output and reuse it for every release below. If acquired=false, fail closed — another deep-research run already holds this packet.\"\n        note: \"Uses the promoted deep-loop-runtime loop-lock CLI (single source of truth: stale-lock reclaim, clean owner-scoped release). macOS/BSD locking is advisory — best-effort single-writer, not a hard mutex across host calls; stale-lock override is confirm-only or explicit recovery-only.\"\n        # Lock-cleanup contract: the lock file MUST be released on every terminal exit path that follows acquisition.\n        # Runtimes honoring step_acquire_lock are required to perform this cleanup before halting or pausing.\n        on_halt:\n          action: \"Release the lock before any terminal halt branch returns control\"\n          applies_to: [\"step_classify_session.on_invalid_state\", \"step_classify_session.on_completed_session\", \"step_preinit_spec_branch.conflict-detected\"]\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; failures here are logged but do not block the halt\"\n        on_cancel:\n          action: \"Release the lock on user cancel or pause-sentinel detection before sentinel processing\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; cancel completes regardless of cleanup result\"\n        on_workflow_exit:\n          action: \"Release the lock as the final step of any workflow exit path (success or failure)\"\n          command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}; idempotent — safe to invoke when already released\"\n\n      step_classify_session:\n        action: \"Classify the session before writing files\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        classify:\n          fresh: \"None of the three state artifacts exist\"\n          resume: \"Config, JSONL, and strategy all exist and agree on topic/spec folder; missing wait-checkpoint fields are read as nextRunAt:null and remainingDelayMs:null\"\n          completed-session: \"Resume artifacts exist and config.status == 'complete'\"\n          invalid-state: \"Any partial, missing, or contradictory combination\"\n        outputs:\n          - session_state: \"fresh | resume | completed-session | invalid-state\"\n        on_resume:\n          # T-YML-DPR-01 / R50-001: Resume is a WRITE-PATH. Produces `iteration-NNN.md` + JSONL appends.\n          # Paired with T-DOC-03 Gate 3 trigger addition (resume, save context, save memory, /memory:save).\n          gate3_classification: write-path\n          gate3_rationale: \"resume produces iteration-NNN.md writes and JSONL state-log appends\"\n          log: \"Auto-resume: state artifacts are complete and consistent. Continue the same lineage (sessionId unchanged, generation unchanged, no archive).\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"resumed\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"resume\",\"continuedFromRun\":{iteration_count},\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":null,\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: phase_loop\n        on_restart:\n          action: \"Archive the current research packet under the root-level research_archive/ tree and start a new lineage segment with a fresh sessionId and generation+1.\"\n          command: \"if [ -d {state_paths.packet_dir} ]; then mkdir -p {state_paths.archive_root} && mv {state_paths.packet_dir} {state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}; fi\"\n          set:\n            lineage_mode: \"restart\"\n            parent_session_id: \"{prior_session_id}\"\n            generation: \"{prior_generation + 1}\"\n          append_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"restarted\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"sessionId\":\"{session_id}\",\"parentSessionId\":\"{prior_session_id}\",\"lineageMode\":\"restart\",\"generation\":{generation},\"archivedPath\":\"{state_paths.archive_root}/{timestamp_slug}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          skip_to: step_create_config\n        note_deferred_branches: \"fork and completed-continue are deferred and no longer runtime-supported in this release. The reducer still reads `lineageMode` from config for dashboards and analysis, but only `new`, `resume`, and `restart` are live. See deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md §Lifecycle Branch Contract for the one-session contract.\"\n        on_completed_session:\n          log: \"Prior session already completed. Do not route directly to synthesis; archive the completed research/ tree or start a fresh packet instead.\"\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Completed deep-research packet detected. Archive or replace the existing research/ tree before starting a new session.\"\n        on_invalid_state:\n          halt: true\n          message: \"Existing deep-research state is incomplete or contradictory. Repair or archive the invalid research packet before continuing.\"\n        on_fresh:\n          action: \"Proceed with a new session\"\n\n      step_resolve_session_id:\n        action: \"Resolve init session id from caller when supplied, else preserve the auto-generated fallback\"\n        branch_on: \"session_id\"\n        if_present:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{session_id}\"\n        if_absent:\n          bind:\n            session_id_init: \"{AUTO_SESSION_ID}\"\n\n      step_create_config:\n        action: \"Create deep-research-config.json from template\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          maxIterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          minIterations: 3\n          # Semantic: newInfoRatio with negative-knowledge emphasis. See SKILL.md §\"Convergence Threshold Semantics\".\n          convergenceThreshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n          convergenceMode: \"default\"\n          stuckThreshold: 3\n          minIdeaObservations: 2\n          maxDurationMinutes: 120\n          specFolder: \"{spec_folder}\"\n          resource_map_present: \"{resource_map_present}\"\n          # Honor the parsed --no-resource-map flag from deep-research.md:73 (default true; false when flag is set).\n          # The markdown command parses $ARGUMENTS and binds {resource_map_emit} before this step runs.\n          resource_map.emit: \"{resource_map_emit}\"\n          createdAt: \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"\n          status: \"initialized\"\n          executionMode: \"auto\"\n          lineage.sessionId: \"{session_id_init}\"\n          lineage.parentSessionId: null\n          lineage.lineageMode: \"new\"\n          lineage.generation: 1\n          lineage.continuedFromRun: null\n          nextRunAt: null\n          remainingDelayMs: null\n        output: \"{state_paths.config}\"\n\n      step_create_state_log:\n        action: \"Initialize JSONL state log with config record\"\n        # Same parsed --no-resource-map flag honored here so config and state_log agree from line 1.\n        content: '{\"type\":\"config\",\"topic\":\"{research_topic}\",\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"minIterations\":3,\"convergenceThreshold\":{convergence_threshold},\"convergenceMode\":\"default\",\"minIdeaObservations\":2,\"resource_map_present\":{resource_map_present},\"resource_map\":{\"emit\":{resource_map_emit}},\"createdAt\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"specFolder\":\"{spec_folder}\",\"nextRunAt\":null,\"remainingDelayMs\":null}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n\n      step_create_strategy:\n        action: \"Create strategy file from template with initial questions\"\n        template: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\n        populate:\n          topic: \"{research_topic}\"\n          key_questions: \"Derive 3-5 key questions from the research topic\"\n          known_context: \"None\"\n          known_context_summary: \"None\"\n          max_iterations: \"{max_iterations}\"\n          convergence_threshold: \"{convergence_threshold}\"\n        output: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_create_registry:\n        action: \"Initialize reducer-owned findings registry\"\n        content: '{\"openQuestions\":[],\"resolvedQuestions\":[],\"keyFindings\":[],\"ruledOutDirections\":[],\"metrics\":{\"iterationsCompleted\":0,\"openQuestions\":0,\"resolvedQuestions\":0,\"keyFindings\":0,\"convergenceScore\":0,\"coverageBySources\":{}}}'\n        output: \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_context:\n        action: \"Ensure Known Context is written only after strategy.md exists\"\n        condition: \"prior_context_found\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"Append or replace the Known Context section with prior_context_summary and retained detail from prior_context\"\n\n      step_enrich_strategy_resource_map:\n        action: \"Inject resource-map status into Known Context after strategy.md exists\"\n        edit: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        note: \"When resource_map_present is true, append the resource_map_known_context snapshot. When false, append 'resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate'.\"\n\n      step_detect_spec_present:\n        action: \"Classify late-INIT spec.md state after the durable research packet exists\"\n        inspect:\n          - \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n          - \"{state_paths.lock_file}\"\n        classify:\n          no-spec: \"spec.md is absent before any pre-init mutation\"\n          spec-present: \"spec.md exists and approved host anchors are available for bounded mutation\"\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run: \"spec.md already carries this run's DR seed markers and should not be reseeded\"\n          conflict-detected: \"missing host anchor, duplicate markers, or generated-block ambiguity makes mutation unsafe\"\n        outputs:\n          - folder_state: \"no-spec | spec-present | spec-just-created-by-this-run | conflict-detected\"\n          - normalized_topic: \"Trim, lowercase, and collapse whitespace in research_topic before dedupe checks\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"spec_check_result\",\"folder_state\":\"{folder_state}\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"lockPath\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n      step_preinit_spec_branch:\n        action: \"Run the bounded pre-init spec branch required by spec_check_protocol\"\n        protocol_reference: \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\"\n        branches:\n          no-spec:\n            create: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            seed_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            requirements_host: \"Seed Requirements from the research ask without broadening scope\"\n            scope_host: \"Seed Scope from the research ask without inventing implementation details\"\n            set:\n              folder_state: \"spec-just-created-by-this-run\"\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_seed_created\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-just-created-by-this-run\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Requirements\",\"Scope\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Seeded Level 1 spec.md from research topic with DR seed markers.\",\"seed_markers\":[\"DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS\",\"DR-SEED:SCOPE\"],\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-present:\n            edit: \"{spec_folder}/spec.md\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: true\n            idempotency_check:\n              host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n              normalized_match: \"Normalize the existing anchor text by lowercasing, stripping punctuation, collapsing whitespace, and trimming before comparing with {normalized_topic}.\"\n              if_match:\n                skip_append: true\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_deduped\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Skipped duplicate pre-init topic append because normalized topic already exists in Open Questions.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n              if_no_match:\n                append_only:\n                  - host_anchor: \"Open Questions\"\n                    content: \"Add the normalized research topic only if it is not already present.\"\n                  - host_anchor: \"Research Context\"\n                    content: \"Add a bounded note that deep-research is active for this topic and that research/research.md remains canonical.\"\n                append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_preinit_context_added\",\"folder_state\":\"spec-present\",\"anchors_touched\":[\"Open Questions\",\"Research Context\"],\"diff_summary\":\"Appended bounded pre-init research context for the normalized topic.\",\"normalized_topic\":\"{normalized_topic}\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n          spec-just-created-by-this-run:\n            verify_markers:\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:REQUIREMENTS -->\"\n              - \"<!-- DR-SEED:SCOPE -->\"\n            set:\n              validate_spec_doc: false\n            note: \"Treat already-seeded spec.md as a no-op guard and continue.\"\n          conflict-detected:\n            append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"spec_mutation\",\"event\":\"spec_mutation_conflict\",\"folder_state\":\"conflict-detected\",\"reason\":\"Pre-init spec.md mutation is ambiguous or unsafe.\",\"specPath\":\"{spec_folder}/spec.md\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n            halt: true\n\n      step_validate_preinit_spec_doc:\n        action: \"Run targeted strict validation after any deep-research pre-init spec.md mutation\"\n        condition: \"validate_spec_doc\"\n        command: \"SPECKIT_RULES=FRONTMATTER_VALID,LEVEL_DECLARED,TEMPLATE_SOURCE,TEMPLATE_HEADERS,PLACEHOLDER_FILLED,SECTIONS_PRESENT,ANCHORS_VALID,SPEC_DOC_INTEGRITY,TOC_POLICY bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/validate.sh {spec_folder} --strict\"\n        note: \"This enforces the authored-spec markdown structural contract without applying full-packet required-file or completeness checks to workflow-owned research artifacts. It uses the Node validation orchestrator, whose strict path was measured at about 108ms for a fresh Level 3 packet on the local harness.\"\n\n      step_telemetry_heartbeat_started:\n        action: \"Emit a single-loop started row in the orchestration status ledger\"\n        skip_when: \"config.fanout is present\"\n        canonical_lifecycle_event: \"iteration_start\"\n        command: |\n          node --experimental-strip-types --input-type=module <<'EOF'\n          import { readFileSync } from 'node:fs';\n\n          import { appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic } from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/atomic-state.ts';\n          import observabilityEvents from './.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/observability-events.cjs';\n\n          const { appendObservabilityEvent } = observabilityEvents;\n          const config = JSON.parse(readFileSync('{state_paths.config}', 'utf8'));\n          const timestamp = '{ISO_8601_NOW}';\n          const sessionId = String(config.lineage?.sessionId ?? '{AUTO_SESSION_ID}');\n          const generation = Number(config.lineage?.generation ?? 1);\n          const observabilityPath = '{state_paths.packet_dir}/observability-events.jsonl';\n          const row = {\n            event: 'started',\n            label: 'single',\n            at: timestamp,\n            duration_ms: 0,\n            loop_type: 'research',\n            sessionId,\n            generation,\n            gauges: { iterations: 0, elapsed_ms: 0, score: 0 },\n          };\n\n          const appended = appendJsonlIfChangedAtomic('{state_paths.status_ledger}', row, {\n            diffData: { event: row.event, label: row.label, sessionId, generation, gauges: { iterations: 0, score: 0 } },\n            diffField: 'state_hash',\n          });\n          if (appended) {\n            try {\n              appendObservabilityEvent(observabilityPath, row, {\n                producer: 'deep-research-auto',\n                stream: 'single-loop-telemetry',\n                subject: { label: row.label, sessionId, generation },\n                event: row.event,\n                status: 'running',\n              });\n            } catch {}\n          }\n          EOF\n        working_directory: \"{repo_root}\"\n        outputs:\n          - status_ledger_started: \"A fan-out-shaped status row with label single and event started\"\n\n      step_init_complete:\n        log: \"Initialization complete. Config, state, and strategy files created.\"\n        set: { current_iteration: 1, current_segment: 1, stuck_count: 0 }\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 2: ITERATION LOOP\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_loop:\n    purpose: Dispatch agent iterations until convergence\n    repeat: true\n    max_repeats: \"{max_iterations}\"\n    steps:\n\n      step_read_state:\n        action: \"Read current state from JSONL and strategy\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n        extract:\n          - iteration_count: \"Count lines where type === 'iteration'\"\n          - current_iteration: \"iteration_count + 1\"\n          - current_segment: \"Latest segment_start event segment, else 1\"\n          - last_newInfoRatio: \"Extract newInfoRatio from last iteration record\"\n          - last_focus: \"Extract focus from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - ratio_prev: \"Extract newInfoRatio from second-latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - ratio_latest: \"Extract newInfoRatio from latest iteration record, else 'N/A'\"\n          - next_focus: \"Extract 'Next Focus' section from strategy.md\"\n          - remaining_questions: \"Count unchecked items in 'Key Questions'\"\n          - remaining_questions_list: \"List unchecked key questions from strategy.md\"\n          - carried_forward_open_questions: \"Extract 'Carried-Forward Open Questions' section from strategy.md, else '[None yet]'\"\n          - answered_count: \"Count answered questions from strategy.md\"\n          - total_questions: \"Count total questions tracked in strategy.md\"\n          - resource_map_present: \"Extract boolean from deep-research-config.json, default false\"\n          - resource_map_prompt_line: \"If resource_map_present is true, return 'Resource map: prior-inventoried files are listed in {spec_folder}/resource-map.md; treat them as the exclusion set when hunting for net-new files; flag only missed-from-map candidates as gaps.' Else return 'Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.'\"\n          - memory_context_prompt_line: \"If a refreshed memory context summary exists from the previous iteration, return 'Memory context refresh: {summary}'. Else use prior_context_summary from startup when available; otherwise return 'Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.'\"\n          - least_explored: \"First unanswered question not covered by the most recent iteration focus, else first unanswered question\"\n          - last_3_summaries: \"Summarize the latest 3 iteration records as 'run N: focus (ratio)'\"\n          - latest_status: \"Extract status from latest iteration record, else 'none yet'\"\n          - nextRunAt: \"Extract nullable nextRunAt from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - remainingDelayMs: \"Extract nullable remainingDelayMs from deep-research-config.json, default null\"\n          - min_iterations_present: \"Boolean true when deep-research-config.json has a numeric minIterations field\"\n          - min_iterations_missing_warning: \"Boolean true when minIterations is missing; use no floor and log a warning so older configs keep prior stop behavior\"\n          - min_iterations_raw: \"Extract numeric minIterations from deep-research-config.json when present, default 0\"\n          - effective_min_iterations: \"Clamp min_iterations_raw to the inclusive range 0..max_iterations; if min_iterations_raw exceeds max_iterations, use max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_clamped: \"Boolean true when min_iterations_raw > max_iterations\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_already_passed: \"Boolean true when state_log already contains event == 'min_iterations_guard_pass'\"\n          - convergence_mode: \"Extract convergenceMode when it is 'default' or 'off'; default to 'default'\"\n          - convergence_mode_warning: \"Boolean true when convergenceMode is present with an unsupported value; use 'default'\"\n          - rejected_patterns_count: \"Read registry.rejectedPatterns length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - rejected_candidate_matches: \"Read registry.suppressedCandidates when registry exists, else []\"\n          - rejected_pattern_fuzzy_threshold: \"Read config.rejectedPatternFuzzyThreshold when present, else 0.85\"\n          - min_idea_observations: \"Read config.minIdeaObservations when present, default 2; clamp to 1..10\"\n          - observed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.observedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_count: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n          - promoted_ideas_list: \"Read registry.promotedIdeas idea text in rank order when registry exists, else []\"\n          - suppressed_ideas_count: \"Read registry.suppressedIdeas length when registry exists, else 0\"\n\n      step_run_now_check:\n        action: \"Detect and consume a one-shot run-now sentinel before pause/convergence/dispatch\"\n        command: |\n          node <<'EOF'\n          const { appendFileSync, existsSync, renameSync, unlinkSync } = require('node:fs');\n\n          const stateLogPath = \"{state_paths.state_log}\";\n          const sentinelPath = \"{state_paths.run_now_sentinel}\";\n          const pausePath = \"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\";\n          const timestamp = \"{ISO_8601_NOW}\";\n          const sessionId = \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\";\n          const generation = Number(\"{config.lineage.generation}\");\n          const run = Number(\"{current_iteration}\");\n\n          function append(event) {\n            appendFileSync(\n              stateLogPath,\n              `${JSON.stringify({\n                type: \"event\",\n                mode: \"research\",\n                run,\n                timestamp,\n                sessionId,\n                generation,\n                ...event,\n              })}\\n`,\n              \"utf8\",\n            );\n          }\n\n          if (existsSync(sentinelPath)) {\n            append({ event: \"run_now_requested\", sentinelPath });\n            if (existsSync(pausePath)) {\n              append({\n                event: \"run_now_rejected\",\n                reason: \"loop_paused\",\n                sentinelPath,\n                pauseSentinelPath: pausePath,\n              });\n            } else {\n              const claimPath = `${sentinelPath}.consuming.${process.pid}.${Date.now()}`;\n              try {\n                renameSync(sentinelPath, claimPath);\n                unlinkSync(claimPath);\n                append({\n                  event: \"run_now_accepted\",\n                  sentinelPath,\n                  dispatchEvent: \"iteration_start\",\n                });\n              } catch (error) {\n                if (!error || error.code !== \"ENOENT\") {\n                  throw error;\n                }\n              }\n            }\n          }\n          EOF\n        outputs:\n          - run_now_requested: \"Emitted when {state_paths.run_now_sentinel} exists at the loop boundary\"\n          - run_now_accepted: \"Emitted after the sentinel is atomically renamed and deleted before dispatch\"\n          - run_now_rejected: \"Emitted with reason loop_paused when pause takes precedence; sentinel remains present\"\n\n      step_check_pause_sentinel:\n        action: \"Check for pause sentinel file\"\n        check: \"Does {state_paths.pause_sentinel} exist?\"\n        if_exists:\n          log_event: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"userPaused\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"userPaused\",\"sentinelPath\":\"{state_paths.pause_sentinel}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          message: \"Research paused. Delete research/.deep-research-pause to resume.\"\n          halt: true\n        if_not_exists:\n          proceed: true\n\n      step_validate_convergence_config:\n        action: \"Validate convergence floor settings when loading config\"\n        if_min_iterations_missing:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"fallback\":0,\"message\":\"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations missing; using no convergence floor for backward compatibility.\"\n        if_min_iterations_clamped:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"minIterations\",\"configured\":{min_iterations_raw},\"effective\":{effective_min_iterations},\"maxIterations\":{max_iterations},\"message\":\"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"minIterations exceeds maxIterations; clamping to the hard cap.\"\n        if_convergence_mode_invalid:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"config_warning\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"field\":\"convergenceMode\",\"fallback\":\"default\",\"message\":\"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Unsupported convergenceMode; using default convergence behavior.\"\n\n      step_graph_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate coverage-graph convergence before the inline 3-signal vote and persist the graph decision snapshot\"\n        bash: 'node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/convergence.cjs --spec-folder \"{spec_folder}\" --loop-type \"research\" --session-id \"{config.lineage.sessionId}\"'\n        note: \"Run before the inline vote. STOP from the inline 3-signal vote is allowed only when the graph decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\"\n        outputs:\n          - graph_decision: \"Tool decision value (CONTINUE | STOP_ALLOWED | STOP_BLOCKED), else null when unavailable\"\n          - graph_decision_json: \"JSON-encoded graph decision string, else null\"\n          - graph_signals_json: \"Tool signals object, else {}\"\n          - graph_blockers_json: \"Tool blockers array, else []\"\n          - graph_trace_json: \"Tool trace payload, else []\"\n          - graph_convergence_score: \"signals.blendedScore when present, else the best available graph score, else 0\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"graph_convergence\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"decision\":{graph_decision_json},\"signals\":{graph_signals_json},\"blockers\":{graph_blockers_json},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n\n      step_check_convergence:\n        action: \"Evaluate stop conditions and combine the inline 3-signal vote with graph convergence\"\n        algorithm: |\n          1. if iteration_count >= max_iterations: STOP (maxIterationsReached). This terminal cap bypasses quality-guard overrides; record failed guards/blockers as synthesis evidence instead of continuing.\n          2. if stuck_count >= config.stuckThreshold: STUCK_RECOVERY\n          3. if convergence_mode == \"off\": skip convergence stop candidates and continue unless a terminal cap, pause sentinel, or recovery halt has already fired.\n          4. if remaining_questions == 0: STOP (all_questions_answered)\n          5. GRAPH-ASSISTED COMPOSITE CONVERGENCE:\n               step_graph_convergence already recorded graph_decision, graph_signals_json, graph_blockers_json, and graph_convergence_score for this run.\n               The existing inline 3-signal vote still computes the inline STOP candidate and is not replaced.\n               signals = []\n               Filter: exclude iterations where status == thought from signal inputs (use only evidence iterations)\n               a) Rolling average (w=0.30, needs 3+ iterations):\n                  avg = mean(last 3 newInfoRatios)\n                  stop if avg < convergence_threshold\n               b) MAD noise floor (w=0.35, needs 4+ iterations):\n                  noiseFloor = MAD(all ratios) * 1.4826\n                  stop if latest ratio <= noiseFloor\n               c) Question entropy (w=0.35):\n                  coverage = answered / total questions\n                  stop if coverage >= 0.85\n               Redistribute weights for unavailable signals.\n               if weighted_stop_score > 0.60: inline_stop_candidate = true\n               Combined stop rule: STOP only if the inline 3-signal vote says STOP AND graph_decision is STOP_ALLOWED or absent.\n               if inline_stop_candidate and graph_decision == \"STOP_BLOCKED\":\n                 decision = \"BLOCKED\"\n                 reason = \"blockedStop\"\n                 stop_blocked = true\n                 blocked_by_json = JSON array derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 blocked_by_csv = comma-separated blocker names derived from graph_blockers_json\n                 gate_convergence_pass = false\n                 gate_convergence_score = graph_convergence_score\n                 gate_key_question_coverage_pass = no blocker named questionCoverage\n                 gate_evidence_density_pass = no blocker named sourceDiversity or evidenceDepth\n                 gate_evidence_density_sources = graph_signals_json.sourceDiversity or 0\n                 gate_hotspot_saturation_pass = true\n                 recovery_strategy = first blocker reason/message, else \"Collect deeper graph evidence before stopping.\"\n               else if inline_stop_candidate and (graph_decision == \"STOP_ALLOWED\" or graph_decision is absent):\n                 decision = \"STOP\"\n                 reason = \"composite_converged\"\n                 stop_blocked = false\n          6. else: CONTINUE\n          7. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\" and effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count < effective_min_iterations:\n               decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n               reason = \"minIterationsNotReached\"\n               min_iterations_guard_blocked = true\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = false\n          8. if effective_min_iterations > 1 and iteration_count >= effective_min_iterations and min_iterations_guard_already_passed == false:\n               min_iterations_guard_pass = true\n          9. if decision == \"STOP\" and reason != \"maxIterationsReached\":\n               guardResult = checkQualityGuards(state, strategy)\n               if not guardResult.passed:\n                 log: \"Quality guard failed: {guardResult.violations}. Overriding STOP to CONTINUE.\"\n                 decision = \"CONTINUE\"\n          See convergence.md for full pseudocode and signal definitions.\n          Segment-aware convergence is experimental/reference-only; live workflow uses the current session as a single segment.\n        outputs:\n          - decision: \"STOP | BLOCKED | STUCK_RECOVERY | CONTINUE\"\n          - reason: \"Human-readable stop reason\"\n          - stop_blocked: \"Boolean marker set when graph convergence vetoes an inline STOP candidate\"\n          - blocked_by_json: \"JSON array of graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - blocked_by_csv: \"Comma-separated graph blocker names when decision == BLOCKED\"\n          - gate_convergence_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail for the graph-assisted convergence gate\"\n          - gate_convergence_score: \"Numeric score recorded from graph convergence\"\n          - gate_key_question_coverage_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker coverage signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_pass: \"Boolean pass/fail derived from graph blocker evidence-depth signals\"\n          - gate_evidence_density_sources: \"Source-diversity count or equivalent evidence-depth proxy\"\n          - gate_hotspot_saturation_pass: \"Research placeholder gate; true unless an explicit blocker sets otherwise\"\n          - recovery_strategy: \"One-line hint describing the next research action when decision == BLOCKED or STUCK_RECOVERY\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_pass: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor has cleared for the first time\"\n          - min_iterations_guard_blocked: \"Boolean true when the configured convergence floor overrides a STOP candidate to CONTINUE\"\n\n      step_emit_min_iterations_guard_pass:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class event when the convergence floor clears\"\n        if_pass:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"min_iterations_guard_pass\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"iterationCount\":{iteration_count},\"minIterations\":{effective_min_iterations},\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Minimum iteration floor cleared for convergence stopping.\"\n\n      step_emit_blocked_stop:\n        action: \"Persist a first-class blocked_stop event when the legal-stop decision tree returns blocked\"\n        if_blocked:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"blocked_stop\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"blockedBy\":{blocked_by_json},\"gateResults\":{\"convergence\":{\"pass\":{gate_convergence_pass},\"score\":{gate_convergence_score}},\"keyQuestionCoverage\":{\"pass\":{gate_key_question_coverage_pass},\"answered\":{answered_count},\"total\":{total_questions}},\"evidenceDensity\":{\"pass\":{gate_evidence_density_pass},\"sources\":{gate_evidence_density_sources}},\"hotspotSaturation\":{\"pass\":{gate_hotspot_saturation_pass}}},\"recoveryStrategy\":\"{recovery_strategy}\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Graph convergence blocked STOP. Failed blockers: {blocked_by_csv}. Recovery strategy: {recovery_strategy}\"\n          set:\n            decision: \"CONTINUE\"\n            reason: \"blockedStop\"\n            stop_blocked: false\n\n      step_handle_convergence:\n        action: \"Act on convergence decision\"\n        if_stop:\n          log: \"Loop stopping. Reason: {reason}\"\n          skip_to: phase_synthesis\n        if_stuck_recovery:\n          append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"mode\":\"research\",\"run\":{current_iteration},\"stopReason\":\"stuckRecovery\",\"fromIteration\":{current_iteration},\"outcome\":\"recovered\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\",\"sessionId\":\"{config.lineage.sessionId}\",\"generation\":{config.lineage.generation}}'\n          log: \"Stuck detected ({stuck_count} consecutive no-progress). Entering recovery.\"\n          set: { next_focus: \"RECOVERY: Widen scope. Try fundamentally different approach. Least-explored question: {least_explored}\" }\n          reset: { stuck_count: 0 }\n        if_continue:\n          log: \"Iteration {current_iteration}: Continuing. Focus: {next_focus}\"\n\n      step_rejected_pattern_cache:\n        action: \"Apply reducer-derived rejected-pattern suppression before dispatch candidate selection\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.state_log}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.registry}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n        candidate_sources:\n          next_focus:\n            category: \"next-focus\"","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":736,"totalLines":737,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783486574783,"end":1783486574791}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc612187804923e016a4dd86ebc988191964d7775f98e1441"}},"id":"prt_f401570ad001VXuDf29Am7nZed","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486574819,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_HptouuBjzEop58TA8MtQCEaP","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","offset":1,"limit":2000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: description: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\n3: argument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\n4: allowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n5: ---\n6: \n7: # Deep Start Research Loop\n8: \n9: !`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`\n\n(End of file - total 9 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\n!`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/research.md","text":"---\ndescription: Autonomous deep-research loop: iterative investigation with convergence detection. Modes :auto, :confirm.\nargument-hint: \"<topic> [:auto|:confirm] [--max-iterations=N] [--convergence=N] [--lineage-timeout-hours=N] [--stop-policy=convergence|max-iterations] [--dry-run] [--executor=<type> [--model=X] [--config-dir=PATH] [--count=N] [--label=X] ...] [--executors=<json>] [--concurrency=N] (:auto supports PRE-BOUND SETUP ANSWERS: prompt-body block for non-interactive setup)\"\nallowed-tools: Read, Write, Edit, Bash, Grep, Glob, Task, WebFetch, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_context, mcp__mk_spec_memory__memory_search, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_query, mcp__mk_code_index__code_graph_context\n---\n\n# Deep Start Research Loop\n\n!`node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/render-command-contract.cjs --command deep/research -- '$ARGUMENTS'`","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":9,"totalLines":9,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/research.md","time":{"start":1783486574815,"end":1783486574818}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc612187804923e016a4dd86ebca881919fdf0ccc4d6ba5eb"}},"id":"prt_f401570cb0016DrDUFTaK20xXr","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486574835,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_32SusbCl8ptm0yHyOFGmJFt8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: {\n2:   \"topic\": \"\",\n3:   \"maxIterations\": 10,\n4:   \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n5:   \"antiConvergence\": {\n6:     \"minIterations\": 3,\n7:     \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n8:     \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n9:   },\n10:   \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n11:   \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n12:   \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n13:   \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n14:   \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n15:   \"specFolder\": \"\",\n16:   \"createdAt\": \"\",\n17:   \"status\": \"initialized\",\n18:   \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n19:   \"executor\": {\n20:     \"kind\": \"native\",\n21:     \"model\": null,\n22:     \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n23:     \"serviceTier\": null,\n24:     \"sandboxMode\": null,\n25:     \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n26:   },\n27:   \"lineage\": {\n28:     \"sessionId\": \"\",\n29:     \"parentSessionId\": null,\n30:     \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n31:     \"allowedModes\": [\n32:       \"new\",\n33:       \"resume\",\n34:       \"restart\"\n35:     ],\n36:     \"deferredModes\": [\n37:       \"fork\",\n38:       \"completed-continue\"\n39:     ],\n40:     \"generation\": 1,\n41:     \"continuedFromRun\": null\n42:   },\n43:   \"reducer\": {\n44:     \"enabled\": true,\n45:     \"version\": \"1.0\",\n46:     \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n47:     \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n48:     \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n49:     \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n50:       \"key-questions\",\n51:       \"answered-questions\",\n52:       \"what-worked\",\n53:       \"what-failed\",\n54:       \"exhausted-approaches\",\n55:       \"ruled-out-directions\",\n56:       \"next-focus\"\n57:     ]\n58:   },\n59:   \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n60:   \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n61:   \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n62:   \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n63:   \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n64:   \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n65:   \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n66:   \"fileProtection\": {\n67:     \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n68:     \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n69:     \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n70:     \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n71:     \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n72:     \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n73:     \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n74:   },\n75:   \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n76:     \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n77:     \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n78:     \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n79:     \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n80:     \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n81:   }\n82: }\n\n(End of file - total 82 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","text":"{\n  \"topic\": \"\",\n  \"maxIterations\": 10,\n  \"convergenceThreshold\": 0.05,\n  \"antiConvergence\": {\n    \"minIterations\": 3,\n    \"convergenceMode\": \"default\",\n    \"stopPolicy\": \"fail-closed\"\n  },\n  \"stuckThreshold\": 3,\n  \"maxDurationMinutes\": 120,\n  \"maxToolCallsPerIteration\": 12,\n  \"maxMinutesPerIteration\": 10,\n  \"progressiveSynthesis\": true,\n  \"specFolder\": \"\",\n  \"createdAt\": \"\",\n  \"status\": \"initialized\",\n  \"executionMode\": \"auto\",\n  \"executor\": {\n    \"kind\": \"native\",\n    \"model\": null,\n    \"reasoningEffort\": null,\n    \"serviceTier\": null,\n    \"sandboxMode\": null,\n    \"timeoutSeconds\": 900\n  },\n  \"lineage\": {\n    \"sessionId\": \"\",\n    \"parentSessionId\": null,\n    \"lineageMode\": \"new\",\n    \"allowedModes\": [\n      \"new\",\n      \"resume\",\n      \"restart\"\n    ],\n    \"deferredModes\": [\n      \"fork\",\n      \"completed-continue\"\n    ],\n    \"generation\": 1,\n    \"continuedFromRun\": null\n  },\n  \"reducer\": {\n    \"enabled\": true,\n    \"version\": \"1.0\",\n    \"registryFile\": \"research/findings-registry.json\",\n    \"dashboardFile\": \"research/deep-research-dashboard.md\",\n    \"strategyFile\": \"research/deep-research-strategy.md\",\n    \"machineOwnedSections\": [\n      \"key-questions\",\n      \"answered-questions\",\n      \"what-worked\",\n      \"what-failed\",\n      \"exhausted-approaches\",\n      \"ruled-out-directions\",\n      \"next-focus\"\n    ]\n  },\n  \"capabilityMatrixPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json\",\n  \"capabilityMatrixDocPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md\",\n  \"runtimeCapabilityResolver\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs\",\n  \"reducerScriptPath\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs\",\n  \"pauseSentinelPath\": \"research/.deep-research-pause\",\n  \"archiveRoot\": \"research_archive\",\n  \"migrationWindowDays\": 28,\n  \"fileProtection\": {\n    \"deep-research-config.json\": \"immutable\",\n    \"deep-research-state.jsonl\": \"append-only\",\n    \"deep-research-strategy.md\": \"mutable\",\n    \"deep-research-dashboard.md\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"findings-registry.json\": \"auto-generated\",\n    \"iteration-*.md\": \"write-once\",\n    \"research/research.md\": \"mutable\"\n  },\n  \"_optimizerManaged\": {\n    \"description\": \"Fields managed by the offline loop optimizer (042.004). See optimizer-manifest.json for the canonical tunable/locked field registry.\",\n    \"manifestPath\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json\",\n    \"tunableFields\": [\"convergenceThreshold\", \"stuckThreshold\", \"maxIterations\"],\n    \"lockedFields\": [\"lineage\", \"reducer\", \"fileProtection\", \"sessionId\", \"status\", \"antiConvergence.convergenceMode\", \"antiConvergence.stopPolicy\"],\n    \"promotionMode\": \"advisory-only\"\n  }\n}","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":82,"totalLines":82,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json","time":{"start":1783486574831,"end":1783486574834}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc612187804923e016a4dd86ebcb08191b5481a17f453ff12"}},"id":"prt_f401570e0001Use0fgPzdldzQ6","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486574860,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_wQJCrPG4Fsx4EPMpTTQB6DaD","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Strategy Template\n3: description: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research strategy\"\n6:   - \"research strategy template\"\n7:   - \"research session tracking\"\n8:   - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n9:   - \"research stop conditions\"\n10:   - \"ruled out research directions\"\n11: importance_tier: normal\n12: contextType: planning\n13: version: 1.14.0.19\n14: ---\n15: \n16: # Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n17: \n18: Runtime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n19: \n20: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n21: \n22: ### Purpose\n23: \n24: Serves as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n25: \n26: ### Usage\n27: \n28: - **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n29: - **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n30: - **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n31: - **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n32: \n33: ### Question Injection Surface\n34: \n35: Use `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n36: \n37: - `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n38: - `text`: question text to promote\n39: - `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n40: - `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n41: - `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n42: - `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n43: \n44: The reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n45: \n46: Question ownership is explicit:\n47: \n48: - Inbox rows are immutable input.\n49: - The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n50: - Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n51: \n52: When an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n53: \n54: ---\n55: \n56: ## 2. TOPIC\n57: [Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n62: ## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n63: Generated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n64: \n65: - [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n66: - [ ] [Question 2]\n67: - [ ] [Question 3]\n68: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n69: \n70: ---\n71: \n72: ## 4. NON-GOALS\n73: [What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n74: \n75: ---\n76: \n77: ## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n78: [Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n79: \n80: ---\n81: \n82: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n83: ## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n84: [None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n85: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n86: \n87: ---\n88: \n89: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n90: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n91: ## 7. WHAT WORKED\n92: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n93: - [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n94: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n95: \n96: ---\n97: \n98: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n99: ## 8. WHAT FAILED\n100: [First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n101: - [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n102: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n103: \n104: ---\n105: \n106: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n107: ## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n108: [Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n109: \n110: ### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n111: - What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n112: - Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n113: - Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n114: \n115: ### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n116: - What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n117: - Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n118: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n119: \n120: ---\n121: \n122: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n123: ## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n124: [Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n125: - [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n126: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n127: \n128: ---\n129: \n130: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n131: ## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n132: [Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n133: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n134: \n135: ---\n136: \n137: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n138: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n139: [Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n140: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n141: \n142: ---\n143: \n144: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n145: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n146: [Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n147: \n148: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n149: \n150: Populate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n151: \n152: - Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n153: - Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n154: - Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n155: - Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n156: \n157: Do not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n158: \n159: ---\n160: \n161: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n162: - Max iterations: [from config]\n163: - Convergence threshold: [from config]\n164: - Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n165: - Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n166: - research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n167: - Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n168: - Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n169: - Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n170: - Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n171: - Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n172: - Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n173: - Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n174: - Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n175: - Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n176: - Started: [timestamp]\n\n(End of file - total 176 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Strategy Template\ndescription: Runtime template copied to research/ during initialization to track research progress, focus decisions, and outcomes across iterations.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research strategy\"\n  - \"research strategy template\"\n  - \"research session tracking\"\n  - \"exhausted research approaches\"\n  - \"research stop conditions\"\n  - \"ruled out research directions\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: planning\nversion: 1.14.0.19\n---\n\n# Deep Research Strategy - Session Tracking Template\n\nRuntime template copied to `{spec_folder}/research/` during initialization. Tracks research progress across iterations.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nServes as the \"persistent brain\" for a deep research session. Records what to investigate, what worked, what failed, and where to focus next. Read by the orchestrator and agents at every iteration.\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Init:** Orchestrator copies this template to `{spec_folder}/research/deep-research-strategy.md` and populates Topic, Key Questions, Known Context, and Research Boundaries from config and memory context.\n- **Per iteration:** Agent reads Next Focus, writes iteration evidence, and the reducer refreshes What Worked/Failed, answered questions, carried-forward questions, ruled-out directions, and Next Focus.\n- **Mutability:** Mutable — analyst-owned sections remain stable, while machine-owned sections are rewritten by the reducer after each iteration. Section 3 is a generated projection from the reducer registry.\n- **Protection:** Shared state with explicit ownership boundaries. Orchestrator validates consistency on resume.\n\n### Question Injection Surface\n\nUse `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl` to append external questions during an active run. Each line is one JSON object with:\n\n- `id`: stable inbox record identifier\n- `text`: question text to promote\n- `source`: concrete source label, such as an angle bank entry, analyst strategy, or operator note\n- `origin`: one of `angle-bank`, `analyst-strategy`, `operator`, or `legacy-import`\n- `injectedAtIteration`: iteration number when the question was introduced\n- `promotedQuestionId`: promoted registry question id, or `null` until promotion\n\nThe reducer reads the inbox on every reduce step and carries `origin` into the question registry and dashboard badges. Direct edits to Section 3 still work as a compatibility path, but they are attributed as `legacy-import`.\n\nQuestion ownership is explicit:\n\n- Inbox rows are immutable input.\n- The reducer registry is canonical question state.\n- Section 3 is rendered only from the registry view.\n\nWhen an inbox row targets an existing registry question but carries different text, the reducer keeps the registry value, records `operatorDecision: needs_decision`, and appends a `question_conflict` event with both `inboxValue` and `registryValue`.\n\n---\n\n## 2. TOPIC\n[Research topic from config -- set during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 3. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\nGenerated from the reducer registry. Add external or late questions through `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`; direct edits are imported as compatibility input and may be replaced on the next reduce step.\n\n- [ ] [Question 1 -- identified during initialization or iteration 1]\n- [ ] [Question 2]\n- [ ] [Question 3]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 4. NON-GOALS\n[What this research session is NOT trying to answer -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n## 5. STOP CONDITIONS\n[Explicit conditions beyond convergence that should end the session -- populated during initialization]\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 6. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n[None yet -- populated as iterations answer questions]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 7. WHAT WORKED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it worked] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 8. WHAT FAILED\n[First iteration -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n- [Approach]: [Why it failed] (iteration N)\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 9. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n[Populated when an approach has been tried from multiple angles without success]\n\n### [Category Name] -- BLOCKED (iteration N, N attempts)\n- What was tried: [specific approaches attempted]\n- Why blocked: [root cause of exhaustion]\n- Do NOT retry: [explicit prohibition]\n\n### [Category Name] -- PRODUCTIVE (iteration N)\n- What worked: [successful approaches in this category]\n- Prefer for: [related questions where this category may help]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 10. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n[Approaches that were investigated and definitively eliminated -- consolidated from iteration dead-end data]\n- [Approach]: [Why ruled out] (iteration N, evidence: [source])\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 11A. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n[Self-owned open questions from iteration write-back -- populated after iteration 1 completes]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n[Recommended focus area for the next iteration -- updated at end of each iteration]\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n[Populated during initialization from memory_context() results, if any prior work exists]\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n\nPopulate during initialization when the target is codebase-scoped. Keep this pointer-based and small:\n\n- Source pointers: paths, symbols, or resource-map entries relevant to the topic.\n- Reuse candidates: existing utilities, patterns, docs, or agents worth extending.\n- Integration points: files or contracts the research is likely to touch.\n- Constraints and risks: scope limits, stale graph or memory gaps, and known non-goals.\n\nDo not inline full source bodies. Do not dispatch the retired standalone context loop. Use `@context` for one-shot retrieval, and use this snapshot only to seed the research loop.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: [from config]\n- Convergence threshold: [from config]\n- Per-iteration budget: [from config.maxToolCallsPerIteration] tool calls, [from config.maxMinutesPerIteration] minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true (default)\n- research/research.md ownership: workflow-owned canonical synthesis output\n- Lifecycle branches: `resume`, `restart` (live); `fork`, `completed-continue` (deferred, not runtime-wired)\n- Machine-owned sections: reducer controls Sections 3, 6, 7-11A\n- Question injection surface: `{spec_folder}/research/inbox.jsonl`\n- Question conflict owner: reducer registry; `question_conflict` events surface inbox/registry disagreements for operator decision\n- Canonical pause sentinel: `research/.deep-research-pause`\n- Capability matrix: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/runtime_capabilities.json`\n- Capability matrix doc: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/guides/capability_matrix.md`\n- Capability resolver: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/runtime-capabilities.cjs`\n- Current generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n- Started: [timestamp]","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":176,"totalLines":176,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md","time":{"start":1783486574849,"end":1783486574859}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc612187804923e016a4dd86ebcb4819194b46a2970813955"}},"id":"prt_f401570f9001wB1NKS9poD6wt5","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486574861,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_bqW7r0KY3GMftUBCCSnTmsXH","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: Deep Research Dashboard Template\n3: description: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\n4: trigger_phrases:\n5:   - \"deep research dashboard\"\n6:   - \"research session overview\"\n7:   - \"research dashboard template\"\n8:   - \"research convergence trend\"\n9:   - \"research dead ends section\"\n10: importance_tier: normal\n11: contextType: general\n12: version: 1.14.0.9\n13: ---\n14: \n15: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n16: \n17: Auto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n18: \n19: ## 1. OVERVIEW\n20: \n21: ### Purpose\n22: \n23: Provides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n24: 1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n25: 2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n26: 3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n27: \n28: ### Usage\n29: \n30: - **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n31: - **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n32: - **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n33: - **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n34: \n35: ---\n36: \n37: ## 2. STATUS\n38: - Topic: [from config]\n39: - Started: [from config.createdAt]\n40: - Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n41: - Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n42: - Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n43: - Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n44: - Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n45: - Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n46: \n47: ---\n48: \n49: ## 3. PROGRESS\n50: \n51: | # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n52: |---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n53: | [per iteration from JSONL] |\n54: \n55: - iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n56: - keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n57: - openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n58: - resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: ## 4. QUESTIONS\n63: - Answered: [X/Y]\n64: - [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n65: - [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: ## 5. TREND\n70: - Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n71: - Stuck count: [N]\n72: - Guard violations: [none | list]\n73: - convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n74: - coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n75: \n76: ---\n77: \n78: ## 6. DEAD ENDS\n79: - [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n80: \n81: ---\n82: \n83: ## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n84: [from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n89: - [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n90: - [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n91: \n92: ---\n93: \n94: ## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n95: \n96: Reference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n97: \n98: ```markdown\n99: # Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n100: \n101: ## 2. STATUS\n102: - Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n103: - Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n104: - Status: ITERATING\n105: - Iteration: 5 of 10\n106: - Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n107: - Parent Session: none\n108: - Lifecycle Mode: new\n109: - Generation: 1\n110: \n111: ## 3. PROGRESS\n112: \n113: | # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n114: |---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n115: | 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n116: | 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n117: | 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n118: | 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n119: | 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n120: \n121: ## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n122: - Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n123: - Stuck count: 0\n124: - Guard violations: none\n125: - convergenceScore: 0.71\n126: - coverageBySources: 0.83\n127: ```\n\n(End of file - total 127 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.9\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","text":"---\ntitle: Deep Research Dashboard Template\ndescription: Template for the auto-generated dashboard file regenerated after every iteration from JSONL + strategy data. Provides human-readable session overview and recovery surface.\ntrigger_phrases:\n  - \"deep research dashboard\"\n  - \"research session overview\"\n  - \"research dashboard template\"\n  - \"research convergence trend\"\n  - \"research dead ends section\"\nimportance_tier: normal\ncontextType: general\nversion: 1.14.0.9\n---\n\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\nAuto-generated from JSONL state log and strategy file. Regenerated after every iteration evaluation. Never manually edited.\n\n## 1. OVERVIEW\n\n### Purpose\n\nProvides a compact, human-readable summary of the current research session. Serves three roles:\n1. **Observability** — quick status check during long autonomous runs\n2. **Recovery surface** — second recovery channel alongside JSONL after context compaction\n3. **Lifecycle decision** — in confirm mode, shown before `resume` or `restart`\n\n### Usage\n\n- **Location:** `{artifact_dir}/deep-research-dashboard.md`\n- **Generated by:** Orchestrator (step_generate_dashboard in YAML workflow)\n- **Data sources:** `deep-research-state.jsonl` + `findings-registry.json` + `deep-research-strategy.md`\n- **Protection:** `auto-generated` — overwritten each iteration, never manually edited\n\n---\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: [from config]\n- Started: [from config.createdAt]\n- Status: [ITERATING | CONVERGING | STUCK_RECOVERY | COMPLETE]\n- Iteration: [N] of [maxIterations]\n- Session ID: [from config.lineage.sessionId]\n- Parent Session: [from config.lineage.parentSessionId or none]\n- Lifecycle Mode: [new | resume | restart]\n- Generation: [from config.lineage.generation]\n\n---\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus | Track | Ratio | Findings | Status |\n|---|-------|-------|-------|----------|--------|\n| [per iteration from JSONL] |\n\n- iterationsCompleted: [from findings registry metrics]\n- keyFindings: [from findings registry metrics]\n- openQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n- resolvedQuestions: [from findings registry metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 4. QUESTIONS\n- Answered: [X/Y]\n- [x] Q1: [summary] (iteration N)\n- [ ] Q2: [remaining]\n\n---\n\n## 5. TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: [0.XX -> 0.XX -> 0.XX] [improving | stable | declining]\n- Stuck count: [N]\n- Guard violations: [none | list]\n- convergenceScore: [from reducer metrics]\n- coverageBySources: [from reducer metrics]\n\n---\n\n## 6. DEAD ENDS\n- [approach]: [reason] (iteration N)\n\n---\n\n## 7. NEXT FOCUS\n[from strategy.md \"Next Focus\" section]\n\n---\n\n## 8. ACTIVE RISKS\n- [guard violations, high stuck count, declining trend, etc.]\n- [migration events, reducer warnings, lifecycle conflicts]\n\n---\n\n## 9. EXAMPLE (POPULATED)\n\nReference snippet showing what a rendered dashboard looks like after iteration 5 of a 10-iteration run. Use this as a visual anchor when inspecting a live dashboard.\n\n```markdown\n# Deep Research Dashboard - Session Overview\n\n## 2. STATUS\n- Topic: OpenCode plugin loader resilience\n- Started: 2026-04-20T09:14:22+02:00\n- Status: ITERATING\n- Iteration: 5 of 10\n- Session ID: dr-20260420-091422\n- Parent Session: none\n- Lifecycle Mode: new\n- Generation: 1\n\n## 3. PROGRESS\n\n| # | Focus                       | Track        | Ratio | Findings | Status     |\n|---|-----------------------------|--------------|-------|----------|------------|\n| 1 | Entry-point discovery rules | architecture | 0.82  | 4        | converging |\n| 2 | ESM vs CommonJS interop     | runtime      | 0.64  | 3        | converging |\n| 3 | Plugin-load error surfaces  | observability| 0.47  | 2        | converging |\n| 4 | Host/plugin version gating  | lifecycle    | 0.35  | 2        | converging |\n| 5 | Cross-runtime parity        | portability  | 0.28  | 1        | converging |\n\n## 5. CONVERGENCE TREND\n- Last 3 ratios: 0.47 -> 0.35 -> 0.28 (declining)\n- Stuck count: 0\n- Guard violations: none\n- convergenceScore: 0.71\n- coverageBySources: 0.83\n```","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":127,"totalLines":127,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_dashboard.md","time":{"start":1783486574851,"end":1783486574860}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0bc612187804923e016a4dd86ebcb88191b8cbda51a04920ae"}},"id":"prt_f40157102001pnI1ZCT6UHq7l6","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40154876001G15PCi9dfpJ6tJ"}}
