{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486730899,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_EXiBEPDdDsTt1TeVXyl2grOk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [ ] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n11: - [ ] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n12: - [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n13: - [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n14: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n20: - Do not implement or move files.\n21: - Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n22: - Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: - At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n28: - Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n29: - The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: None yet.\n36: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n37: \n38: ---\n39: \n40: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n41: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n42: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n43: None yet.\n44: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n45: \n46: ---\n47: \n48: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n49: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n50: None yet.\n51: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n52: \n53: ---\n54: \n55: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n56: ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n57: None yet.\n58: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: \n60: ---\n61: \n62: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n63: ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n64: None yet.\n65: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n66: \n67: ---\n68: \n69: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n70: ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n71: None yet.\n72: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n73: \n74: ---\n75: \n76: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n77: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n78: Structural layout and ownership seams: verify the live split between workflow skill packets, runtime libraries/scripts, and command YAML before judging whether the merge should make runtime a nested packet under a unified system skill.\n79: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n80: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n81: \n82: ---\n83: \n84: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n85: - Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n86: - Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n87: - `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n88: \n89: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n90: - Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n91: - Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n92: - Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n93: \n94: ---\n95: \n96: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n97: - Max iterations: 10\n98: - Min iterations: 3\n99: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n100: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n101: - Progressive synthesis: true\n102: - Current generation: 1\n103: - Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z\n\n(End of file - total 103 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [ ] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [ ] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [ ] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.\n- Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n- Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n- At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n- Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n- The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nStructural layout and ownership seams: verify the live split between workflow skill packets, runtime libraries/scripts, and command YAML before judging whether the merge should make runtime a nested packet under a unified system skill.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n- Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n- `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n- Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n- Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Min iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":103,"totalLines":103,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783486730889,"end":1783486730896}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0b01dd0644568e7e016a4dd90ace2881918bff4307b42a9653"}},"id":"prt_f4017d285001nmHZX6J3