:     {\n74:       \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\",\n75:       \"sha256\": \"187a85f1719cc7623a0df1bbf72c8052de4ca53344e0ef8276c026f9a6751efb\",\n76:       \"section\": \"full\"\n77:     },\n78:     {\n79:       \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\",\n80:       \"sha256\": \"cba6c31b8f9f296cb852df3a09baa5374a0f2da8f12ea8b0ed1f7587fa4a022a\",\n\n(Showing lines 1-80 of 479. Use offset=81 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"<!-- GENERATED_COMMAND_CONTRACT_HEADER_START\n{\n  \"id\": \"deep/research\",\n  \"command\": \"/deep:research\",\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"generatedBy\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs\",\n  \"sourceDigests\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/research.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"d0b29d814e0b47a5876c942beab504e93fe838f55fff8813c4fe88069e8b96f5\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ef9fd8156deccea8f0bf332c7eea4378f28d3b6b6937d8bea00198a8ae15db2e\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"cc283b7c5e62bd8b012a8f249f4cc63f4f353ad264358e1a5c9b85d753713d64\",","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md","text":"<!-- GENERATED_COMMAND_CONTRACT_HEADER_START\n{\n  \"id\": \"deep/research\",\n  \"command\": \"/deep:research\",\n  \"version\": 1,\n  \"generatedBy\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs\",\n  \"sourceDigests\": [\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/research.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"d0b29d814e0b47a5876c942beab504e93fe838f55fff8813c4fe88069e8b96f5\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_presentation.txt\",\n      \"sha256\": \"ef9fd8156deccea8f0bf332c7eea4378f28d3b6b6937d8bea00198a8ae15db2e\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"cc283b7c5e62bd8b012a8f249f4cc63f4f353ad264358e1a5c9b85d753713d64\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml\",\n      \"sha256\": \"634e3cace3e2eea2b0c1a01cf9c078df12e96b78407fabe678f7b66b7a19e933\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_confirm.yaml\",\n      \"sha256\": \"44e63a6a531f929faa5f720af6b9a950c26b304412e55c8051a52ac44e8e35ea\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\",\n      \"sha256\": \"790d462884619d320352d957ada7a6b40be2f79dfc70db7e1ba5830825c846fb\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"75d26ab439f8fab2b9a667e9fab4b1c7a42201e61f2ed823f502ba4be0313a75\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/SKILL.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"b29824d384b85b8cf8e8a0ba8dba3e90e00359ff41ef31b13b794d2093e0cdd4\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/loop_protocol.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"110ed186b9b77cbe8ef47fcca69ab04b410541ae844aec1df145d3d38622d881\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"18fd54c8024f85d447bafbdcbd849c5eab5f61a47c81b398fd6b57a6810cd4d8\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/state/state_format.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"e2de11c00ab2f35394164ccc8922dc02f2523cb1f5fe7bd0b92fa1b87595e03c\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/convergence/convergence.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"489e960f4dd6fd720614343c7e55e8ab08d84f4195124e8a16a22c72ef0e7e0c\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_config.json\",\n      \"sha256\": \"3bf720deec29aedf47f93c20ca6f705266cdb9b7e0a66c43e9b1a10d40831c71\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/deep_research_strategy.md\",\n      \"sha256\": \"187a85f1719cc7623a0df1bbf72c8052de4ca53344e0ef8276c026f9a6751efb\",\n      \"section\": \"full\"\n    },\n    {\n      \"path\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/assets/prompt_pack_iteration.md.tmpl\",\n      \"sha256\": \"cba6c31b8f9f296cb852df3a09baa5374a0f2da8f12ea8b0ed1f7587fa4a022a\",","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":80,"totalLines":479,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md","time":{"start":1783486909998,"end":1783486910009}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a76281af48175f016a4dd9bde9e08191b954989ba42e0de3"}},"id":"prt_f401a8e2d001CbS9tLKpplJKsI","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401a5a58001PMnNHAbH40r7pb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486910015,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_BciHMC769UeHIDRQm5w6dtB3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts","offset":90,"limit":90},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n90: \n91: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n92: // MODULE: Merged Deep-Loop Identity + Mode Layer\n93: // ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n94: //\n95: // The active legacy deep-loop modes (deep-research, deep-review,\n96: // deep-ai-council, deep-improvement) are folded into one public skill,\n97: // deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode (see\n98: // deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json). canonicalSkillId above is\n99: // deliberately UNCHANGED: an alias still resolves to its mode-level legacy id\n100: // (e.g. 'spec_kit:deep-review' -> 'deep-review') so existing callers and the\n101: // alias contract keep working. This layer adds the SECOND projection — legacy\n102: // mode-level id -> (merged skill, workflowMode) — that routers use to land on\n103: // deep-loop-workflows with the right mode once the old skill nodes leave the\n104: // graph.\n105: //\n106: // The removed standalone context route is intentionally absent from\n107: // DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL and no longer appears in active registry routing.\n108: // Use @context for retrieval and research/review bounded snapshots for loops.\n109: export const MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = 'deep-loop-workflows';\n110: \n111: const ALIAS_TO_MODE = new Map<string, string>(\n112:   Object.entries(RAW_ALIAS_GROUPS).flatMap(([canonical, aliases]) => {\n113:     const mode = DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL[canonical];\n114:     if (!mode) return [];\n115:     return [\n116:       [canonical, mode] as const,\n117:       ...aliases.map((alias) => [alias, mode] as const),\n118:     ];\n119:   }),\n120: );\n121: \n122: const PROMPT_ALIAS_ENTRIES = Array.from(ALIAS_TO_MODE.entries())\n123:   .sort((left, right) => right[0].length - left[0].length || left[0].localeCompare(right[0]));\n124: \n125: function escapeRegExp(value: string): string {\n126:   return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n127: }\n128: \n129: function promptContainsAlias(promptLower: string, alias: string): boolean {\n130:   const normalized = alias.toLowerCase();\n131:   if (!normalized) return false;\n132:   if (/^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9 -]*[a-z0-9]$/u.test(normalized)) {\n133:     return new RegExp(`(^|[^a-z0-9])${escapeRegExp(normalized)}([^a-z0-9]|$)`, 'u').test(promptLower);\n134:   }\n135:   return promptLower.includes(normalized);\n136: }\n137: \n138: /**\n139:  * Resolve any deep-loop alias (or mode-level legacy id) to its workflowMode, or\n140:  * null when the id is not a folded deep-loop mode.\n141:  */\n142: export function modeForAlias(skillId: string): string | null {\n143:   return ALIAS_TO_MODE.get(skillId) ?? ALIAS_TO_MODE.get(canonicalSkillId(skillId)) ?? null;\n144: }\n145: \n146: /**\n147:  * Resolve a deep-loop workflowMode when a prompt directly names a generated\n148:  * alias. Returns null for broad merged-skill prompts that require hub routing.\n149:  */\n150: export function modeForPromptAlias(prompt: string): string | null {\n151:   const promptLower = prompt.toLowerCase();\n152:   for (const [alias, mode] of PROMPT_ALIAS_ENTRIES) {\n153:     if (promptContainsAlias(promptLower, alias)) return mode;\n154:   }\n155:   return null;\n156: }\n157: \n158: /**\n159:  * Resolve any deep-loop alias to the merged skill id (deep-loop-workflows) when\n160:  * it names a folded mode, else fall back to the plain canonical id. Non-deep\n161:  * skills are returned unchanged.\n162:  */\n163: export function mergedSkillForAlias(skillId: string): string {\n164:   return modeForAlias(skillId) !== null ? MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID : canonicalSkillId(skillId);\n165: }\n\n(End of file - total 165 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Merged Deep-Loop Identity + Mode Layer\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\n// The active legacy deep-loop modes (deep-research, deep-review,\n// deep-ai-council, deep-improvement) are folded into one public skill,\n// deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode (see\n// deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json). canonicalSkillId above is\n// deliberately UNCHANGED: an alias still resolves to its mode-level legacy id\n// (e.g. 'spec_kit:deep-review' -> 'deep-review') so existing callers and the\n// alias contract keep working. This layer adds the SECOND projection — legacy\n// mode-level id -> (merged skill, workflowMode) — that routers use to land on\n// deep-loop-workflows with the right mode once the old skill nodes leave the\n// graph.\n//\n// The removed standalone context route is intentionally absent from\n// DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL and no longer appears in active registry routing.\n// Use @context for retrieval and research/review bounded snapshots for loops.\nexport const MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = 'deep-loop-workflows';","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts","text":"\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// MODULE: Merged Deep-Loop Identity + Mode Layer\n// ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n//\n// The active legacy deep-loop modes (deep-research, deep-review,\n// deep-ai-council, deep-improvement) are folded into one public skill,\n// deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode (see\n// deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json). canonicalSkillId above is\n// deliberately UNCHANGED: an alias still resolves to its mode-level legacy id\n// (e.g. 'spec_kit:deep-review' -> 'deep-review') so existing callers and the\n// alias contract keep working. This layer adds the SECOND projection — legacy\n// mode-level id -> (merged skill, workflowMode) — that routers use to land on\n// deep-loop-workflows with the right mode once the old skill nodes leave the\n// graph.\n//\n// The removed standalone context route is intentionally absent from\n// DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL and no longer appears in active registry routing.\n// Use @context for retrieval and research/review bounded snapshots for loops.\nexport const MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = 'deep-loop-workflows';\n\nconst ALIAS_TO_MODE = new Map<string, string>(\n  Object.entries(RAW_ALIAS_GROUPS).flatMap(([canonical, aliases]) => {\n    const mode = DEEP_MODE_BY_CANONICAL[canonical];\n    if (!mode) return [];\n    return [\n      [canonical, mode] as const,\n      ...aliases.map((alias) => [alias, mode] as const),\n    ];\n  }),\n);\n\nconst PROMPT_ALIAS_ENTRIES = Array.from(ALIAS_TO_MODE.entries())\n  .sort((left, right) => right[0].length - left[0].length || left[0].localeCompare(right[0]));\n\nfunction escapeRegExp(value: string): string {\n  return value.replace(/[.*+?^${}()|[\\]\\\\]/g, '\\\\$&');\n}\n\nfunction promptContainsAlias(promptLower: string, alias: string): boolean {\n  const normalized = alias.toLowerCase();\n  if (!normalized) return false;\n  if (/^[a-z0-9][a-z0-9 -]*[a-z0-9]$/u.test(normalized)) {\n    return new RegExp(`(^|[^a-z0-9])${escapeRegExp(normalized)}([^a-z0-9]|$)`, 'u').test(promptLower);\n  }\n  return promptLower.includes(normalized);\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve any deep-loop alias (or mode-level legacy id) to its workflowMode, or\n * null when the id is not a folded deep-loop mode.\n */\nexport function modeForAlias(skillId: string): string | null {\n  return ALIAS_TO_MODE.get(skillId) ?? ALIAS_TO_MODE.get(canonicalSkillId(skillId)) ?? null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve a deep-loop workflowMode when a prompt directly names a generated\n * alias. Returns null for broad merged-skill prompts that require hub routing.\n */\nexport function modeForPromptAlias(prompt: string): string | null {\n  const promptLower = prompt.toLowerCase();\n  for (const [alias, mode] of PROMPT_ALIAS_ENTRIES) {\n    if (promptContainsAlias(promptLower, alias)) return mode;\n  }\n  return null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve any deep-loop alias to the merged skill id (deep-loop-workflows) when\n * it names a folded mode, else fall back to the plain canonical id. Non-deep\n * skills are returned unchanged.\n */\nexport function mergedSkillForAlias(skillId: string): string {\n  return modeForAlias(skillId) !== null ? MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID : canonicalSkillId(skillId);\n}","lineStart":90,"lineEnd":165,"totalLines":165,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts","time":{"start":1783486909994,"end":1783486910014}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a76281af48175f016a4dd9bde9d08191809139289b700a8c"}},"id":"prt_f401a8e28001b0hzzH0gf6BhUi","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401a5a58001PMnNHAbH40r7pb"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486910018,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_iTeskNnur9bROSB6jb51RopN","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py","offset":2568,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n2568: DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.65\n2569: \n2570: # The active legacy deep-loop modes are folded into one public skill,\n2571: # deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode. The Candidate-3 internal\n2572: # discriminator keys below stay spelled as the legacy skill ids because the\n2573: # regex pattern groups and prior-art matchers key off them and match live\n2574: # artifact/agent names still present across the live agent and artifact surfaces;\n2575: # DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY projects each onto the merged skill's workflowMode so\n2576: # the routing contract emits {skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode}. The removed\n2577: # standalone context route is intentionally not a Candidate-3 discriminator, so\n2578: # DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS stays 3.\n2579: MERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = \"deep-loop-workflows\"\n2580: # BEGIN GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION\n2581: DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS = (\"deep-review\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-ai-council\")\n2582: DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY = {\n2583:     \"deep-review\": \"review\",\n2584:     \"deep-research\": \"research\",\n2585:     \"deep-ai-council\": \"ai-council\",\n2586: }\n2587: # END GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION\n2588: \n2589: DEEP_ROUTING_LEXICAL_PATTERNS = {\n2590:     \"deep-review\": (\n2591:         (r\":review:(?:auto|confirm)\\b\", 2.0),\n2592:         (r\"\\bdeep[- ]review\\b\", 1.8),\n2593:         (r\"\\breview loop\\b|\\biterative review\\b|\\bmulti-pass review\\b\", 1.4),\n2594:         (r\"\\baudit\\b|\\breview\\b\", 0.7),\n2595:         (r\"\\bfindings?\\b|\\bconvergence\\b|\\bloop\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.35),\n2596:     ),\n2597:     \"deep-research\": (\n2598:         (r\"\\bautoresearch\\b|/autoresearch\\b\", 2.0),\n2599:         (r\"\\bdeep[- ]research\\b|\\bresearch loop\\b|\\biterative research\\b\", 1.8),\n2600:         (r\"\\binvestigat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bresearch\\b|\\bdiscover(?:y|ing)?\\b\", 1.2),\n2601:         (r\"\\bnewinforatio\\b|\\bnegative knowledge\\b|\\bruled out\\b\", 1.2),\n2602:         (r\"\\bconvergence\\b|\\bloop\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.25),\n2603:     ),\n2604:     \"deep-ai-council\": (\n2605:         (r\"\\bdeep[- ]ai[- ]council\\b|\\bdeep[- ]council\\b|\\bsk[- ]ai[- ]council\\b|\\bai[- ]council\\b\", 2.0),\n2606:         (r\"\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bmulti-seat\\b|\\bcouncil\\b\", 1.5),\n2607:         (r\"\\bstrateg(?:y|ies)\\b|\\boption(?:s)?\\b|\\bverdict\\b|\\bdecision\\b\", 0.7),\n2608:         (r\"\\bconver(?:ge|ges|gence)\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.2),\n2609:     ),\n2610: }\n2611: \n2612: DEEP_ROUTING_STRUCTURAL_PATTERNS = {\n2613:     \"deep-review\": (\n2614:         (r\"\\bfindings? stabiliz(?:e|es|ed|ing)\\b|\\bfindingstability\\b\", 2.0),\n2615:         (r\"\\b(p0|p1|p2)\\b|\\bseverity tiers?\\b|\\badversarial\\b|\\bdefect(?:s)?\\b\", 1.4),\n2616:         (r\"\\bcode audit\\b|\\bquality audit\\b|\\brelease readiness\\b|\\bsecurity audit\\b\", 1.2),\n2617:         (r\"\\bcoverage-graph signals?\\b\", 0.4),\n2618:     ),\n2619:     \"deep-research\": (\n2620:         (r\"\\binvestigation\\b|\\binvestigate whether\\b|\\bresearch topic\\b|\\boriginal .* investigation topic\\b\", 1.8),\n2621:         (r\"\\bnewinforatio\\b|\\bnew information\\b|\\bdiscover new\\b|\\bdiscovering new\\b\", 1.6),\n2622:         (r\"\\bnegative knowledge\\b|\\bruled[- ]out directions?\\b|\\bdead ends?\\b\", 1.3),\n2623:         (r\"\\bdeep[- ]research packet\\b.*\\bdrift\\b|\\bdrift\\b.*\\binvestigation topic\\b\", 1.5),\n2624:     ),\n2625:     \"deep-ai-council\": (\n2626:         (r\"\\barchitecture decision\\b|\\bdesign decision\\b|\\bstrategy comparison\\b\", 2.0),\n2627:         (r\"\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bmulti-seat\\b|\\bopinion synthesis\\b\", 1.8),\n2628:         (r\"\\bwhether\\b.{0,80}\\b(or|vs|versus)\\b|\\bcoverage-graph signals\\b.{0,80}\\badjudicator self-scoring\\b\", 1.5),\n2629:         (r\"\\bverdict stability\\b|\\badjudicator[- ]verdict\\b|\\brecommend the best\\b\", 1.4),\n2630:     ),\n2631: }\n2632: \n2633: \n2634: def _packet_context_has_prior_art(packet_context: Dict[str, Any]) -> bool:\n2635:     \"\"\"Return True when routing context contains any usable prior-art signal.\"\"\"\n2636:     return bool(packet_context)\n2637: \n2638: \n2639: def _flatten_context_values(value: Any) -> List[str]:\n2640:     \"\"\"Flatten packet-context primitives into lowercase strings for prior-art matching.\"\"\"\n2641:     if value is None:\n2642:         return []\n2643:     if isinstance(value, str):\n2644:         return [value.lower()]\n2645:     if isinstance(value, (int, float, bool)):\n2646:         return [str(value).lower()]\n2647:     if isinstance(value, dict):\n2648:         values: List[str] = []\n2649:         for key, item in value.items():\n2650:             values.append(str(key).lower())\n2651:             values.extend(_flatten_context_values(item))\n2652:         return values\n2653:     if isinstance(value, (list, tuple, set)):\n2654:         values = []\n2655:         for item in value:\n2656:             values.extend(_flatten_context_values(item))\n2657:         return values\n2658:     return [str(value).lower()]\n2659: \n2660: \n2661: def _score_prior_art(packet_context: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, float]:\n2662:     \"\"\"Score existing packet artifacts and operator history for Candidate-3 routing.\"\"\"\n2663:     scores = {skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n2664:     flattened = \" \".join(_flatten_context_values(packet_context))\n2665:     if not flattened:\n2666:         return scores\n2667: \n2668:     prior_patterns = {\n2669:         \"deep-review\": (\n2670:             r\"deep-review|review-report|deep-review-findings-registry|p0|p1|p2\",\n2671:         ),\n2672:         \"deep-research\": (\n2673:             r\"deep-research|research\\.md|deep-research-findings-registry|(^|[\\s/])findings-registry|newinforatio|research_topic\",\n2674:         ),\n2675:         \"deep-ai-council\": (\n2676:             r\"deep-ai-council|deep-council|sk-ai-council|ai-council|council-report|session-report|verdict stability\",\n2677:         ),\n2678:     }\n2679: \n2680:     for skill, patterns in prior_patterns.items():\n2681:         for pattern in patterns:\n2682:             if re.search(pattern, flattened):\n2683:                 scores[skill] += 1.0\n2684: \n2685:     recent = packet_context.get(\"recent_recommendations\") or packet_context.get(\"operator_history\")\n2686:     for value in _flatten_context_values(recent):\n2687:         for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS:\n2688:             aliases = SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS.get(skill, {skill})\n2689:             if skill in value or any(alias in value for alias in aliases):\n2690:                 scores[skill] += 0.75\n2691: \n2692:     return scores\n2693: \n2694: \n2695: def _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower: str, patterns: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, float]:\n2696:     \"\"\"Score regex pattern groups against the normalized prompt.\"\"\"\n2697:     scores = {skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n2698:     for skill, entries in patterns.items():\n2699:         for pattern, weight in entries:\n2700:             if re.search(pattern, prompt_lower):\n2701:                 scores[skill] += weight\n2702:     return scores\n2703: \n2704: \n2705: def _apply_deep_routing_incompatibility_penalties(\n2706:     prompt_lower: str,\n2707:     totals: Dict[str, float],\n2708: ) -> None:\n2709:     \"\"\"Lower plausible-but-wrong siblings when structural intent is explicit.\"\"\"\n2710:     if re.search(r\"\\bfindings? stabiliz(?:e|es|ed|ing)\\b|\\bfindingstability\\b\", prompt_lower):\n2711:         totals[\"deep-research\"] *= 0.35\n2712:         totals[\"deep-ai-council\"] *= 0.65\n2713: \n2714:     if re.search(r\"\\binvestigation\\b|\\binvestigate whether\\b|\\boriginal .* investigation topic\\b\", prompt_lower):\n2715:         totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.45\n2716: \n2717:     if re.search(r\"\\barchitecture decision\\b|\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bwhether\\b.{0,80}\\b(or|vs|versus)\\b\", prompt_lower):\n2718:         totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.50\n2719:         totals[\"deep-research\"] *= 0.55\n2720: \n2721:     if re.search(r\"\\bdeep[- ]research packet\\b.*\\bdrift\\b|\\bdrift\\b.*\\binvestigation topic\\b\", prompt_lower):\n2722:         totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.55\n2723: \n2724: \n2725: def _deep_routing_confidence(total_score: float) -> float:\n2726:     \"\"\"Map weighted Candidate scores into a 0..0.95 advisor confidence.\"\"\"\n2727:     return round(min(0.95, total_score / (total_score + 2.0)), 2)\n2728: \n2729: \n2730: def score_deep_skill_routing(prompt: str, packet_context: dict) -> Dict[str, float]:\n2731:     \"\"\"Return Candidate-3 scores for deep-review/deep-research/deep-ai-council.\n2732: \n2733:     Weighted routing is paired with parity invariants guarded by the Vitest suite.\n2734:     \"\"\"\n2735:     prompt_lower = prompt.lower()\n2736:     context = packet_context if isinstance(packet_context, dict) else {}\n2737:     lexical_scores = _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower, DEEP_ROUTING_LEXICAL_PATTERNS)\n2738:     structural_scores = _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower, DEEP_ROUTING_STRUCTURAL_PATTERNS)\n2739:     prior_art_scores = _score_prior_art(context) if _packet_context_has_prior_art(context) else {\n2740:         skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS\n2741:     }\n2742: \n2743:     totals: Dict[str, float] = {}\n2744:     for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS:\n2745:         totals[skill] = (\n2746:             lexical_scores[skill] * 1.0\n2747:             + structural_scores[skill] * 2.0\n2748:             + prior_art_scores[skill] * 3.0\n2749:         )\n2750: \n2751:     _apply_deep_routing_incompatibility_penalties(prompt_lower, totals)\n2752:     return {skill: _deep_routing_confidence(totals[skill]) for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n2753: \n2754: \n2755: def _deep_routing_confidence_band(max_score: float) -> str:\n2756:     \"\"\"Classify score confidence using the 130 Candidate-3 bands.\"\"\"\n2757:     if max_score >= 0.75:\n2758:         return \"HIGH\"\n2759:     if max_score >= 0.50:\n2760:         return \"MED\"\n2761:     return \"LOW\"\n2762: \n2763: \n2764: def _deep_routing_clarifying_question(prompt_lower: str, winner: str, runner_up: str) -> str:\n2765:     \"\"\"Return the targeted clarification for low-confidence deep-loop mode routing.\n2766: \n2767:     `winner`/`runner_up` are deep-loop-workflows workflowMode names\n2768:     (research|review|ai-council), not legacy skill ids.\n2769:     \"\"\"\n2770:     if \"architecture\" in prompt_lower or \"decision\" in prompt_lower or \"strategy\" in prompt_lower:\n2771:         return \"Are you comparing existing strategies (ai-council mode) or discovering new ones (research mode)?\"\n2772:     if \"findings\" in prompt_lower or \"convergence\" in prompt_lower or \"stabilize\" in prompt_lower:\n2773:         return \"Are these findings defects to audit until stable (review mode), research discoveries to exhaust (research mode), or council opinions to deliberate (ai-council mode)?\"\n2774:     return f\"Should this route to {winner} or {runner_up} mode, and what output do you expect: review-report.md, research.md, or council-report.md?\"\n2775: \n2776: \n2777: def deep_skill_routing_payload(prompt: str, packet_context: dict) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n2778:     \"\"\"Return the merged deep-loop routing payload with LOW-confidence clarification.\n2779: \n2780:     The five legacy deep-loop skills are collapsed into deep-loop-workflows, so\n2781:     the contract is {skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode: <workflowMode>} plus\n2782:     mode-keyed scores. Internal scoring still discriminates per mode; this layer\n2783:     projects the legacy discriminator keys onto registry workflowMode names so a\n2784:     prompt that used to win \"deep-research\" now resolves to\n2785:     (deep-loop-workflows, research) WITHOUT flattening the mode distinction.\n2786:     \"\"\"\n2787:     scores = score_deep_skill_routing(prompt, packet_context)\n\n(Showing lines 2568-2787 of 4443. Use offset=2788 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.65\n\n# The active legacy deep-loop modes are folded into one public skill,\n# deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode. The Candidate-3 internal\n# discriminator keys below stay spelled as the legacy skill ids because the\n# regex pattern groups and prior-art matchers key off them and match live\n# artifact/agent names still present across the live agent and artifact surfaces;\n# DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY projects each onto the merged skill's workflowMode so\n# the routing contract emits {skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode}. The removed\n# standalone context route is intentionally not a Candidate-3 discriminator, so\n# DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS stays 3.\nMERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = \"deep-loop-workflows\"\n# BEGIN GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION\nDEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS = (\"deep-review\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-ai-council\")\nDEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY = {\n    \"deep-review\": \"review\",\n    \"deep-research\": \"research\",\n    \"deep-ai-council\": \"ai-council\",\n}\n# END GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py","text":"DEEP_ROUTING_CONFIDENCE_THRESHOLD = 0.65\n\n# The active legacy deep-loop modes are folded into one public skill,\n# deep-loop-workflows, discriminated by workflowMode. The Candidate-3 internal\n# discriminator keys below stay spelled as the legacy skill ids because the\n# regex pattern groups and prior-art matchers key off them and match live\n# artifact/agent names still present across the live agent and artifact surfaces;\n# DEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY projects each onto the merged skill's workflowMode so\n# the routing contract emits {skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode}. The removed\n# standalone context route is intentionally not a Candidate-3 discriminator, so\n# DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS stays 3.\nMERGED_DEEP_SKILL_ID = \"deep-loop-workflows\"\n# BEGIN GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION\nDEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS = (\"deep-review\", \"deep-research\", \"deep-ai-council\")\nDEEP_ROUTING_MODE_BY_KEY = {\n    \"deep-review\": \"review\",\n    \"deep-research\": \"research\",\n    \"deep-ai-council\": \"ai-council\",\n}\n# END GENERATED DEEP ROUTING LEXICAL PROJECTION\n\nDEEP_ROUTING_LEXICAL_PATTERNS = {\n    \"deep-review\": (\n        (r\":review:(?:auto|confirm)\\b\", 2.0),\n        (r\"\\bdeep[- ]review\\b\", 1.8),\n        (r\"\\breview loop\\b|\\biterative review\\b|\\bmulti-pass review\\b\", 1.4),\n        (r\"\\baudit\\b|\\breview\\b\", 0.7),\n        (r\"\\bfindings?\\b|\\bconvergence\\b|\\bloop\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.35),\n    ),\n    \"deep-research\": (\n        (r\"\\bautoresearch\\b|/autoresearch\\b\", 2.0),\n        (r\"\\bdeep[- ]research\\b|\\bresearch loop\\b|\\biterative research\\b\", 1.8),\n        (r\"\\binvestigat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bresearch\\b|\\bdiscover(?:y|ing)?\\b\", 1.2),\n        (r\"\\bnewinforatio\\b|\\bnegative knowledge\\b|\\bruled out\\b\", 1.2),\n        (r\"\\bconvergence\\b|\\bloop\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.25),\n    ),\n    \"deep-ai-council\": (\n        (r\"\\bdeep[- ]ai[- ]council\\b|\\bdeep[- ]council\\b|\\bsk[- ]ai[- ]council\\b|\\bai[- ]council\\b\", 2.0),\n        (r\"\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bmulti-seat\\b|\\bcouncil\\b\", 1.5),\n        (r\"\\bstrateg(?:y|ies)\\b|\\boption(?:s)?\\b|\\bverdict\\b|\\bdecision\\b\", 0.7),\n        (r\"\\bconver(?:ge|ges|gence)\\b|\\biterate\\b\", 0.2),\n    ),\n}\n\nDEEP_ROUTING_STRUCTURAL_PATTERNS = {\n    \"deep-review\": (\n        (r\"\\bfindings? stabiliz(?:e|es|ed|ing)\\b|\\bfindingstability\\b\", 2.0),\n        (r\"\\b(p0|p1|p2)\\b|\\bseverity tiers?\\b|\\badversarial\\b|\\bdefect(?:s)?\\b\", 1.4),\n        (r\"\\bcode audit\\b|\\bquality audit\\b|\\brelease readiness\\b|\\bsecurity audit\\b\", 1.2),\n        (r\"\\bcoverage-graph signals?\\b\", 0.4),\n    ),\n    \"deep-research\": (\n        (r\"\\binvestigation\\b|\\binvestigate whether\\b|\\bresearch topic\\b|\\boriginal .* investigation topic\\b\", 1.8),\n        (r\"\\bnewinforatio\\b|\\bnew information\\b|\\bdiscover new\\b|\\bdiscovering new\\b\", 1.6),\n        (r\"\\bnegative knowledge\\b|\\bruled[- ]out directions?\\b|\\bdead ends?\\b\", 1.3),\n        (r\"\\bdeep[- ]research packet\\b.*\\bdrift\\b|\\bdrift\\b.*\\binvestigation topic\\b\", 1.5),\n    ),\n    \"deep-ai-council\": (\n        (r\"\\barchitecture decision\\b|\\bdesign decision\\b|\\bstrategy comparison\\b\", 2.0),\n        (r\"\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bmulti-seat\\b|\\bopinion synthesis\\b\", 1.8),\n        (r\"\\bwhether\\b.{0,80}\\b(or|vs|versus)\\b|\\bcoverage-graph signals\\b.{0,80}\\badjudicator self-scoring\\b\", 1.5),\n        (r\"\\bverdict stability\\b|\\badjudicator[- ]verdict\\b|\\brecommend the best\\b\", 1.4),\n    ),\n}\n\n\ndef _packet_context_has_prior_art(packet_context: Dict[str, Any]) -> bool:\n    \"\"\"Return True when routing context contains any usable prior-art signal.\"\"\"\n    return bool(packet_context)\n\n\ndef _flatten_context_values(value: Any) -> List[str]:\n    \"\"\"Flatten packet-context primitives into lowercase strings for prior-art matching.\"\"\"\n    if value is None:\n        return []\n    if isinstance(value, str):\n        return [value.lower()]\n    if isinstance(value, (int, float, bool)):\n        return [str(value).lower()]\n    if isinstance(value, dict):\n        values: List[str] = []\n        for key, item in value.items():\n            values.append(str(key).lower())\n            values.extend(_flatten_context_values(item))\n        return values\n    if isinstance(value, (list, tuple, set)):\n        values = []\n        for item in value:\n            values.extend(_flatten_context_values(item))\n        return values\n    return [str(value).lower()]\n\n\ndef _score_prior_art(packet_context: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Score existing packet artifacts and operator history for Candidate-3 routing.\"\"\"\n    scores = {skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n    flattened = \" \".join(_flatten_context_values(packet_context))\n    if not flattened:\n        return scores\n\n    prior_patterns = {\n        \"deep-review\": (\n            r\"deep-review|review-report|deep-review-findings-registry|p0|p1|p2\",\n        ),\n        \"deep-research\": (\n            r\"deep-research|research\\.md|deep-research-findings-registry|(^|[\\s/])findings-registry|newinforatio|research_topic\",\n        ),\n        \"deep-ai-council\": (\n            r\"deep-ai-council|deep-council|sk-ai-council|ai-council|council-report|session-report|verdict stability\",\n        ),\n    }\n\n    for skill, patterns in prior_patterns.items():\n        for pattern in patterns:\n            if re.search(pattern, flattened):\n                scores[skill] += 1.0\n\n    recent = packet_context.get(\"recent_recommendations\") or packet_context.get(\"operator_history\")\n    for value in _flatten_context_values(recent):\n        for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS:\n            aliases = SKILL_ALIAS_GROUPS.get(skill, {skill})\n            if skill in value or any(alias in value for alias in aliases):\n                scores[skill] += 0.75\n\n    return scores\n\n\ndef _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower: str, patterns: Dict[str, Any]) -> Dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Score regex pattern groups against the normalized prompt.\"\"\"\n    scores = {skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n    for skill, entries in patterns.items():\n        for pattern, weight in entries:\n            if re.search(pattern, prompt_lower):\n                scores[skill] += weight\n    return scores\n\n\ndef _apply_deep_routing_incompatibility_penalties(\n    prompt_lower: str,\n    totals: Dict[str, float],\n) -> None:\n    \"\"\"Lower plausible-but-wrong siblings when structural intent is explicit.\"\"\"\n    if re.search(r\"\\bfindings? stabiliz(?:e|es|ed|ing)\\b|\\bfindingstability\\b\", prompt_lower):\n        totals[\"deep-research\"] *= 0.35\n        totals[\"deep-ai-council\"] *= 0.65\n\n    if re.search(r\"\\binvestigation\\b|\\binvestigate whether\\b|\\boriginal .* investigation topic\\b\", prompt_lower):\n        totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.45\n\n    if re.search(r\"\\barchitecture decision\\b|\\bdeliberat(?:e|ion|ing)\\b|\\bwhether\\b.{0,80}\\b(or|vs|versus)\\b\", prompt_lower):\n        totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.50\n        totals[\"deep-research\"] *= 0.55\n\n    if re.search(r\"\\bdeep[- ]research packet\\b.*\\bdrift\\b|\\bdrift\\b.*\\binvestigation topic\\b\", prompt_lower):\n        totals[\"deep-review\"] *= 0.55\n\n\ndef _deep_routing_confidence(total_score: float) -> float:\n    \"\"\"Map weighted Candidate scores into a 0..0.95 advisor confidence.\"\"\"\n    return round(min(0.95, total_score / (total_score + 2.0)), 2)\n\n\ndef score_deep_skill_routing(prompt: str, packet_context: dict) -> Dict[str, float]:\n    \"\"\"Return Candidate-3 scores for deep-review/deep-research/deep-ai-council.\n\n    Weighted routing is paired with parity invariants guarded by the Vitest suite.\n    \"\"\"\n    prompt_lower = prompt.lower()\n    context = packet_context if isinstance(packet_context, dict) else {}\n    lexical_scores = _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower, DEEP_ROUTING_LEXICAL_PATTERNS)\n    structural_scores = _score_pattern_group(prompt_lower, DEEP_ROUTING_STRUCTURAL_PATTERNS)\n    prior_art_scores = _score_prior_art(context) if _packet_context_has_prior_art(context) else {\n        skill: 0.0 for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS\n    }\n\n    totals: Dict[str, float] = {}\n    for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS:\n        totals[skill] = (\n            lexical_scores[skill] * 1.0\n            + structural_scores[skill] * 2.0\n            + prior_art_scores[skill] * 3.0\n        )\n\n    _apply_deep_routing_incompatibility_penalties(prompt_lower, totals)\n    return {skill: _deep_routing_confidence(totals[skill]) for skill in DEEP_ROUTING_SKILLS}\n\n\ndef _deep_routing_confidence_band(max_score: float) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Classify score confidence using the 130 Candidate-3 bands.\"\"\"\n    if max_score >= 0.75:\n        return \"HIGH\"\n    if max_score >= 0.50:\n        return \"MED\"\n    return \"LOW\"\n\n\ndef _deep_routing_clarifying_question(prompt_lower: str, winner: str, runner_up: str) -> str:\n    \"\"\"Return the targeted clarification for low-confidence deep-loop mode routing.\n\n    `winner`/`runner_up` are deep-loop-workflows workflowMode names\n    (research|review|ai-council), not legacy skill ids.\n    \"\"\"\n    if \"architecture\" in prompt_lower or \"decision\" in prompt_lower or \"strategy\" in prompt_lower:\n        return \"Are you comparing existing strategies (ai-council mode) or discovering new ones (research mode)?\"\n    if \"findings\" in prompt_lower or \"convergence\" in prompt_lower or \"stabilize\" in prompt_lower:\n        return \"Are these findings defects to audit until stable (review mode), research discoveries to exhaust (research mode), or council opinions to deliberate (ai-council mode)?\"\n    return f\"Should this route to {winner} or {runner_up} mode, and what output do you expect: review-report.md, research.md, or council-report.md?\"\n\n\ndef deep_skill_routing_payload(prompt: str, packet_context: dict) -> Dict[str, Any]:\n    \"\"\"Return the merged deep-loop routing payload with LOW-confidence clarification.\n\n    The five legacy deep-loop skills are collapsed into deep-loop-workflows, so\n    the contract is {skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode: <workflowMode>} plus\n    mode-keyed scores. Internal scoring still discriminates per mode; this layer\n    projects the legacy discriminator keys onto registry workflowMode names so a\n    prompt that used to win \"deep-research\" now resolves to\n    (deep-loop-workflows, research) WITHOUT flattening the mode distinction.\n    \"\"\"\n    scores = score_deep_skill_routing(prompt, packet_context)","lineStart":2568,"lineEnd":2787,"totalLines":4443,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py","time":{"start":1783486909991,"end":1783486910017}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_06a76281af48175f016a4dd9bde9cc8191847fccdbffb70481"}},"id":"prt_f401a8e1c001YOoLyLxBx8eEL6","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401a5a58001PMnNHAbH40r7pb"}}
