{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783486988860,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"apply_patch","callID":"call_PLZNFhAYe5Qby3Wl0z80OLBu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"patchText":"*** Begin Patch\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/prompts/iteration-002.md\n+DEEP-RESEARCH\n+Resolved route: mode=research; target_agent=@deep-research; execution=single_iteration; state_source=externalized_files; do_not_switch_mode=true\n+\n+# Deep-Research Iteration Prompt Pack\n+\n+## STATE\n+\n+STATE SUMMARY (auto-generated):\n+Segment: 1 | Iteration: 2 of 10\n+Questions: 1/5 answered | Last focus: Structural layout and ownership seams\n+Last 2 ratios: N/A -> 0.82 | Stuck count: 0\n+Resource map: resource-map.md not present; skipping coverage gate.\n+Memory context refresh: none loaded yet.\n+Next focus: Path-coupling inventory across commands, agents, docs, scripts, tests, and advisor surfaces.\n+\n+Research Topic: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n+Iteration: 2 of 10\n+Focus Area: Path-coupling inventory.\n+Remaining Key Questions: path coupling, system-spec-kit tooling borrow, reference migration, fallback-router wiring\n+Carried-Forward Open Questions: Which exact path references must be rewritten atomically across commands, agents, docs, scripts, tests, and advisor surfaces?\n+Last 3 Iterations Summary: run 1: Structural layout and ownership seams (0.82)\n+\n+## STATE FILES\n+\n+- Config: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-config.json\n+- State Log: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-state.jsonl\n+- Strategy: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md\n+- Registry: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-findings-registry.json\n+- Write iteration narrative to: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+- Write per-iteration delta file to: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+\n+## CONSTRAINTS\n+\n+- LEAF iteration. Do not dispatch sub-agents.\n+- Write only inside the lineage artifact directory.\n+- Report findings only; do not implement fixes.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/iterations/iteration-002.md\n+# Iteration 2: Bidirectional Path-Coupling Inventory\n+\n+## Focus\n+This iteration inventoried concrete path couplings that a `deep-loop-runtime` + `deep-loop-workflows` merge must repair. The focus was not every textual mention, but migration-critical references that affect command execution, agent routing, test discovery, advisor routing, compiled command contracts, and operational diagnostics.\n+\n+## Actions Taken\n+- Read the current state log, strategy, and registry before selecting the path-coupling focus.\n+- Grepped command, agent, advisor, and system-spec-kit surfaces for `deep-loop-runtime` and `deep-loop-workflows` references.\n+- Read representative files at the highest-risk coupling points: `/deep:*` YAML contracts, doctor route manifest, orchestrator route contract, advisor deep-routing code, TypeScript alias projection, system-spec-kit test config, optimizer manifest, and runtime integration-points doc.\n+\n+## Findings\n+1. `/deep:*` command YAML is the highest-risk rewrite surface because it embeds both sides of the split: mode packet paths under `deep-loop-workflows` and runtime script/library paths under `deep-loop-runtime`. `deep_research_auto.yaml` references workflow skill docs/assets [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77], runtime fanout/lock/convergence/prompt/audit/validation/upsert/merge paths [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:160] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:229-243] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:616] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:819-859] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:1017-1039] [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:1290-1297]. This must be migrated atomically with the directory move.\n+2. The compiled command contract is a second command-surface coupling, not just generated noise: `deep_research.contract.md` says it was generated by `deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs` and carries source digests for `/deep:research`, both YAML modes, `mode-registry.json`, hub `SKILL.md`, and deep-research packet files [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1-80]. Any path move must regenerate compiled contracts after source rewrites.\n+3. `/doctor deep-loop` directly routes diagnostics to runtime script paths and declares its route as read-only diagnostic over coverage/council graphs [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110]. A merge must update doctor route manifests and doctor assets, or diagnostics will keep pointing to the old runtime skill.\n+4. Agent routing is coupled through `orchestrate.md`: deep routes must include a `Deep Route:` line whose source of truth is `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json`, and dispatch correctness is verifiable by diffing against that registry [SOURCE: .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206]. The registry path is therefore an agent prompt contract, not just a documentation link.\n+5. The skill advisor has two hardcoded coupling layers. Python deep routing projects legacy deep skill IDs to `{skill: deep-loop-workflows, mode}` and sets `MODE_REGISTRY_PATH` to the workflows registry [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587]. TypeScript alias scoring similarly resolves old deep-loop aliases to `deep-loop-workflows` and points comments/readers to `deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:95-165]. Reference migration must include advisor source, tests, graph metadata, and generated skill graph records.\n+6. `system-spec-kit` is a bidirectional consumer, not only an external dependency. Its Vitest config discovers `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:15-22], while its optimizer manifest lists deep-research/deep-review config files under `deep-loop-workflows` [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json:7-18] [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json:30-39]. Moving either side without updating system-spec-kit tests and optimizer metadata will silently degrade verification.\n+7. The runtime integration-points document already records additional consumers beyond the main command loop: ai-council command/orchestration, doctor route/update, system-code-graph playbooks, legacy MCP READMEs, and deep-improvement docs [SOURCE: .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:158-170]. This is an existing migration checklist and should be used as a coverage oracle.\n+\n+## Questions Answered\n+- Answered: Bidirectional path-coupling repair must include command YAML + compiled contracts, doctor, agents, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, runtime integration docs, and mode packet references.\n+\n+## Questions Remaining\n+- Which system-spec-kit tooling should remain borrowed rather than moved or duplicated?\n+- What exact reference-migration plan is required for READMEs, catalogs, playbooks, and advisor corpus artifacts?\n+- Whether fallback-router should be wired into real model fallback.\n+\n+## Ruled Out\n+- A pure `mv deep-loop-runtime deep-loop-workflows/runtime` without precomputed path rewrite is ruled out: executable YAML, command contracts, doctor routes, agent prompts, advisor scoring, and system-spec-kit tests all carry concrete old paths.\n+\n+## Dead Ends\n+- Relying on command contract generation alone to fix references is insufficient; contracts are generated outputs, but the source YAML, command markdown, advisor source, and test config also embed paths and must be updated first [SOURCE: .opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1-80].\n+\n+## Edge Cases\n+- Ambiguous input: \"reference migration\" overlaps with \"path-coupling repair\"; this iteration classified executable and verification references as path-coupling, leaving prose docs/catalogs/playbooks for a later reference-migration pass.\n+- Contradictory evidence: None found; sources consistently show both roots are currently live.\n+- Missing dependencies: No code graph MCP was used; direct grep/read gave enough evidence.\n+- Partial success: The coupling map is broad but not exhaustive at line-by-line scale; it identifies classes that need automated rewrite and validation.\n+\n+## Sources Consulted\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:160`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:229-243`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:616`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:819-859`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:1017-1039`\n+- `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1-80`\n+- `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110`\n+- `.opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:95-165`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:15-22`\n+- `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json:7-18`\n+- `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:158-170`\n+\n+## Assessment\n+- New information ratio: 0.74\n+- Novelty justification: This pass added a concrete migration surface taxonomy across command execution, generated contracts, doctor, agents, advisor, system-spec-kit, and runtime docs.\n+- Questions addressed: path coupling; reference migration precursor; system-spec-kit interaction.\n+- Questions answered: path coupling answered at class level with representative source anchors.\n+- Confidence: High for the listed migration classes; medium for total occurrence count because the repo contains many catalog/playbook references intentionally left for iteration 4.\n+\n+## Reflection\n+- What worked and why: Searching exact old root names across scoped surfaces quickly exposed executable couplings.\n+- What did not work and why: Global grep results included generated/corpus artifacts; classifying by runtime impact was necessary to avoid false priority.\n+- What I would do differently: Separate executable path rewrites from documentation/corpus rewrite in the final migration plan.\n+\n+## Recommended Next Focus\n+System-spec-kit tooling borrow: identify which current shared pieces (`resolveArtifactRoot`, spec validation, memory/context save, resource-map extraction, optimizer/test discovery) should remain external contracts versus be moved, wrapped, or duplicated under the merged `system-deep-loop` root.\n*** Add File: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deltas/iter-002.jsonl\n+{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling inventory\",\"focusTrack\":\"migration\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.74,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass added a concrete migration surface taxonomy across command execution, generated contracts, doctor, agents, advisor, system-spec-kit, and runtime docs.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which bidirectional path couplings between deep-loop-workflows, deep-loop-runtime, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Path-coupling repair must include command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agents, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs.\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Directory move without precomputed rewrite inventory\",\"reason\":\"Executable YAML, generated contracts, doctor routes, agents, advisor, and test config contain concrete old paths.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77; .opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110; .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206\"}],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1-80\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110\",\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advi