aving detailed migration inventory for later.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Does the proposed system-deep-loop structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Structural layout should preserve workflows as public hub/mode packets and runtime as internal backend under a single system-deep-loop root.\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Flatten runtime and workflow packets into one directory\",\"reason\":\"Contradicts hub logic-free and runtime backend-only contracts.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:37-39; .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30\"}],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Glob\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:72-85\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json:1-17\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:819-859\"],\"graphEvents\":[{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"q-structural-layout\",\"kind\":\"QUESTION\",\"label\":\"Structural layout preserves ownership seams\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"f-001-runtime-internal\",\"kind\":\"FINDING\",\"label\":\"Runtime remains internal backend under merged system\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"src-workflows-skill-12\",\"kind\":\"SOURCE\",\"label\":\"deep-loop-workflows hub contract\"},{\"type\":\"node\",\"id\":\"src-runtime-readme-23\",\"kind\":\"SOURCE\",\"label\":\"deep-loop-runtime README commandless backend contract\"},{\"type\":\"edge\",\"id\":\"... (line truncated to 2000 chars)\n{\"type\":\"iteration\",\"run\":2,\"iteration\":2,\"mode\":\"research\",\"target_agent\":\"deep-research\",\"agent_definition_loaded\":true,\"resolved_route\":\"Resolved route: mode=research target_agent=deep-research\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Bidirectional path-coupling inventory\",\"focusTrack\":\"migration\",\"findingsCount\":7,\"newInfoRatio\":0.74,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass added a concrete migration surface taxonomy across command execution, generated contracts, doctor, agents, advisor, system-spec-kit, and runtime docs.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Which bidirectional path couplings between deep-loop-workflows, deep-loop-runtime, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Path-coupling repair must include command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agents, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs.\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Directory move without precomputed rewrite inventory\",\"reason\":\"Executable YAML, generated contracts, doctor routes, agents, advisor, and test config contain concrete old paths.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77; .opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110; .opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206\"}],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77\",\".opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:1-80\",\".opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110\",\".opencode/agents/orchestrate.md:180-206\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587\",\".opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/aliases.ts:95-165\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts:15-22\",\".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/optimizer/optimizer-manifest.json:7-18\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:158-170\"],\"graphEvents\":[... (line truncated to 2000 chars)","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":4,"totalLines":4,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-state.jsonl","time":{"start":1783487088753,"end":1783487088761}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02edf65a83ea06b1016a4dda70ab9c8191bef80a9fb83b47ef"}},"id":"prt_f401d484c001JzRA51bUAHU9nk","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401cf598001eQINGmkGV9v1h0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487088853,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_cizT3ZnSi6Wm7zLYnVDK8vLk","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":140},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n11: - [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n12: - [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n13: - [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n14: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n20: - Do not implement or move files.\n21: - Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n22: - Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: - At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n28: - Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n29: - The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: - Structural layout: preserve `deep-loop-workflows` as public hub/mode packets and `deep-loop-runtime` as internal backend under a merged `system-deep-loop` root; do not flatten them (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n36: - Path coupling: rewrite command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agent prompt contracts, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs atomically with the move (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587`).\n37: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n42: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n43: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n44: - Contract-first structural read: hub/runtime READMEs and SKILL contracts exposed the ownership seam before path inventory work (iteration 1).\n45: - Exact old-root greps across scoped surfaces separated executable migration targets from lower-priority prose references (iteration 2).\n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n51: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n52: - Broad markdown globbing across `deep-loop-workflows` was noisy because catalogs/playbooks dominate the tree; targeted grep/read is needed next (iteration 1).\n53: - Generated compiled contracts are not authoritative enough to repair references on their own; source YAML/advisor/test files must rewrite first, then contracts regenerate (iteration 2).\n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n60: None yet.\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n66: ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n67: - Flattening runtime and workflow packets into one directory: contradicts the logic-free hub and backend-only runtime contracts (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:37-39`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n68: - Moving directories first and relying on generated contracts to catch up: generated contracts are outputs, while source YAML, advisor code, agents, and test configs carry old paths (iteration 2).\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n74: ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n75: - Which system-spec-kit tooling should remain borrowed/external instead of moving into `system-deep-loop`?\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n81: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n82: System-spec-kit tooling borrow: identify which current shared pieces (`resolveArtifactRoot`, spec validation, memory/context save, resource-map extraction, optimizer/test discovery) should remain external contracts versus be moved, wrapped, or duplicated under the merged `system-deep-loop` root.\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n84: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n89: - Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n90: - Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n91: - `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n92: \n93: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n94: - Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n95: - Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n96: - Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n101: - Max iterations: 10\n102: - Min iterations: 3\n103: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n104: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n105: - Progressive synthesis: true\n106: - Current generation: 1\n107: - Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.\n- Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n- Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n- At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n- Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n- The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- Structural layout: preserve `deep-loop-workflows` as public hub/mode packets and `deep-loop-runtime` as internal backend under a merged `system-deep-loop` root; do not flatten them (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n- Path coupling: rewrite command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agent prompt contracts, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs atomically with the move (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587`).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n- Contract-first structural read: hub/runtime READMEs and SKILL contracts exposed the ownership seam before path inventory work (iteration 1).\n- Exact old-root greps across scoped surfaces separated executable migration targets from lower-priority prose references (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n- Broad markdown globbing across `deep-loop-workflows` was noisy because catalogs/playbooks dominate the tree; targeted grep/read is needed next (iteration 1).\n- Generated compiled contracts are not authoritative enough to repair references on their own; source YAML/advisor/test files must rewrite first, then contracts regenerate (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Flattening runtime and workflow packets into one directory: contradicts the logic-free hub and backend-only runtime contracts (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:37-39`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n- Moving directories first and relying on generated contracts to catch up: generated contracts are outputs, while source YAML, advisor code, agents, and test configs carry old paths (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- Which system-spec-kit tooling should remain borrowed/external instead of moving into `system-deep-loop`?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nSystem-spec-kit tooling borrow: identify which current shared pieces (`resolveArtifactRoot`, spec validation, memory/context save, resource-map extraction, optimizer/test discovery) should remain external contracts versus be moved, wrapped, or duplicated under the merged `system-deep-loop` root.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n- Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n- `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n- Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n- Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Min iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":107,"totalLines":107,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487088849,"end":1783487088853}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02edf65a83ea06b1016a4dda70abac8191949ba61fa1f749d2"}},"id":"prt_f401d4896001ct911kvKE75gGR","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401cf598001eQINGmkGV9v1h0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487089027,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_NTNJ56jjrviUDQHJUxU7HuhW","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs","offset":1,"limit":800},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Artifact-Root Resolver (shared backend seam)                            ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ Canonical import point for the artifact-topology contract consumed by    ║\n5: // ║ every graph-backed deep-loop reducer (research, review, context). The    ║\n6: // ║ single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; the runtime  ║\n7: // ║ owns the seam so deep-loop consumers depend on the backend rather than   ║\n8: // ║ reaching across into another skill. Re-export keeps the resolver a       ║\n9: // ║ single source of truth (no second copy to drift).                        ║\n10: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n11: \n12: 'use strict';\n13: \n14: const path = require('node:path');\n15: \n16: // resolveArtifactRoot, allocateShortSubfolder, normalizeSpecFolderReference.\n17: module.exports = require(\n18:   path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'shared', 'review-research-paths.cjs'),\n19: );\n\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Artifact-Root Resolver (shared backend seam)                            ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Canonical import point for the artifact-topology contract consumed by    ║\n// ║ every graph-backed deep-loop reducer (research, review, context). The    ║\n// ║ single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; the runtime  ║\n// ║ owns the seam so deep-loop consumers depend on the backend rather than   ║\n// ║ reaching across into another skill. Re-export keeps the resolver a       ║\n// ║ single source of truth (no second copy to drift).                        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\n// resolveArtifactRoot, allocateShortSubfolder, normalizeSpecFolderReference.\nmodule.exports = require(\n  path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'shared', 'review-research-paths.cjs'),\n);","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Artifact-Root Resolver (shared backend seam)                            ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Canonical import point for the artifact-topology contract consumed by    ║\n// ║ every graph-backed deep-loop reducer (research, review, context). The    ║\n// ║ single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; the runtime  ║\n// ║ owns the seam so deep-loop consumers depend on the backend rather than   ║\n// ║ reaching across into another skill. Re-export keeps the resolver a       ║\n// ║ single source of truth (no second copy to drift).                        ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\n// resolveArtifactRoot, allocateShortSubfolder, normalizeSpecFolderReference.\nmodule.exports = require(\n  path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'shared', 'review-research-paths.cjs'),\n);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":19,"totalLines":19,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs","time":{"start":1783487089022,"end":1783487089025}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02edf65a83ea06b1016a4dda70abb48191b72149de6dcf2046"}},"id":"prt_f401d48d2001QlKoHLO1zTD3dS","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401cf598001eQINGmkGV9v1h0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487089056,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_41OQbqqBA9tCTDrytuh3GdVR","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Review Research Paths                                                    ║\n3: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n4: \n5: 'use strict';\n6: \n7: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n8: // 1. IMPORTS\n9: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n10: \n11: const fs = require('node:fs');\n12: const path = require('node:path');\n13: \n14: const MODE_CONFIG_FILE = {\n15:   research: 'deep-research-config.json',\n16:   review: 'deep-review-config.json',\n17: };\n18: \n19: const MODE_STATE_FILE = {\n20:   research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n21:   review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n22: };\n23: \n24: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n25: // 2. CORE LOGIC\n26: // ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n27: \n28: /**\n29:  * Allocate the next artifact subfolder name under an artifact root directory\n30:  * using the {phaseSlug}-pt-{NN} naming convention.\n31:  *\n32:  * The phase slug is the FULL first-segment folder name under the spec tree\n33:  * root (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\").  NN is a two-digit zero-padded counter:\n34:  * 1 + the number of existing pt-folders whose slug prefix matches the requested\n35:  * phase, so repeated calls produce sequential names without any stored counter.\n36:  *\n37:  * @param {string} rootDir   - Absolute path to the artifact root (research/ or review/)\n38:  * @param {string} phaseSlug - Full phase folder name (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\")\n39:  * @returns {string} Subfolder name, e.g. \"019-system-hardening-pt-03\"\n40:  */\n41: function allocateShortSubfolder(rootDir, phaseSlug) {\n42:   let existingCount = 0;\n43: \n44:   if (fs.existsSync(rootDir)) {\n45:     const prefix = `${phaseSlug}-pt-`;\n46:     existingCount = fs.readdirSync(rootDir).filter(\n47:       (entry) => entry.startsWith(prefix),\n48:     ).length;\n49:   }\n50: \n51:   const nn = String(existingCount + 1).padStart(2, '0');\n52:   return `${phaseSlug}-pt-${nn}`;\n53: }\n54: \n55: function normalizeSpecFolderReference(specFolder) {\n56:   if (!specFolder) {\n57:     return null;\n58:   }\n59: \n60:   const normalized = String(specFolder)\n61:     .trim()\n62:     .replace(/\\\\/g, '/')\n63:     .replace(/\\/+$/g, '');\n64: \n65:   if (!normalized) {\n66:     return null;\n67:   }\n68: \n69:   const opencodeSpecsMarker = '/.opencode/specs/';\n70:   const specsMarker = '/specs/';\n71:   const opencodeIndex = normalized.lastIndexOf(opencodeSpecsMarker);\n72:   if (opencodeIndex !== -1) {\n73:     return normalized.slice(opencodeIndex + opencodeSpecsMarker.length);\n74:   }\n75: \n76:   const specsIndex = normalized.lastIndexOf(specsMarker);\n77:   if (specsIndex !== -1) {\n78:     return normalized.slice(specsIndex + specsMarker.length);\n79:   }\n80: \n81:   return normalized\n82:     .replace(/^\\.\\/+/, '')\n83:     .replace(/^\\.opencode\\/specs\\//, '')\n84:     .replace(/^specs\\//, '');\n85: }\n86: \n87: function findAncestorSpecFolder(specFolder) {\n88:   let current = path.resolve(specFolder);\n89: \n90:   while (true) {\n91:     const parent = path.dirname(current);\n92: \n93:     if (parent === current || path.basename(parent) === 'specs') {\n94:       return null;\n95:     }\n96: \n97:     if (fs.existsSync(path.join(parent, 'spec.md'))) {\n98:       return parent;\n99:     }\n100: \n101:     current = parent;\n102:   }\n103: }\n104: \n105: function readPacketSpecFolder(packetDir, mode) {\n106:   const configPath = path.join(packetDir, MODE_CONFIG_FILE[mode]);\n107:   if (fs.existsSync(configPath)) {\n108:     try {\n109:       const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(configPath, 'utf8'));\n110:       return normalizeSpecFolderReference(config.specFolder);\n111:     } catch (_error) {\n112:       // Fall through to state log probing.\n113:     }\n114:   }\n115: \n116:   const stateLogPath = path.join(packetDir, MODE_STATE_FILE[mode]);\n117:   if (!fs.existsSync(stateLogPath)) {\n118:     return null;\n119:   }\n120: \n121:   try {\n122:     const lines = fs.readFileSync(stateLogPath, 'utf8').split(/\\r?\\n/);\n123:     for (const line of lines) {\n124:       if (!line.trim()) {\n125:         continue;\n126:       }\n127:       const parsed = JSON.parse(line);\n128:       return normalizeSpecFolderReference(parsed.specFolder);\n129:     }\n130:   } catch (_error) {\n131:     return null;\n132:   }\n133: \n134:   return null;\n135: }\n136: \n137: function listPacketDirectories(rootDir) {\n138:   if (!fs.existsSync(rootDir)) {\n139:     return [];\n140:   }\n141: \n142:   return fs.readdirSync(rootDir, { withFileTypes: true })\n143:     .filter((entry) => entry.isDirectory() && /-pt-\\d+$/.test(entry.name))\n144:     .map((entry) => entry.name)\n145:     .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }));\n146: }\n147: \n148: function findExistingPacket(rootDir, specFolder, mode) {\n149:   const targetSpecFolder = normalizeSpecFolderReference(specFolder);\n150: \n151:   if (!targetSpecFolder) {\n152:     return null;\n153:   }\n154: \n155:   const matches = [];\n156:   for (const packetName of listPacketDirectories(rootDir)) {\n157:     const packetDir = path.join(rootDir, packetName);\n158:     if (readPacketSpecFolder(packetDir, mode) === targetSpecFolder) {\n159:       matches.push(packetName);\n160:     }\n161:   }\n162: \n163:   return matches.at(-1) || null;\n164: }\n165: \n166: /**\n167:  * Resolve the canonical artifact directory for review or research output.\n168:  *\n169:  * Conventions (post-028 contract fix):\n170:  *   - Root specs ALWAYS use flat: {spec_folder}/{mode}/\n171:  *   - Child phases use FLAT-FIRST:\n172:  *       (a) First run with empty {mode}/ directory → flat (subfolder=null)\n173:  *       (b) Continuation when flat artifact's config matches current target → reuse flat\n174:  *       (c) Existing pt-NN packet matches current target → reuse pt-NN\n175:  *       (d) Prior content exists for non-matching target → allocate pt-NN\n176:  *\n177:  * Subfolder naming convention (when pt-NN allocation kicks in): {phaseSlug}-pt-{NN}\n178:  *   - phaseSlug: the FULL immediate child phase segment under the spec tree\n179:  *     root (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\")\n180:  *   - NN: sequential two-digit counter scoped to that phase within the\n181:  *     artifact root directory; allocated by counting existing same-prefix\n182:  *     entries at call time\n183:  *\n184:  * Example:\n185:  *   - root spec run → {spec_folder}/research/\n186:  *   - child phase first run → {spec_folder}/research/   (flat, no pt-NN wrapper)\n187:  *   - child phase second run with prior content for different target → {spec_folder}/research/{phaseSlug}-pt-NN/\n188:  *   - child phase same-target continuation → reuses prior flat or pt-NN\n189:  *\n190:  * @param {string} specFolder - Absolute or relative path to the target spec folder\n191:  * @param {'review'|'research'|'context'} [mode='review'] - Which artifact type to resolve\n192:  *\n193:  * @returns {{\n194:  *   rootDir: string,\n195:  *   subfolder: string|null,\n196:  *   artifactDir: string,\n197:  *   artifactArchiveRoot: string\n198:  * }} Resolved packet root plus canonical packet/archive directories\n199:  */\n200: function resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, mode = 'review') {\n201:   // Workflow write-authority: reject specFolder values that contain\n202:   // shell metacharacters or quote characters. The YAML workflow interpolates\n203:   // {spec_folder} into a `node -e` shell command; without this guard, a\n204:   // malicious specFolder containing single-quotes / semicolons / backticks /\n205:   // $ / | / & / < / > could break out of the shell-quoted argument and\n206:   // execute arbitrary code in the Node process or shell.\n207:   if (typeof specFolder !== 'string' || specFolder.length === 0) {\n208:     throw new Error(`resolveArtifactRoot: specFolder must be a non-empty string`);\n209:   }\n210:   if (/['\"`$;|&<>\\\\]/.test(specFolder)) {\n211:     throw new Error(\n212:       `resolveArtifactRoot: specFolder contains forbidden shell metacharacter(s); refusing to proceed`,\n213:     );\n214:   }\n215: \n216:   const resolved = path.resolve(specFolder);\n217:   const rootDir = path.join(resolved, mode);\n218:   const artifactArchiveRoot = path.join(resolved, `${mode}_archive`);\n219:   const ancestorSpecFolder = findAncestorSpecFolder(resolved);\n220: \n221:   // ROOT spec: always flat\n222:   if (!ancestorSpecFolder) {\n223:     return {\n224:       rootDir,\n225:       subfolder: null,\n226:       artifactDir: rootDir,\n227:       artifactArchiveRoot,\n228:     };\n229:   }\n230: \n231:   // CHILD phase: prefer existing pt-NN packet for current target if any\n232:   const existingPacket = findExistingPacket(rootDir, resolved, mode);\n233:   if (existingPacket) {\n234:     return {\n235:       rootDir,\n236:       subfolder: existingPacket,\n237:       artifactDir: path.join(rootDir, existingPacket),\n238:       artifactArchiveRoot: path.join(artifactArchiveRoot, existingPacket),\n239:     };\n240:   }\n241: \n242:   // CHILD phase: check for flat artifact at rootDir\n243:   const targetSpecFolder = normalizeSpecFolderReference(resolved);\n244:   const flatConfigPath = path.join(rootDir, MODE_CONFIG_FILE[mode]);\n245:   const flatStateLogPath = path.join(rootDir, MODE_STATE_FILE[mode]);\n246:   const hasFlatArtifact = fs.existsSync(flatConfigPath) || fs.existsSync(flatStateLogPath);\n247: \n248:   if (hasFlatArtifact) {\n249:     const flatSpecFolder = readPacketSpecFolder(rootDir, mode);\n250:     if (flatSpecFolder === null || flatSpecFolder === targetSpecFolder) {\n251:       // Flat artifact matches current target (or its config is unreadable but rootDir is owned by this target's path) → reuse flat\n252:       return {\n253:         rootDir,\n254:         subfolder: null,\n255:         artifactDir: rootDir,\n256:         artifactArchiveRoot,\n257:       };\n258:     }\n259:     // Flat artifact is for a different target — fall through to allocate pt-NN\n260:   }\n261: \n262:   const ptFolders = listPacketDirectories(rootDir);\n263:   const hasPtFolders = ptFolders.length > 0;\n264: \n265:   // CHILD phase first run: empty rootDir → flat\n266:   if (!hasFlatArtifact && !hasPtFolders) {\n267:     return {\n268:       rootDir,\n269:       subfolder: null,\n270:       artifactDir: rootDir,\n271:       artifactArchiveRoot,\n272:     };\n273:   }\n274: \n275:   // CHILD phase: prior content exists (flat for different target, or pt-NN folders)\n276:   // and no matching packet for current target → allocate next pt-NN\n277:   const subfolder = allocateShortSubfolder(rootDir, path.basename(resolved));\n278:   return {\n279:     rootDir,\n280:     subfolder,\n281:     artifactDir: path.join(rootDir, subfolder),\n282:     artifactArchiveRoot: path.join(artifactArchiveRoot, subfolder),\n283:   };\n284: }\n285: \n286: module.exports = {\n287:   resolveArtifactRoot,\n288:   allocateShortSubfolder,\n289:   normalizeSpecFolderReference,\n290: };\n\n(End of file - total 290 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Review Research Paths                                                    ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst MODE_CONFIG_FILE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-config.json',\n  review: 'deep-review-config.json',\n};\n\nconst MODE_STATE_FILE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Review Research Paths                                                    ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 1. IMPORTS\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst fs = require('node:fs');\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\nconst MODE_CONFIG_FILE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-config.json',\n  review: 'deep-review-config.json',\n};\n\nconst MODE_STATE_FILE = {\n  research: 'deep-research-state.jsonl',\n  review: 'deep-review-state.jsonl',\n};\n\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n// 2. CORE LOGIC\n// ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\n/**\n * Allocate the next artifact subfolder name under an artifact root directory\n * using the {phaseSlug}-pt-{NN} naming convention.\n *\n * The phase slug is the FULL first-segment folder name under the spec tree\n * root (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\").  NN is a two-digit zero-padded counter:\n * 1 + the number of existing pt-folders whose slug prefix matches the requested\n * phase, so repeated calls produce sequential names without any stored counter.\n *\n * @param {string} rootDir   - Absolute path to the artifact root (research/ or review/)\n * @param {string} phaseSlug - Full phase folder name (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\")\n * @returns {string} Subfolder name, e.g. \"019-system-hardening-pt-03\"\n */\nfunction allocateShortSubfolder(rootDir, phaseSlug) {\n  let existingCount = 0;\n\n  if (fs.existsSync(rootDir)) {\n    const prefix = `${phaseSlug}-pt-`;\n    existingCount = fs.readdirSync(rootDir).filter(\n      (entry) => entry.startsWith(prefix),\n    ).length;\n  }\n\n  const nn = String(existingCount + 1).padStart(2, '0');\n  return `${phaseSlug}-pt-${nn}`;\n}\n\nfunction normalizeSpecFolderReference(specFolder) {\n  if (!specFolder) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const normalized = String(specFolder)\n    .trim()\n    .replace(/\\\\/g, '/')\n    .replace(/\\/+$/g, '');\n\n  if (!normalized) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const opencodeSpecsMarker = '/.opencode/specs/';\n  const specsMarker = '/specs/';\n  const opencodeIndex = normalized.lastIndexOf(opencodeSpecsMarker);\n  if (opencodeIndex !== -1) {\n    return normalized.slice(opencodeIndex + opencodeSpecsMarker.length);\n  }\n\n  const specsIndex = normalized.lastIndexOf(specsMarker);\n  if (specsIndex !== -1) {\n    return normalized.slice(specsIndex + specsMarker.length);\n  }\n\n  return normalized\n    .replace(/^\\.\\/+/, '')\n    .replace(/^\\.opencode\\/specs\\//, '')\n    .replace(/^specs\\//, '');\n}\n\nfunction findAncestorSpecFolder(specFolder) {\n  let current = path.resolve(specFolder);\n\n  while (true) {\n    const parent = path.dirname(current);\n\n    if (parent === current || path.basename(parent) === 'specs') {\n      return null;\n    }\n\n    if (fs.existsSync(path.join(parent, 'spec.md'))) {\n      return parent;\n    }\n\n    current = parent;\n  }\n}\n\nfunction readPacketSpecFolder(packetDir, mode) {\n  const configPath = path.join(packetDir, MODE_CONFIG_FILE[mode]);\n  if (fs.existsSync(configPath)) {\n    try {\n      const config = JSON.parse(fs.readFileSync(configPath, 'utf8'));\n      return normalizeSpecFolderReference(config.specFolder);\n    } catch (_error) {\n      // Fall through to state log probing.\n    }\n  }\n\n  const stateLogPath = path.join(packetDir, MODE_STATE_FILE[mode]);\n  if (!fs.existsSync(stateLogPath)) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  try {\n    const lines = fs.readFileSync(stateLogPath, 'utf8').split(/\\r?\\n/);\n    for (const line of lines) {\n      if (!line.trim()) {\n        continue;\n      }\n      const parsed = JSON.parse(line);\n      return normalizeSpecFolderReference(parsed.specFolder);\n    }\n  } catch (_error) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  return null;\n}\n\nfunction listPacketDirectories(rootDir) {\n  if (!fs.existsSync(rootDir)) {\n    return [];\n  }\n\n  return fs.readdirSync(rootDir, { withFileTypes: true })\n    .filter((entry) => entry.isDirectory() && /-pt-\\d+$/.test(entry.name))\n    .map((entry) => entry.name)\n    .sort((left, right) => left.localeCompare(right, undefined, { numeric: true }));\n}\n\nfunction findExistingPacket(rootDir, specFolder, mode) {\n  const targetSpecFolder = normalizeSpecFolderReference(specFolder);\n\n  if (!targetSpecFolder) {\n    return null;\n  }\n\n  const matches = [];\n  for (const packetName of listPacketDirectories(rootDir)) {\n    const packetDir = path.join(rootDir, packetName);\n    if (readPacketSpecFolder(packetDir, mode) === targetSpecFolder) {\n      matches.push(packetName);\n    }\n  }\n\n  return matches.at(-1) || null;\n}\n\n/**\n * Resolve the canonical artifact directory for review or research output.\n *\n * Conventions (post-028 contract fix):\n *   - Root specs ALWAYS use flat: {spec_folder}/{mode}/\n *   - Child phases use FLAT-FIRST:\n *       (a) First run with empty {mode}/ directory → flat (subfolder=null)\n *       (b) Continuation when flat artifact's config matches current target → reuse flat\n *       (c) Existing pt-NN packet matches current target → reuse pt-NN\n *       (d) Prior content exists for non-matching target → allocate pt-NN\n *\n * Subfolder naming convention (when pt-NN allocation kicks in): {phaseSlug}-pt-{NN}\n *   - phaseSlug: the FULL immediate child phase segment under the spec tree\n *     root (e.g. \"019-system-hardening\")\n *   - NN: sequential two-digit counter scoped to that phase within the\n *     artifact root directory; allocated by counting existing same-prefix\n *     entries at call time\n *\n * Example:\n *   - root spec run → {spec_folder}/research/\n *   - child phase first run → {spec_folder}/research/   (flat, no pt-NN wrapper)\n *   - child phase second run with prior content for different target → {spec_folder}/research/{phaseSlug}-pt-NN/\n *   - child phase same-target continuation → reuses prior flat or pt-NN\n *\n * @param {string} specFolder - Absolute or relative path to the target spec folder\n * @param {'review'|'research'|'context'} [mode='review'] - Which artifact type to resolve\n *\n * @returns {{\n *   rootDir: string,\n *   subfolder: string|null,\n *   artifactDir: string,\n *   artifactArchiveRoot: string\n * }} Resolved packet root plus canonical packet/archive directories\n */\nfunction resolveArtifactRoot(specFolder, mode = 'review') {\n  // Workflow write-authority: reject specFolder values that contain\n  // shell metacharacters or quote characters. The YAML workflow interpolates\n  // {spec_folder} into a `node -e` shell command; without this guard, a\n  // malicious specFolder containing single-quotes / semicolons / backticks /\n  // $ / | / & / < / > could break out of the shell-quoted argument and\n  // execute arbitrary code in the Node process or shell.\n  if (typeof specFolder !== 'string' || specFolder.length === 0) {\n    throw new Error(`resolveArtifactRoot: specFolder must be a non-empty string`);\n  }\n  if (/['\"`$;|&<>\\\\]/.test(specFolder)) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `resolveArtifactRoot: specFolder contains forbidden shell metacharacter(s); refusing to proceed`,\n    );\n  }\n\n  const resolved = path.resolve(specFolder);\n  const rootDir = path.join(resolved, mode);\n  const artifactArchiveRoot = path.join(resolved, `${mode}_archive`);\n  const ancestorSpecFolder = findAncestorSpecFolder(resolved);\n\n  // ROOT spec: always flat\n  if (!ancestorSpecFolder) {\n    return {\n      rootDir,\n      subfolder: null,\n      artifactDir: rootDir,\n      artifactArchiveRoot,\n    };\n  }\n\n  // CHILD phase: prefer existing pt-NN packet for current target if any\n  const existingPacket = findExistingPacket(rootDir, resolved, mode);\n  if (existingPacket) {\n    return {\n      rootDir,\n      subfolder: existingPacket,\n      artifactDir: path.join(rootDir, existingPacket),\n      artifactArchiveRoot: path.join(artifactArchiveRoot, existingPacket),\n    };\n  }\n\n  // CHILD phase: check for flat artifact at rootDir\n  const targetSpecFolder = normalizeSpecFolderReference(resolved);\n  const flatConfigPath = path.join(rootDir, MODE_CONFIG_FILE[mode]);\n  const flatStateLogPath = path.join(rootDir, MODE_STATE_FILE[mode]);\n  const hasFlatArtifact = fs.existsSync(flatConfigPath) || fs.existsSync(flatStateLogPath);\n\n  if (hasFlatArtifact) {\n    const flatSpecFolder = readPacketSpecFolder(rootDir, mode);\n    if (flatSpecFolder === null || flatSpecFolder === targetSpecFolder) {\n      // Flat artifact matches current target (or its config is unreadable but rootDir is owned by this target's path) → reuse flat\n      return {\n        rootDir,\n        subfolder: null,\n        artifactDir: rootDir,\n        artifactArchiveRoot,\n      };\n    }\n    // Flat artifact is for a different target — fall through to allocate pt-NN\n  }\n\n  const ptFolders = listPacketDirectories(rootDir);\n  const hasPtFolders = ptFolders.length > 0;\n\n  // CHILD phase first run: empty rootDir → flat\n  if (!hasFlatArtifact && !hasPtFolders) {\n    return {\n      rootDir,\n      subfolder: null,\n      artifactDir: rootDir,\n      artifactArchiveRoot,\n    };\n  }\n\n  // CHILD phase: prior content exists (flat for different target, or pt-NN folders)\n  // and no matching packet for current target → allocate next pt-NN\n  const subfolder = allocateShortSubfolder(rootDir, path.basename(resolved));\n  return {\n    rootDir,\n    subfolder,\n    artifactDir: path.join(rootDir, subfolder),\n    artifactArchiveRoot: path.join(artifactArchiveRoot, subfolder),\n  };\n}\n\nmodule.exports = {\n  resolveArtifactRoot,\n  allocateShortSubfolder,\n  normalizeSpecFolderReference,\n};","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":290,"totalLines":290,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs","time":{"start":1783487089052,"end":1783487089054}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02edf65a83ea06b1016a4dda70abb881918bdf3dbe8788ce13"}},"id":"prt_f401d4982001SQ9U1S3qjSpBc4","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401cf598001eQINGmkGV9v1h0"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487089070,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_P7PzLgniDfBqKjwLnVkIoJtQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs","offset":1,"limit":1000},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n2: // ║ Resource-Map Synthesis Primitive (workflows-shared)                       ║\n3: // ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n4: // ║ Shared synthesis helper for the deep-loop workflow modes. emitResourceMap ║\n5: // ║ is workflow output rendering, NOT runtime backend plumbing, so it lives   ║\n6: // ║ here (a non-discoverable shared location) rather than in deep-loop-      ║\n7: // ║ runtime. The single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; ║\n8: // ║ this re-export is the seam research/review reducers consume so the       ║\n9: // ║ rendered markdown stays byte-identical to the original renderer.         ║\n10: // ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n11: \n12: 'use strict';\n13: \n14: const path = require('node:path');\n15: \n16: // emitResourceMap (and any sibling exports of the extractor).\n17: module.exports = require(\n18:   path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'scripts', 'resource-map', 'extract-from-evidence.cjs'),\n19: );\n\n(End of file - total 19 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Resource-Map Synthesis Primitive (workflows-shared)                       ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Shared synthesis helper for the deep-loop workflow modes. emitResourceMap ║\n// ║ is workflow output rendering, NOT runtime backend plumbing, so it lives   ║\n// ║ here (a non-discoverable shared location) rather than in deep-loop-      ║\n// ║ runtime. The single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; ║\n// ║ this re-export is the seam research/review reducers consume so the       ║\n// ║ rendered markdown stays byte-identical to the original renderer.         ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\n// emitResourceMap (and any sibling exports of the extractor).\nmodule.exports = require(\n  path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'scripts', 'resource-map', 'extract-from-evidence.cjs'),\n);","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs","text":"// ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗\n// ║ Resource-Map Synthesis Primitive (workflows-shared)                       ║\n// ╠══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╣\n// ║ Shared synthesis helper for the deep-loop workflow modes. emitResourceMap ║\n// ║ is workflow output rendering, NOT runtime backend plumbing, so it lives   ║\n// ║ here (a non-discoverable shared location) rather than in deep-loop-      ║\n// ║ runtime. The single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; ║\n// ║ this re-export is the seam research/review reducers consume so the       ║\n// ║ rendered markdown stays byte-identical to the original renderer.         ║\n// ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝\n\n'use strict';\n\nconst path = require('node:path');\n\n// emitResourceMap (and any sibling exports of the extractor).\nmodule.exports = require(\n  path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'scripts', 'resource-map', 'extract-from-evidence.cjs'),\n);","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":19,"totalLines":19,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/shared/synthesis/resource-map.cjs","time":{"start":1783487089065,"end":1783487089068}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_02edf65a83ea06b1016a4dda70abbc81918a10f6e975b55c40"}},"id":"prt_f401d499f001QsPtSsi1A5xnwx","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401cf598001eQINGmkGV9v1h0"}}
