{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487102773,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_1JIc2JDxwX9ksN6FrNMoLNQj","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1630,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1630:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1631:   # PHASE 4: SAVE\n1632:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1633:   phase_save:\n1634:     purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n1635:     steps:\n1636: \n1637:       step_compose_save_payload:\n1638:         action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n1639:         output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n1640:         requirements:\n1641:           - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n1642:           - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n1643:           - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n1644:         example_payload: |\n1645:           {\n1646:             \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n1647:             \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n1648:             \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n1649:             \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n1650:             \"exchanges\": [],\n1651:             \"toolCalls\": []\n1652:           }\n1653: \n1654:       step_generate_context:\n1655:         action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n1656:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n1657:         critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n1658: \n1659:       step_index_memory:\n1660:         action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n1661:         mcp_tool: memory_save\n1662:         invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n1663:         note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n1664: \n1665:       step_verify_save:\n1666:         action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n1667:         check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n1668:         on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n1669: \n1670:       step_release_lock:\n1671:         action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n1672:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n1673:         append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n1674: \n1675:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1676:   # COMPLETION\n1677:   # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n1678:   completion:\n1679:     message: |\n1680:       Deep research complete.\n1681:       Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n1682:       Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n1683: \n1684:       Artifacts:\n1685:         - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n1686:         - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n1687:         - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n1688:         - Memory context saved\n1689: \n1690:       STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n1691:     next_steps:\n1692:       - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n1693:       - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n1694:       - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n1695: \n1696: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1697: # ERROR RECOVERY\n1698: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1699: error_recovery:\n1700:   agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n1701:   state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n1702:   consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n1703:   memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n1704: \n1705: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1706: # RULES\n1707: # ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n1708: rules:\n1709:   ALWAYS:\n\n(Showing lines 1630-1709 of 1740. Use offset=1710 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # PHASE 4: SAVE\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  phase_save:\n    purpose: Preserve research context to memory system\n    steps:\n\n      step_compose_save_payload:\n        action: \"Compose the structured JSON payload consumed by generate-context.js\"\n        output: \"/tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json\"\n        requirements:\n          - \"Write this file before invoking generate-context.js; the loader fails closed if the explicit JSON file is absent.\"\n          - \"Include `specFolder`, a concise `sessionSummary`, curated `observations`, `recent_context`, `toolCalls`, and `exchanges` from the completed research loop.\"\n          - \"Use a session-scoped temp filename; do not use the retired shared `/tmp/save-context-data.json` path.\"\n        example_payload: |\n          {\n            \"specFolder\": \"{spec_folder}\",\n            \"sessionSummary\": \"Deep research completed; see research/research.md for synthesized findings.\",\n            \"observations\": [\"Summarize the final research conclusions and evidence.\"],\n            \"recent_context\": [\"Point to the generated research artifacts and next action.\"],\n            \"exchanges\": [],\n            \"toolCalls\": []\n          }\n\n      step_generate_context:\n        action: \"Route continuity content into the correct canonical spec document via generate-context.js\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js /tmp/save-context-data-<session-id>.json {spec_folder}\"\n        critical_rule: \"NEVER manually author files under retired memory/ paths (the runtime rejects them); use generate-context.js so the save routes into decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md\"\n\n      step_index_memory:\n        action: \"Index the routed canonical spec document with memory_save when immediate MCP visibility is required\"\n        mcp_tool: memory_save\n        invocation: 'memory_save({ filePath: \"[routed-canonical-spec-doc-path]\" })'\n        note: \"Use the actual canonical spec-doc path returned by generate-context.js (decision-record.md, implementation-summary.md, or handover.md); memory_index_scan remains the bulk fallback\"\n\n      step_verify_save:\n        action: \"Verify canonical save routed content into the correct spec document\"\n        check: \"Does {spec_folder}/implementation-summary.md, {spec_folder}/decision-record.md, or {spec_folder}/handover.md carry the new continuity update?\"\n        on_fail: \"Log warning but do not block completion\"\n\n      step_release_lock:\n        action: \"Release the single-writer lock after save, skip-save, or cancellation cleanup has resolved\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/loop-lock.cjs release --lock-path {state_paths.lock_file} --owner-pid {captured_owner_pid}\"\n        append_to_jsonl: '{\"type\":\"event\",\"event\":\"lock_released\",\"path\":\"{state_paths.lock_file}\",\"releasePhase\":\"save\",\"timestamp\":\"{ISO_8601_NOW}\"}'\n\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  # COMPLETION\n  # ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════\n  completion:\n    message: |\n      Deep research complete.\n      Iterations: {iteration_count} | Stop reason: {reason}\n      Questions answered: {answered_count}/{total_questions}\n\n      Artifacts:\n        - research/research.md (compiled from {iteration_count} iterations)\n        - {iteration_count} iteration files in research/\n        - State files: config.json, state.jsonl, strategy.md, deep-research-findings-registry.json, dashboard.md\n        - Memory context saved\n\n      STATUS=OK PATH={spec_folder}\n    next_steps:\n      - \"/speckit:plan [feature-description]\"\n      - \"/deep:research [new-topic] (for related deep research)\"\n      - \"/memory:save {spec_folder} (refresh canonical continuity before the next session)\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# ERROR RECOVERY\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nerror_recovery:\n  agent_dispatch_timeout: \"Retry once with reduced scope (fewer research actions). If second timeout, mark as 'timeout' and continue.\"\n  state_file_missing: \"If JSONL missing during loop, reconstruct from iteration files. If strategy missing, create minimal version.\"\n  consecutive_failures: \"After 3 consecutive errors, halt loop and enter synthesis with partial findings.\"\n  memory_save_failure: \"Preserve the research/ packet as backup. Log warning.\"\n\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n# RULES\n# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\nrules:\n  ALWAYS:","lineStart":1630,"lineEnd":1709,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783487102736,"end":1783487102765}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_051404d0ca0eb138016a4dda7ea1b08191bcb16a783fb82305"}},"id":"prt_f401d7f0e001jRKLrn1EZKGka9","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401d4e0b001hyLGjxSYZJysjh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487102780,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_j90GvsH2lYNTUvIo6AXYQPQ9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","offset":1321,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1321:       step_read_all_iterations:\n1322:         action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n1323:         read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n1324:         read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n1325: \n1326:       step_emit_resource_map:\n1327:         action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n1328:         command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n1329:         read:\n1330:           - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n1331:           - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n1332:         write:\n1333:           - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n1334:         guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n1335: \n1336:       step_compile_research:\n1337:         action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n1338:         instructions: |\n1339:           If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n1340:             1. Read current research/research.md\n1341:             2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n1342:             3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n1343:             4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n1344:             5. Add convergence report as appendix\n1345:             6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation\n\n(Showing lines 1321-1345 of 1740. Use offset=1346 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","text":"      step_read_all_iterations:\n        action: \"Read all iteration files and strategy\"\n        read_pattern: \"{state_paths.iteration_dir}/iteration-*.md\"\n        read_also: \"{state_paths.strategy}\"\n\n      step_emit_resource_map:\n        action: \"Emit {state_paths.resource_map_output} from converged research deltas unless config.resource_map.emit is false\"\n        command: \"node .opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/scripts/reduce-state.cjs {spec_folder} --emit-resource-map\"\n        read:\n          - \"{state_paths.config}\"\n          - \"{state_paths.delta_dir}/iter-*.jsonl\"\n        write:\n          - \"{state_paths.resource_map_output}\"\n        guarantee: \"Reducer skips cleanly when config.resource_map.emit == false and writes a deterministic resource-map when enabled.\"\n\n      step_compile_research:\n        action: \"Compile or finalize research/research.md\"\n        instructions: |\n          If research/research.md exists (progressive synthesis was active):\n            1. Read current research/research.md\n            2. Consolidate and deduplicate findings across all iterations\n            3. Fill any empty sections with findings from iteration files\n            4. Remove redundancy while preserving all unique findings\n            5. Add convergence report as appendix\n            6. If `resource_map_present` is true, cite `{spec_folder}/resource-map.md` in References; otherwise omit any placeholder map citation","lineStart":1321,"lineEnd":1345,"totalLines":1740,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml","time":{"start":1783487102732,"end":1783487102779}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_051404d0ca0eb138016a4dda7ea1ac8191a5202ce0e8a05294"}},"id":"prt_f401d7ee6001LdNRutxFElgVwe","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401d4e0b001hyLGjxSYZJysjh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487103012,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_6jqdn6bZNKXjCP3hsBzMpXyV","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md","offset":120,"limit":30},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n120: \n121: | Level       | When to Load               | Resources                    |\n122: | ----------- | -------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n123: | ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation     | Shared patterns + SKILL.md   |\n124: | CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match   | Intent-mapped references     |\n125: | ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request   | Deep-dive quality standards  |\n126: \n127: `references/workflows/quick_reference.md` is the primary first-touch command surface. Keep the compact `spec_kit` and `memory` command map there, including `/speckit:plan --intake-only` as the standalone intake entry, `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:complete` smart delegation notes, and the pointer from `/deep:research` to `../deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, and use this file only to point readers to it rather than duplicating the full matrix.\n128: \n129: ### Smart Router Pseudocode\n130: \n131: The authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling. Because this skill is an intent/domain router, Pattern 3 is adapted to extensible intent labels over discovered resources rather than keyed resource subdirectories.\n132: \n133: - Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n134: - Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards, de-duplicates with `seen`, and checks `inventory`.\n135: - Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - command and intent signals select domain labels and resource maps without forcing `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subtrees.\n136: - Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` asks for disambiguation and missing-resource cases return a \"no knowledge base\" notice.\n137: \n138: ```python\n139: from pathlib import Path\n140: \n141: SKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\n142: RESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\n143: DEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\"\n144: \n145: INTENT_SIGNALS = {\n146:     \"PLAN\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"plan\", \"design\", \"new spec\", \"level selection\", \"option b\"]},\n147:     \"RESEARCH\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"investigate\", \"explore\", \"analyze\", \"prior work\", \"evidence\"]},\n148:     \"IMPLEMENT\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"execute\", \"workflow\"]},\n149:     \"DEBUG\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"error\", \"not working\", \"failed\", \"debug\"]},\n\n(Showing lines 120-149 of 542. Use offset=150 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"\n| Level       | When to Load               | Resources                    |\n| ----------- | -------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation     | Shared patterns + SKILL.md   |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match   | Intent-mapped references     |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request   | Deep-dive quality standards  |\n\n`references/workflows/quick_reference.md` is the primary first-touch command surface. Keep the compact `spec_kit` and `memory` command map there, including `/speckit:plan --intake-only` as the standalone intake entry, `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:complete` smart delegation notes, and the pointer from `/deep:research` to `../deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, and use this file only to point readers to it rather than duplicating the full matrix.\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling. Because this skill is an intent/domain router, Pattern 3 is adapted to extensible intent labels over discovered resources rather than keyed resource subdirectories.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards, de-duplicates with `seen`, and checks `inventory`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - command and intent signals select domain labels and resource maps without forcing `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subtrees.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` asks for disambiguation and missing-resource cases return a \"no knowledge base\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md","text":"\n| Level       | When to Load               | Resources                    |\n| ----------- | -------------------------- | ---------------------------- |\n| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation     | Shared patterns + SKILL.md   |\n| CONDITIONAL | If intent signals match   | Intent-mapped references     |\n| ON_DEMAND   | Only on explicit request   | Deep-dive quality standards  |\n\n`references/workflows/quick_reference.md` is the primary first-touch command surface. Keep the compact `spec_kit` and `memory` command map there, including `/speckit:plan --intake-only` as the standalone intake entry, `/speckit:plan` and `/speckit:complete` smart delegation notes, and the pointer from `/deep:research` to `../deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md`, and use this file only to point readers to it rather than duplicating the full matrix.\n\n### Smart Router Pseudocode\n\nThe authoritative routing logic for scoped loading, weighted intent scoring, and ambiguity handling. Because this skill is an intent/domain router, Pattern 3 is adapted to extensible intent labels over discovered resources rather than keyed resource subdirectories.\n\n- Pattern 1: Runtime Discovery - `discover_markdown_resources()` recursively inventories `references/` and `assets/`.\n- Pattern 2: Existence-Check Before Load - `load_if_available()` guards, de-duplicates with `seen`, and checks `inventory`.\n- Pattern 3: Extensible Routing Key - command and intent signals select domain labels and resource maps without forcing `references/<key>/` or `assets/<key>/` subtrees.\n- Pattern 4: Multi-Tier Graceful Fallback - `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` asks for disambiguation and missing-resource cases return a \"no knowledge base\" notice.\n\n```python\nfrom pathlib import Path\n\nSKILL_ROOT = Path(__file__).resolve().parent\nRESOURCE_BASES = (SKILL_ROOT / \"references\", SKILL_ROOT / \"assets\")\nDEFAULT_RESOURCE = \"references/workflows/quick_reference.md\"\n\nINTENT_SIGNALS = {\n    \"PLAN\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"plan\", \"design\", \"new spec\", \"level selection\", \"option b\"]},\n    \"RESEARCH\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"investigate\", \"explore\", \"analyze\", \"prior work\", \"evidence\"]},\n    \"IMPLEMENT\": {\"weight\": 3, \"keywords\": [\"implement\", \"build\", \"execute\", \"workflow\"]},\n    \"DEBUG\": {\"weight\": 4, \"keywords\": [\"stuck\", \"error\", \"not working\", \"failed\", \"debug\"]},","lineStart":120,"lineEnd":149,"totalLines":542,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783487102952,"end":1783487103003}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_051404d0ca0eb138016a4dda7ea1bc8191ba34e55cdcf7ecd2"}},"id":"prt_f401d7f15001iJiC136hXOpxbJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401d4e0b001hyLGjxSYZJysjh"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487103012,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_tlzwCQ46OsHd9LrA2fzUgGtQ","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md","offset":525,"limit":25},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n525: | Upgrade level | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/upgrade-level.sh specs/007-feature/ --to 2` |\n526: | Completeness | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/calculate-completeness.sh specs/007-feature/` |\n527: | Worktree isolation | `.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh` creates a per-session git worktree with isolated `SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR`. Pair with `worktree-reaper.sh` for teardown and `worktree-guard.sh` for lock enforcement |\n528: | Session cleanup | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` (renamed from `claude-session-cleanup.sh` with a back-compat shim retained) resolves PIDs across claude/opencode/opencode runtimes |\n529: \n530: Canonical command lifecycle: `/speckit:plan --intake-only` establishes or repairs the packet when standalone intake is needed, `/deep:research` follows `../deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` when research needs bounded `spec.md` anchoring, and `/speckit:plan` or `/speckit:complete` continue from the same folder while reusing the shared intake contract (`.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/intake_contract.md`) only when the local `folder_state` still needs repair. When intake runs, the returned `start_state` is the canonical downstream field.\n531: \n532: **Remember**: This skill is the foundational documentation orchestrator. It enforces structure, template usage, context preservation, and workflow-required validation for all file modifications. Every conversation that modifies files MUST have a spec folder.\n533: \n534: ---\n535: \n536: ## 7. REFERENCES AND RELATED RESOURCES\n537: \n538: The router discovers reference, asset, and script docs dynamically. Start with `references/workflows/quick_reference.md`, `references/templates/template_guide.md`, `references/validation/validation_rules.md`, `references/memory/save_workflow.md`, then load task-specific resources from `references/`, templates from `assets/`, and automation from `scripts/` when present.\n539: \n540: Scripts: `scripts/spec/validate.sh`, `scripts/spec/create.sh`, `scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`, `scripts/spec/check-completion.sh`.\n541: \n542: Related skills: `sk-doc` for authored documentation quality, `sk-code` for code changes, `sk-git` for git handoff, and `deep-loop-workflows` for iterative research and audit (its `research` and `review` modes).\n\n(End of file - total 542 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| Upgrade level | `bash .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/upgrade-level.sh specs/007-feature/ --to 2` |\n| Completeness | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/spec/calculate-completeness.sh specs/007-feature/` |\n| Worktree isolation | `.opencode/bin/worktree-session.sh` creates a per-session git worktree with isolated `SPEC_KIT_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_CODE_GRAPH_DB_DIR` / `SPECKIT_IPC_SOCKET_DIR`. Pair with `worktree-reaper.sh` for teardown and `worktree-guard.sh` for lock enforcement |\n| Session cleanup | `.opencode/scripts/session-cleanup.sh` (renamed from `claude-session-cleanup.sh` with a back-compat shim retained) resolves PIDs across claude/opencode/opencode runtimes |\n\nCanonical command lifecycle: `/speckit:plan --intake-only` establishes or repairs the packet when standalone intake is needed, `/deep:research` follows `../deep-loop-workflows/deep-research/references/protocol/spec_check_protocol.md` when research needs bounded `spec.m