{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487103012,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_MKuQJcFp3VNLx852Na83U8pu","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md","offset":94,"limit":18},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n94: ## 6. SYSTEM-SPEC-KIT TEST DISCOVERY\n95: \n96: The runtime tests are discovered from the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config:\n97: \n98: ```text\n99: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts\n100:   '../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'\n101: ```\n102: \n103: Production imports resolve from this skill's own `node_modules` via bare specifiers — no reach-in to a sibling skill's installed packages:\n104: \n105: - `executor-config.ts` and `prompt-pack.ts` import `zod` (declared in this skill's `package.json`).\n106: - `coverage-graph-db.ts`, `coverage-graph-signals.ts`, and `council/council-graph-db.ts` import `better-sqlite3` (declared here; pinned to the same version `system-spec-kit` uses so the native binding stays ABI-compatible).\n107: - The `*.cjs` scripts boot the tsx loader through `require.resolve('tsx')`, which resolves from this skill's own `node_modules`.\n108: \n109: The dependency versions are kept in lockstep with `system-spec-kit` (see `package.json`), which is why graph metadata still lists `system-spec-kit` under `depends_on`. The standalone suite runs via `npm test` (local `vitest.config.ts`); the combined CI run still discovers these tests through the `system-spec-kit` MCP server config above.\n110: \n111: ---\n\n(Showing lines 94-111 of 203. Use offset=112 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"## 6. SYSTEM-SPEC-KIT TEST DISCOVERY\n\nThe runtime tests are discovered from the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config:\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts\n  '../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'\n```\n\nProduction imports resolve from this skill's own `node_modules` via bare specifiers — no reach-in to a sibling skill's installed packages:\n\n- `executor-config.ts` and `prompt-pack.ts` import `zod` (declared in this skill's `package.json`).\n- `coverage-graph-db.ts`, `coverage-graph-signals.ts`, and `council/council-graph-db.ts` import `better-sqlite3` (declared here; pinned to the same version `system-spec-kit` uses so the native binding stays ABI-compatible).\n- The `*.cjs` scripts boot the tsx loader through `require.resolve('tsx')`, which resolves from this skill's own `node_modules`.\n\nThe dependency versions are kept in lockstep with `system-spec-kit` (see `package.json`), which is why graph metadata still lists `system-spec-kit` under `depends_on`. The standalone suite runs via `npm test` (local `vitest.config.ts`); the combined CI run still discovers these tests through the `system-spec-kit` MCP server config above.\n\n---","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md","text":"## 6. SYSTEM-SPEC-KIT TEST DISCOVERY\n\nThe runtime tests are discovered from the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config:\n\n```text\n.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts\n  '../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'\n```\n\nProduction imports resolve from this skill's own `node_modules` via bare specifiers — no reach-in to a sibling skill's installed packages:\n\n- `executor-config.ts` and `prompt-pack.ts` import `zod` (declared in this skill's `package.json`).\n- `coverage-graph-db.ts`, `coverage-graph-signals.ts`, and `council/council-graph-db.ts` import `better-sqlite3` (declared here; pinned to the same version `system-spec-kit` uses so the native binding stays ABI-compatible).\n- The `*.cjs` scripts boot the tsx loader through `require.resolve('tsx')`, which resolves from this skill's own `node_modules`.\n\nThe dependency versions are kept in lockstep with `system-spec-kit` (see `package.json`), which is why graph metadata still lists `system-spec-kit` under `depends_on`. The standalone suite runs via `npm test` (local `vitest.config.ts`); the combined CI run still discovers these tests through the `system-spec-kit` MCP server config above.\n\n---","lineStart":94,"lineEnd":111,"totalLines":203,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md","time":{"start":1783487102995,"end":1783487103010}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_051404d0ca0eb138016a4dda7ea1cc8191ac8a018d7da13ffd"}},"id":"prt_f401d800f001zMTsCw3IgOClm8","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401d4e0b001hyLGjxSYZJysjh"}}
