{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487161343,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_o1qbce3Oqt3WIpmHhn5GCJ5M","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","offset":1,"limit":220},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n2: \n3: ## 1. TOPIC\n4: Validate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n5: \n6: ---\n7: \n8: <!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n9: ## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n10: - [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n11: - [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n12: - [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n13: - [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n14: - [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n15: <!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## 3. NON-GOALS\n20: - Do not implement or move files.\n21: - Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n22: - Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n23: \n24: ---\n25: \n26: ## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n27: - At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n28: - Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n29: - The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n30: \n31: ---\n32: \n33: <!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n34: ## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n35: - Structural layout: preserve `deep-loop-workflows` as public hub/mode packets and `deep-loop-runtime` as internal backend under a merged `system-deep-loop` root; do not flatten them (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n36: - Path coupling: rewrite command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agent prompt contracts, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs atomically with the move (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587`).\n37: <!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n38: \n39: ---\n40: \n41: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n42: <!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n43: ## 6. WHAT WORKED\n44: - Contract-first structural read: hub/runtime READMEs and SKILL contracts exposed the ownership seam before path inventory work (iteration 1).\n45: - Exact old-root greps across scoped surfaces separated executable migration targets from lower-priority prose references (iteration 2).\n46: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n47: \n48: ---\n49: \n50: <!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n51: ## 7. WHAT FAILED\n52: - Broad markdown globbing across `deep-loop-workflows` was noisy because catalogs/playbooks dominate the tree; targeted grep/read is needed next (iteration 1).\n53: - Generated compiled contracts are not authoritative enough to repair references on their own; source YAML/advisor/test files must rewrite first, then contracts regenerate (iteration 2).\n54: <!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n55: \n56: ---\n57: \n58: <!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n59: ## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\n60: None yet.\n61: <!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n62: \n63: ---\n64: \n65: <!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n66: ## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n67: - Flattening runtime and workflow packets into one directory: contradicts the logic-free hub and backend-only runtime contracts (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:37-39`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n68: - Moving directories first and relying on generated contracts to catch up: generated contracts are outputs, while source YAML, advisor code, agents, and test configs carry old paths (iteration 2).\n69: <!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n70: \n71: ---\n72: \n73: <!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n74: ## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n75: - Which system-spec-kit tooling should remain borrowed/external instead of moving into `system-deep-loop`?\n76: <!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n77: \n78: ---\n79: \n80: <!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n81: ## 11. NEXT FOCUS\n82: System-spec-kit tooling borrow: identify which current shared pieces (`resolveArtifactRoot`, spec validation, memory/context save, resource-map extraction, optimizer/test discovery) should remain external contracts versus be moved, wrapped, or duplicated under the merged `system-deep-loop` root.\n83: <!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n84: <!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n85: \n86: ---\n87: \n88: ## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n89: - Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n90: - Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n91: - `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n92: \n93: ### Bounded Context Snapshot\n94: - Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n95: - Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n96: - Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n97: \n98: ---\n99: \n100: ## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n101: - Max iterations: 10\n102: - Min iterations: 3\n103: - Convergence threshold: 0.05\n104: - Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n105: - Progressive synthesis: true\n106: - Current generation: 1\n107: - Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z\n\n(End of file - total 107 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","text":"# Deep Research Strategy - gpt55-fast-1\n\n## 1. TOPIC\nValidate and stress-test the merge design for folding deep-loop-runtime into deep-loop-workflows as system-deep-loop: structural layout, bidirectional path-coupling repair, the system-spec-kit tooling-borrow, reference migration across commands/agents/READMEs/advisor-corpus, and whether fallback-router.ts should be wired for real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n## 2. KEY QUESTIONS (remaining)\n- [x] Does the proposed `system-deep-loop` structural layout preserve the current workflow/runtime split without creating ambiguous ownership or broken relative paths?\n- [x] Which bidirectional path couplings between `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, commands, agents, docs, tests, and scripts must be repaired mechanically during the merge?\n- [ ] Which `system-spec-kit` tooling should be borrowed, wrapped, or left external instead of duplicated inside the merged deep-loop system?\n- [ ] What reference migration is required across commands, agents, READMEs, skill docs, feature catalogs, manual testing playbooks, specs, and advisor corpus entries?\n- [ ] Should `fallback-router.ts` be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:key-questions -->\n\n---\n\n## 3. NON-GOALS\n- Do not implement or move files.\n- Do not modify `deep-loop-workflows`, `deep-loop-runtime`, command assets, agents, specs, advisor corpus, or root packet docs.\n- Do not write outside this lineage artifact directory.\n\n---\n\n## 4. STOP CONDITIONS\n- At least three evidence iterations have completed and all key questions have cited answers.\n- Further iterations would add only marginal confirmation relative to the accumulated evidence.\n- The loop reaches `maxIterations: 10`.\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n## 5. ANSWERED QUESTIONS\n- Structural layout: preserve `deep-loop-workflows` as public hub/mode packets and `deep-loop-runtime` as internal backend under a merged `system-deep-loop` root; do not flatten them (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:12`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n- Path coupling: rewrite command YAML and compiled contracts, doctor routes/assets, orchestrator/agent prompt contracts, advisor Python/TS/tests/metadata, system-spec-kit test/optimizer/docs, and runtime integration docs atomically with the move (iteration 2, evidence: `.opencode/commands/deep/assets/deep_research_auto.yaml:64-77`, `.opencode/commands/doctor/_routes.yaml:100-110`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py:2570-2587`).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:answered-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: START -->\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n## 6. WHAT WORKED\n- Contract-first structural read: hub/runtime READMEs and SKILL contracts exposed the ownership seam before path inventory work (iteration 1).\n- Exact old-root greps across scoped surfaces separated executable migration targets from lower-priority prose references (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-worked -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n## 7. WHAT FAILED\n- Broad markdown globbing across `deep-loop-workflows` was noisy because catalogs/playbooks dominate the tree; targeted grep/read is needed next (iteration 1).\n- Generated compiled contracts are not authoritative enough to repair references on their own; source YAML/advisor/test files must rewrite first, then contracts regenerate (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:what-failed -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n## 8. EXHAUSTED APPROACHES (do not retry)\nNone yet.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:exhausted-approaches -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n## 9. RULED OUT DIRECTIONS\n- Flattening runtime and workflow packets into one directory: contradicts the logic-free hub and backend-only runtime contracts (iteration 1, evidence: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md:37-39`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:23-30`).\n- Moving directories first and relying on generated contracts to catch up: generated contracts are outputs, while source YAML, advisor code, agents, and test configs carry old paths (iteration 2).\n<!-- /ANCHOR:ruled-out-directions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n## 10. CARRIED-FORWARD OPEN QUESTIONS\n- Which system-spec-kit tooling should remain borrowed/external instead of moving into `system-deep-loop`?\n<!-- /ANCHOR:carried-forward-open-questions -->\n\n---\n\n<!-- ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n## 11. NEXT FOCUS\nSystem-spec-kit tooling borrow: identify which current shared pieces (`resolveArtifactRoot`, spec validation, memory/context save, resource-map extraction, optimizer/test discovery) should remain external contracts versus be moved, wrapped, or duplicated under the merged `system-deep-loop` root.\n<!-- /ANCHOR:next-focus -->\n<!-- MACHINE-OWNED: END -->\n\n---\n\n## 12. KNOWN CONTEXT\n- Active spec packet says this phase is read-only research and forbids modifying `deep-loop-workflows` or `deep-loop-runtime` [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:68-75].\n- Plan confirms the exact fanout payload and flags the `iterations` vs `iters` field-name trap [SOURCE: .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:71-85].\n- `resource-map.md` was absent at init; coverage gate is skipped for prior inventory.\n\n### Bounded Context Snapshot\n- Source pointers: `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/`, `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`, `.opencode/commands/deep/`, `.opencode/agents/`, `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/`, and `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/`.\n- Integration points: command YAML references workflow skill docs, runtime scripts, runtime libraries, and memory/graph/reducer paths.\n- Constraints: all writes for this detached lineage are confined to `.opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1`.\n\n---\n\n## 13. RESEARCH BOUNDARIES\n- Max iterations: 10\n- Min iterations: 3\n- Convergence threshold: 0.05\n- Per-iteration budget: 12 tool calls, 10 minutes\n- Progressive synthesis: true\n- Current generation: 1\n- Started: 2026-07-08T04:57:16Z","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":107,"totalLines":107,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/research/lineages/gpt55-fast-1/deep-research-strategy.md","time":{"start":1783487161290,"end":1783487161336}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_09439ad4b1df9fb8016a4ddab93c508191b13cf0e690f3c260"}},"id":"prt_f401e63c9001L