{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487175549,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"grep","callID":"call_IxXUhG3vqVKvEDDHHTMJ8WIh","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"pattern":"system-spec-kit|generate-context|memory_save|validate\\.sh|review-research-paths|resource-map|optimizer|vitest\\.config","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime","include":"*"},"output":"Found 100 matches (more matches available)\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts:\n  Line 4: // root (npm test) without borrowing the system-spec-kit MCP server config.\n\n  Line 5: // The system-spec-kit config still discovers these same tests for the\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tsconfig.json:\n  Line 13:       \"../system-spec-kit/node_modules/@types\"\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md:\n  Line 267: The system-spec-kit `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` so a single vitest run discovers both surfaces.\n\n  Line 286: - **NEVER** import from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` or `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/` — those locations are empty after the runtime moved here; import from this skill instead\n\n  Line 313: - DB lifecycle inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`\n\n  Line 335: | `tests/` | Unit, integration, lifecycle | Runtime-owned tests discovered by the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config. |\n\n  Line 354: - **system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts** includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` for cross-package test discovery.\n\n  Line 366: - Runtime tests under `tests/` pass through the system-spec-kit Vitest discovery glob\n\n  Line 379: - `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` discovers this skill's `tests/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs:\n  Line 6: // ║ single implementation continues to live in system-spec-kit; the runtime  ║\n\n  Line 18:   path.join(__dirname, '..', '..', '..', 'system-spec-kit', 'shared', 'review-research-paths.cjs'),\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/README.md:\n  Line 3: description: \"Maintainer map for deep-loop runtime helpers moved out of system-spec-kit MCP server.\"\n\n  Line 15: `lib/deep-loop/` is the migrated runtime home for deep-review and deep-research loop helpers. Legacy references to `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` should point here unless they specifically describe old provenance.\n\n  Line 33: | `artifact-root.cjs` | Canonical seam for the artifact-topology resolver (`resolveArtifactRoot`). The single implementation stays in `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`; the research, review and context reducers import it from here so the dependency points at the backend. |\n\n  Line 41: - Spec Kit runtime: `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/memory/bounded-cache.ts`, `audit-rotation.ts`, `lib/runtime/timer-registry.ts`, `shutdown-hooks.ts`.\n\n  Line 42: - Ops: `system-spec-kit/scripts/ops/process-memory-harness.ts`, `process-sweep.ts`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 11:         \"target\": \"system-spec-kit\",\n\n  Line 13:         \"context\": \"imports zod, better-sqlite3, TSX loader, command YAML consumers, and shared test discovery from system-spec-kit paths\"\n\n  Line 61:       \"system-spec-kit\"\n\n  Line 228:     \"causal_summary\": \"Shared runtime infrastructure for deep-review, deep-research and deep-ai-council moved into a peer skill in the 118 FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP arc. Executor configuration, audit provenance, prompt rendering, post-dispatch validation, state safety, Bayesian scoring, fallback routing, coverage-graph storage/query/signals, script entry points, SQLite storage and runtime tests now have one discoverable owner outside the system-spec-kit MCP server. lib/council/ adds 5 cjs modules for multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator verdict scoring, cost guards and session-state hierarchy per packet 131/001/008 ADR-001 (Runtime Boundary Decision).\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/check-contract-drift.cjs:\n  Line 39:   '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/compile-command-contracts.cjs:\n  Line 14:   autoModeContract: '.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/references/workflows/auto_mode_contract.md',\n\n  Line 491:         'classifierPath: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/shared/gate-3-classifier.ts',\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.5.0.0.md:\n  Line 50: - **Graduation benchmark**: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-search-intelligence/007-dark-flag-graduation/008-deeploop-finding-dedup/` (three graduate verdicts, dedup precision 1.0 / distinct-recall 1.0 / zero false collapses)\n\n  Line 51: - **Scale validation and fixes**: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-search-intelligence/010-graduation-follow-ups/002-deeploop-gauges-dedup-scale/` (75-finding scale set, title-only false-collapse 0.50 to 0, lag metric redefinition)\n\n  Line 52: - **Opus deep review**: `.opencode/specs/system-spec-kit/028-memory-search-intelligence/011-followup-deep-review/` (P1-7 stall metric, P2-15 title-aware dedup)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.1.0.0.md:\n  Line 9: The deep-loop-runtime v1.0.0 baseline shipped the arc-118 FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP consolidation but the documentation surface had never been audited end to end against the current sk-doc templates or HVR voice standards. The README was undersized at 174 LOC with only 6 of the 9 sections that the system-spec-kit README structural anchor prescribes. The SKILL.md frontmatter description was 240 chars (over the 130-char skill limit). Two artifacts (SKILL.md and README.md) carried a broken changelog path reference (`v1.0.0.md` instead of `v1.0.0.0.md`). A top-level `## Council Primitives` H2 inside section 3 broke the numbered-H2-ALL-CAPS rule.\n\n  Line 19: The README was rewritten from 174 LOC to 470 LOC. The new structure follows the system-spec-kit 9-section pattern (OVERVIEW, QUICK START, FEATURES with 7 sub-domains, STRUCTURE, CONFIGURATION, USAGE EXAMPLES, TROUBLESHOOTING, FAQ, RELATED DOCUMENTS). The voice is anchored at ~70% of `Public/README.md` intensity. HVR self-scoring caught zero em dashes, zero prose semicolons, zero banned metaphors, zero setup-language patterns and zero copula-avoidance constructions. `validate_document.py --type readme` exits 0.\n\n  Line 63: No consumer action required. The script-interface contract (argv shape, stdout JSON shape, exit codes) is unchanged. TS import paths into `lib/` are unchanged. The SQLite schema is unchanged at version 2. `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob still picks up tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n  Line 74: - **Decision records**: `.../001-deep-loop-runtime/decision-record.md` (ADR-001 Level 3, ADR-002 all-cli-devin phase 5, ADR-003 assets absent, ADR-004 no-code-edit boundary, ADR-005 resource-map.md canonical)\n\n  Line 78: - **Structural anchor**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/README.md` (9-section pattern)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.3.0.0.md:\n  Line 11: 1. The runtime SQLite directory was named `storage/` while the sibling `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` uses `database/`. The inconsistent name made the convention harder to follow and the sqlite inside was committed to git, so external repo users shipped a stale binary database instead of regenerating a fresh one on first run.\n\n  Line 64: - **Convention precedent**: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:\n  Line 1588:       // deep-review-state.jsonl, review-report.md, resource-map.md) INTO lineageDir, so a\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.0.0.0.md:\n  Line 1: This is the first shipped release of `deep-loop-runtime`. The earlier `v0.1.0` state was a phase-001 scaffold. Version `1.0.0` marks the runtime as populated and verified: shared deep-loop libraries, coverage-graph ownership, direct script entry points, SQLite storage, and runtime tests now live together in the peer skill instead of inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\n\n  Line 9: Before 118, every change to the deep-review or deep-research loop infrastructure required touching files inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`. Two consumer skills (`deep-review`, `deep-research`) depended on internals of a third skill (`system-spec-kit`), and the MCP tool surface (`mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*`) added a marshalling layer between workflow YAMLs and the SQLite-backed coverage graph. The arrangement was accumulated drift from early MCP server scaffolding; no ADR justified it. Arc 118 (FULL_ISOLATE_NO_MCP, user-directive override of the 117 AI Council SPLIT ruling) consolidated all deep-loop runtime infrastructure into this peer skill, removed the MCP tool surface entirely, and replaced it with direct `.cjs` script invocation — the same pattern `reduce-state.cjs` already used. Workflow YAML calls became one-step (`bash: node .../scripts/<name>.cjs`) instead of two-step (MCP-dispatch then JSON-parse).\n\n  Line 43: - The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` for cross-package test discovery, so a single `pnpm vitest run` exercises both surfaces.\n\n  Line 59: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/` | 10 shared runtime modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/`. |\n\n  Line 60: | `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/coverage-graph/` | 3 coverage-graph modules moved from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/`. |\n\n  Line 72: Consumers should call the four `.cjs` scripts directly rather than attempting to use the deleted `mcp__mk_spec_memory__deep_loop_graph_*` MCP tools. The migration source was `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`; after arc 118, the runtime owner is `.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/`. Workflow YAMLs (`spec_kit_deep-{review,research}_{auto,confirm}.yaml`) were updated to invoke the scripts via `bash:` blocks; `/doctor` diagnostics and the `system-code-graph` playbook scenario 009 were updated correspondingly. The `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` glob was extended to discover tests at `../deep-loop-runtime/tests/`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/package.json:\n  Line 11:     \"typecheck\": \"../system-spec-kit/node_modules/.bin/tsc --noEmit --composite false -p tsconfig.json\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/changelog/v1.2.0.0.md:\n  Line 31: Two new unit test files for the previously-uncovered `coverage-graph-query` (8 tests) and `coverage-graph-signals` (9 tests). Two weak council tests deepened: multi-seat-dispatch (2 to 6 tests) and round-state-jsonl (2 to 6 tests). All 29 tests pass via the system-spec-kit vitest harness.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-pool-concurrency-cap.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-pool.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/artifact-dir-override-parity.md:\n  Line 50: 6. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-run-cli-lineage-spawn.md:\n  Line 47: 3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-run.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-salvage-recovery.md:\n  Line 48: 3. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-salvage.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-merge-review-strongest-restriction.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts --reporter=verbose`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-merge-research.md:\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/fanout-merge.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/manual_testing_playbook/09--fanout/fanout-config-schema.md:\n  Line 40: - vitest resolves from `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`.\n\n  Line 45: 2. `bash: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/unit/executor-config.vitest.ts`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md:\n  Line 38: Several deep loops shared the same runtime code. Each needed executor config parsing. Each needed atomic state-log writes and single-writer locking. Each needed a coverage graph that survives a session crash. Each needed Bayesian convergence scoring. Before this skill existed, all of that lived inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/` and got reached through MCP tools. The consumer modes depended on the internals of a separate package, every workflow call paid the MCP marshalling and JSON-parse round-trip, and each loop would otherwise duplicate executor config, atomic-state writes, JSONL repair, single-writer locking, coverage-graph ownership, Bayesian scoring and fallback routing.\n\n  Line 81: pnpm --dir .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server exec vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests\n\n  Line 84: Expected output: the vitest runner discovers the unit, integration and lifecycle tests through the cross-package glob in `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts`. A green run confirms the runtime is wired correctly.\n\n  Line 127: `system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `sk-code` owns code standards and test verification. This runtime owns the infrastructure the loops ride and nothing else.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md:\n  Line 36: **Shared backend contracts (consolidation promotions).** Beyond the numbered entries above, the backend hosts a small set of generic plumbing the consumer modes import rather than duplicate: `lib/deep-loop/runtime-capabilities.cjs` (parameterized capability resolver, with byte-compatible per-skill shims), `lib/deep-loop/artifact-root.cjs` (canonical seam re-exporting `resolveArtifactRoot` from `system-spec-kit/shared/review-research-paths.cjs`), `lib/deep-loop/lifecycle-taxonomy.cjs` (terminal lifecycle enum: seven `stopReason` plus four `sessionOutcome` values) and `scripts/loop-lock.cjs` (CLI adapter over `loop-lock.ts`). These contracts register no MCP tools and carry no public workflow routing; resource-map emission stays in the workflow shared-synthesis layer, not in this runtime.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/integration_points.md:\n  Line 96: The runtime tests are discovered from the system-spec-kit MCP server Vitest config:\n\n  Line 99: .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts\n\n  Line 106: - `coverage-graph-db.ts`, `coverage-graph-signals.ts`, and `council/council-graph-db.ts` import `better-sqlite3` (declared here; pinned to the same version `system-spec-kit` uses so the native binding stays ABI-compatible).\n\n  Line 109: The dependency versions are kept in lockstep with `system-spec-kit` (see `package.json`), which is why graph metadata still lists `system-spec-kit` under `depends_on`. The standalone suite runs via `npm test` (local `vitest.config.ts`); the combined CI run still discovers these tests through the `system-spec-kit` MCP server config above.\n\n  Line 169: | 6 | Legacy MCP server READMEs | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/README.md:25-68` + `.../handlers/coverage-graph/README.md` | Original-location stubs documenting the runtime move |\n\n  Line 174: `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/tests/deep-loop/review-depth-reducer.vitest.ts:9` imports `'../../../../deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs'` - the test file lives in `mcp_server` but exercises `deep-review` code, and is discovered via deep-loop-runtime's vitest glob in `vitest.config.ts:20`. Effective SC-007 boundary for any deep-loop-runtime change is therefore tighter than the literal directory listing: changes to `deep-review/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` ALSO re-validate through deep-loop-runtime's test surface.\n\n  Line 202: | `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` | Runtime test discovery. |\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/references/script_interface_contract.md:\n  Line 41: - Scripts resolve `system-spec-kit/scripts/node_modules/tsx/dist/loader.mjs`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/node_modules/vitest/dist/chunks/creator.DgVhQm5q.js:\n  Line 446: \t\tcase \"qwik\": return \"@builder.io/qwik/optimizer\";\n\n  Line 667: \t\tconst configPath = resolve(process.cwd(), `vitest.config.${lang}`);\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/tests/fixtures/council-value/data/README.md:\n  Line 55: cd .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server && npx vitest run ../../deep-loop-runtime/tests/integration/council-graph-value-scenarios.vitest.ts\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/node_modules/vitest/dist/chunks/reporters.d.DtoKVV2s.d.ts:\n  Line 2677: \toptimizer?: Partial<Record<\"client\" | \"ssr\" | ({} & string), DepsOptimizationOptions>>;\n\n  Line 3173: \t* // vitest.config.ts\n\n  Line 3424: \t* Default resolving to `vitest.config.*`, `vite.config.*`\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/node_modules/vitest/dist/chunks/coverage.DM_a_rWm.js:\n  Line 331: \tresolved.deps.optimizer ??= {};\n\n  Line 332: \tresolved.deps.optimizer.ssr ??= {};\n\n  Line 333: \tresolved