{"type":"text","timestamp":1783487179349,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f401ea634001Ktt471yzCS0Lbc","messageID":"msg_f401e9e0f001RgU54cXHZM6WL2","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","type":"text","text":"The evidence points to a clear boundary: keep spec validation and memory continuity in system-spec-kit, keep runtime primitives under deep-loop-runtime/system-deep-loop runtime, and keep resource-map rendering as a workflow synthesis seam re-exporting the existing system-spec-kit renderer.","time":{"start":1783487178293,"end":1783487179348},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"msg_056e85fd659b58c5016a4ddaca4cd08191a3646e2558e285f2","phase":"commentary"}}}}
