{"type":"step_start","timestamp":1783487194255,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"id":"prt_f401ee48e001bbigqm1uHncsM4","messageID":"msg_f401ede8e001NMk64kEjG57Sry","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","snapshot":"88d862a4af72a52fc01828d6b3090abd9ff6697f","type":"step-start"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487202128,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_2GwVgZyQwypT5O1d4NSXAW1K","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","offset":260,"limit":60},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n260: tests/\n261: ├── unit/         # 52 files — per-module unit tests (atomic-state, executor-config, etc.)\n262: ├── integration/  # 9 files — script invocations + review-depth fixtures\n263: ├── lifecycle/    # 1 file — db-open-close pattern verification\n264: └── helpers/      # spawn-cjs helper for direct-invocation tests\n265: ```\n266: \n267: The system-spec-kit `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` so a single vitest run discovers both surfaces.\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## 4. RULES\n272: \n273: ### ALWAYS\n274: \n275: - **ALWAYS** open the SQLite DB inside a `try` block and close it in a `finally` block (script lifecycle invariant per ADR-001, the script interface contract)\n276: - **ALWAYS** emit JSON-only output to stdout from `scripts/*.cjs` (workflow YAML parses stdout for output bindings)\n277: - **ALWAYS** include `'use strict';` on line 2 of every `.cjs` script (per sk-code OPENCODE JS style)\n278: - **ALWAYS** include a `MODULE: <name>` header comment in every `lib/**/*.ts` file (per sk-code OPENCODE TS-MODULE-HEADER convention)\n279: - **ALWAYS** preserve atomic-state semantics when mutating JSONL state — never partial-write\n280: - **ALWAYS** acquire `loop-lock` before any state-log mutation\n281: \n282: ### NEVER\n283: \n284: - **NEVER** register MCP tools from this skill — the isolation ADR explicitly removed the MCP surface; reintroducing tools defeats the FULL_ISOLATE direction\n285: - **NEVER** open the SQLite DB outside `lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts` — single owner of the connection\n286: - **NEVER** import from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` or `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/` — those locations are empty after the runtime moved here; import from this skill instead\n287: - **NEVER** write to `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` without holding the `loop-lock`\n288: - **NEVER** swallow exceptions in script entry points — propagate to the exit-code matrix\n289: \n290: ### ESCALATE IF\n291: \n292: - **ESCALATE** to the user if a runtime call requires a new MCP tool — the architectural direction prohibits MCP additions; the user must decide on policy override\n293: - **ESCALATE** to a new ownership ADR if a new consumer skill (beyond deep-review and deep-research) needs deep-loop runtime — extension requires a new ownership ADR\n294: - **ESCALATE** if the SQLite schema requires a backward-incompatible change — coordinate with all consumer workflows + add migration to `coverage-graph-db.ts`\n295: - **ESCALATE** if a script's stdout JSON contract changes — every workflow YAML output binding depends on the existing shape\n296: \n297: ---\n298: \n299: ## 5. SCOPE\n300: \n301: In scope:\n302: \n303: - runtime libraries under `lib/deep-loop/`\n304: - coverage-graph runtime libraries under `lib/coverage-graph/`\n305: - `.cjs` script entry points under `scripts/`\n306: - runtime-owned SQLite storage under `database/`\n307: - runtime tests under `tests/`\n308: \n309: Out of scope:\n310: \n311: - MCP tool registration\n312: - MCP handler ownership\n313: - DB lifecycle inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`\n314: - direct user command routing\n315: \n316: ---\n317: \n318: ## 6. ARCHITECTURE\n319: \n\n(Showing lines 260-319 of 380. Use offset=320 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"tests/\n├── unit/         # 52 files — per-module unit tests (atomic-state, executor-config, etc.)\n├── integration/  # 9 files — script invocations + review-depth fixtures\n├── lifecycle/    # 1 file — db-open-close pattern verification\n└── helpers/      # spawn-cjs helper for direct-invocation tests\n```\n\nThe system-spec-kit `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` so a single vitest run discovers both surfaces.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- **ALWAYS** open the SQLite DB inside a `try` block and close it in a `finally` block (script lifecycle invariant per ADR-001, the script interface contract)\n- **ALWAYS** emit JSON-only output to stdout from `scripts/*.cjs` (workflow YAML parses stdout for output bindings)\n- **ALWAYS** include `'use strict';` on line 2 of every `.cjs` script (per sk-code OPENCODE JS style)\n- **ALWAYS** include a `MODULE: <name>` header comment in every `lib/**/*.ts` file (per sk-code OPENCODE TS-MODULE-HEADER convention)\n- **ALWAYS** preserve atomic-state semantics when mutating JSONL state — never partial-write","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","text":"tests/\n├── unit/         # 52 files — per-module unit tests (atomic-state, executor-config, etc.)\n├── integration/  # 9 files — script invocations + review-depth fixtures\n├── lifecycle/    # 1 file — db-open-close pattern verification\n└── helpers/      # spawn-cjs helper for direct-invocation tests\n```\n\nThe system-spec-kit `mcp_server/vitest.config.ts` includes `'../deep-loop-runtime/tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'` so a single vitest run discovers both surfaces.\n\n---\n\n## 4. RULES\n\n### ALWAYS\n\n- **ALWAYS** open the SQLite DB inside a `try` block and close it in a `finally` block (script lifecycle invariant per ADR-001, the script interface contract)\n- **ALWAYS** emit JSON-only output to stdout from `scripts/*.cjs` (workflow YAML parses stdout for output bindings)\n- **ALWAYS** include `'use strict';` on line 2 of every `.cjs` script (per sk-code OPENCODE JS style)\n- **ALWAYS** include a `MODULE: <name>` header comment in every `lib/**/*.ts` file (per sk-code OPENCODE TS-MODULE-HEADER convention)\n- **ALWAYS** preserve atomic-state semantics when mutating JSONL state — never partial-write\n- **ALWAYS** acquire `loop-lock` before any state-log mutation\n\n### NEVER\n\n- **NEVER** register MCP tools from this skill — the isolation ADR explicitly removed the MCP surface; reintroducing tools defeats the FULL_ISOLATE direction\n- **NEVER** open the SQLite DB outside `lib/coverage-graph/coverage-graph-db.ts` — single owner of the connection\n- **NEVER** import from `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/deep-loop/` or `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/lib/coverage-graph/` — those locations are empty after the runtime moved here; import from this skill instead\n- **NEVER** write to `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` without holding the `loop-lock`\n- **NEVER** swallow exceptions in script entry points — propagate to the exit-code matrix\n\n### ESCALATE IF\n\n- **ESCALATE** to the user if a runtime call requires a new MCP tool — the architectural direction prohibits MCP additions; the user must decide on policy override\n- **ESCALATE** to a new ownership ADR if a new consumer skill (beyond deep-review and deep-research) needs deep-loop runtime — extension requires a new ownership ADR\n- **ESCALATE** if the SQLite schema requires a backward-incompatible change — coordinate with all consumer workflows + add migration to `coverage-graph-db.ts`\n- **ESCALATE** if a script's stdout JSON contract changes — every workflow YAML output binding depends on the existing shape\n\n---\n\n## 5. SCOPE\n\nIn scope:\n\n- runtime libraries under `lib/deep-loop/`\n- coverage-graph runtime libraries under `lib/coverage-graph/`\n- `.cjs` script entry points under `scripts/`\n- runtime-owned SQLite storage under `database/`\n- runtime tests under `tests/`\n\nOut of scope:\n\n- MCP tool registration\n- MCP handler ownership\n- DB lifecycle inside `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/`\n- direct user command routing\n\n---\n\n## 6. ARCHITECTURE\n","lineStart":260,"lineEnd":319,"totalLines":380,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/SKILL.md","time":{"start":1783487202124,"end":1783487202128}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f15a2db0dd5f9e0016a4ddae2052481908b27c6c2ede71ca6"}},"id":"prt_f401f032c001SBoUhgkOBEi7hw","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401ede8e001NMk64kEjG57Sry"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487202149,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_FfPayEjkhOdgjIow7cKrNKTK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md","offset":120,"limit":20},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n120: | `research` | Calls `convergence.cjs`, `upsert.cjs`, `query.cjs` and `status.cjs` from its workflow YAML. Imports `lib/deep-loop/` for prompt-pack rendering, atomic state and executor audit. |\n121: | `review` | Mirrors the research mode's script calls. Imports `lib/coverage-graph/` for its reducer and uses the Bayesian scorer and coverage signals to decide when a review has converged. |\n122: | `ai-council` | Consumes `lib/council/` for multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator scoring, cost guards and session-state hierarchy. The operator-facing council semantics stay in the `ai-council` mode. |\n123: | `improvement` | Imports the deep-loop executor config and the council cost guards. Its evaluator-first pipeline rides the same executor dispatch path the other modes use. |\n124: \n125: The deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out. Runtime `context` parsing remains for existing artifacts and graph rows until a migration proves it can be removed safely.\n126: \n127: `system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `sk-code` owns code standards and test verification. This runtime owns the infrastructure the loops ride and nothing else.\n128: \n129: ---\n130: \n131: ## 6. TROUBLESHOOTING\n132: \n133: | What you see | Why | Fix |\n134: |---|---|---|\n135: | Script exits with code 2 (DB error) | The SQLite database is missing, corrupt or locked by another writer | Confirm `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` exists and is writable. If a stale `database/.deep-loop-graph-writer.lock` survived a crash, remove it after confirming no live writer (`ps aux | grep convergence.cjs`). |\n136: | Script exits with code 3 (input validation) | Argv parsing rejected the input | Check `--spec-folder` is present, `--loop-type` is valid for the script, and `--session-id` has no path-traversal characters. Active convergence loop types are `research`, `review` and `council`; fan-out accepts only `research` and `review`; legacy `context` is retained only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility. `improvement` is host-driven, not a runtime `loopType`. The full contract is in `references/script_interface_contract.md`. |\n137: | Convergence returns CONTINUE past a high iteration count | The typed convergence signals are not passing the stop thresholds | Check the iteration outputs for corrupt data that injects fake coverage or contradiction signals. If outputs are valid, the loop is genuinely surfacing new evidence and the hard cap is the correct stop. |\n138: | Loop-lock acquisition times out | A long-running upsert holds the lock, or a stale lock survived a crash | Raise `DEEP_LOOP_WRITER_LOCK_MAX_WAIT_MS` for contended workloads. For a stale lock, remove the writer lockfile after confirming no live writer. |\n139: | A state log is corrupt mid-line | The crash happened during a write, not at a line boundary | `jsonl-repair` recovers only trailing corruption. For mid-line corruption, inspect the file and delete the broken line. The loop resumes from the last intact record. |\n\n(Showing lines 120-139 of 202. Use offset=140 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"| `research` | Calls `convergence.cjs`, `upsert.cjs`, `query.cjs` and `status.cjs` from its workflow YAML. Imports `lib/deep-loop/` for prompt-pack rendering, atomic state and executor audit. |\n| `review` | Mirrors the research mode's script calls. Imports `lib/coverage-graph/` for its reducer and uses the Bayesian scorer and coverage signals to decide when a review has converged. |\n| `ai-council` | Consumes `lib/council/` for multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator scoring, cost guards and session-state hierarchy. The operator-facing council semantics stay in the `ai-council` mode. |\n| `improvement` | Imports the deep-loop executor config and the council cost guards. Its evaluator-first pipeline rides the same executor dispatch path the other modes use. |\n\nThe deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out. Runtime `context` parsing remains for existing artifacts and graph rows until a migration proves it can be removed safely.\n\n`system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `sk-code` owns code standards and test verification. This runtime owns the infrastructure the loops ride and nothing else.\n\n---\n\n## 6. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| What you see | Why | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| Script exits with code 2 (DB error) | The SQLite database is missing, corrupt or locked by another writer | Confirm `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` exists and is writable. If a stale `database/.deep-loop-graph-writer.lock` survived a crash, remove it after confirming no live writer (`ps aux | grep convergence.cjs`). |\n| Script exits with code 3 (input validation) | Argv parsing rejected the input | Check `--spec-folder` is present, `--loop-type` is valid for the script, and `--session-id` has no path-traversal characters. Active convergence loop types are `research`, `review` and `council`; fan-out accepts only `research` and `review`; legacy `context` is retained only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility. `improvement` is host-driven, not a runtime `loopType`. The full contract is in `references/script_interface_contract.md`. |\n| Convergence returns CONTINUE past a high iteration count | The typed convergence signals are not passing the stop thresholds | Check the iteration outputs for corrupt data that injects fake coverage or contradiction signals. If outputs are valid, the loop is genuinely surfacing new evidence and the hard cap is the correct stop. |\n| Loop-lock acquisition times out | A long-running upsert holds the lock, or a stale lock survived a crash | Raise `DEEP_LOOP_WRITER_LOCK_MAX_WAIT_MS` for contended workloads. For a stale lock, remove the writer lockfile after confirming no live writer. |\n| A state log is corrupt mid-line | The crash happened during a write, not at a line boundary | `jsonl-repair` recovers only trailing corruption. For mid-line corruption, inspect the file and delete the broken line. The loop resumes from the last intact record. |","truncated":true,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md","text":"| `research` | Calls `convergence.cjs`, `upsert.cjs`, `query.cjs` and `status.cjs` from its workflow YAML. Imports `lib/deep-loop/` for prompt-pack rendering, atomic state and executor audit. |\n| `review` | Mirrors the research mode's script calls. Imports `lib/coverage-graph/` for its reducer and uses the Bayesian scorer and coverage signals to decide when a review has converged. |\n| `ai-council` | Consumes `lib/council/` for multi-seat dispatch, round-state JSONL, adjudicator scoring, cost guards and session-state hierarchy. The operator-facing council semantics stay in the `ai-council` mode. |\n| `improvement` | Imports the deep-loop executor config and the council cost guards. Its evaluator-first pipeline rides the same executor dispatch path the other modes use. |\n\nThe deprecated standalone context loop no longer consumes fan-out. Runtime `context` parsing remains for existing artifacts and graph rows until a migration proves it can be removed safely.\n\n`system-spec-kit` owns the spec folder, validation and memory continuity. `sk-code` owns code standards and test verification. This runtime owns the infrastructure the loops ride and nothing else.\n\n---\n\n## 6. TROUBLESHOOTING\n\n| What you see | Why | Fix |\n|---|---|---|\n| Script exits with code 2 (DB error) | The SQLite database is missing, corrupt or locked by another writer | Confirm `database/deep-loop-graph.sqlite` exists and is writable. If a stale `database/.deep-loop-graph-writer.lock` survived a crash, remove it after confirming no live writer (`ps aux | grep convergence.cjs`). |\n| Script exits with code 3 (input validation) | Argv parsing rejected the input | Check `--spec-folder` is present, `--loop-type` is valid for the script, and `--session-id` has no path-traversal characters. Active convergence loop types are `research`, `review` and `council`; fan-out accepts only `research` and `review`; legacy `context` is retained only where a script explicitly documents historical artifact compatibility. `improvement` is host-driven, not a runtime `loopType`. The full contract is in `references/script_interface_contract.md`. |\n| Convergence returns CONTINUE past a high iteration count | The typed convergence signals are not passing the stop thresholds | Check the iteration outputs for corrupt data that injects fake coverage or contradiction signals. If outputs are valid, the loop is genuinely surfacing new evidence and the hard cap is the correct stop. |\n| Loop-lock acquisition times out | A long-running upsert holds the lock, or a stale lock survived a crash | Raise `DEEP_LOOP_WRITER_LOCK_MAX_WAIT_MS` for contended workloads. For a stale lock, remove the writer lockfile after confirming no live writer. |\n| A state log is corrupt mid-line | The crash happened during a write, not at a line boundary | `jsonl-repair` recovers only trailing corruption. For mid-line corruption, inspect the file and delete the broken line. The loop resumes from the last intact record. |","lineStart":120,"lineEnd":139,"totalLines":202,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md","time":{"start":1783487202146,"end":1783487202149}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f15a2db0dd5f9e0016a4ddae2053481908890817acc89d835"}},"id":"prt_f401f034e001HUT6P1TgKLATlJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401ede8e001NMk64kEjG57Sry"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487202159,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_P2aeHPNFxS9pUEFdlko1AOYl","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts","offset":1,"limit":40},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: // MODULE: deep-loop-runtime Vitest Config\n2: //\n3: // Self-contained discovery config so the runtime suite runs from this skill\n4: // root (npm test) without borrowing the system-spec-kit MCP server config.\n5: // The system-spec-kit config still discovers these same tests for the\n6: // combined CI run; this config covers the standalone path.\n7: \n8: import { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\n9: import path from 'node:path';\n10: \n11: const TEST_TIMEOUT_MS = 30_000;\n12: const TEARDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS = 1_000;\n13: \n14: export default defineConfig({\n15:   root: path.resolve(import.meta.dirname),\n16:   test: {\n17:     include: ['tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'],\n18:     // Several script and lifecycle suites mutate shared state (the graph\n19:     // writer lock, temp project roots). Run files serially for determinism.\n20:     fileParallelism: false,\n21:     globals: true,\n22:     environment: 'node',\n23:     testTimeout: TEST_TIMEOUT_MS,\n24:     teardownTimeout: TEARDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS,\n25:   },\n26: });\n\n(End of file - total 26 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"// MODULE: deep-loop-runtime Vitest Config\n//\n// Self-contained discovery config so the runtime suite runs from this skill\n// root (npm test) without borrowing the system-spec-kit MCP server config.\n// The system-spec-kit config still discovers these same tests for the\n// combined CI run; this config covers the standalone path.\n\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\nconst TEST_TIMEOUT_MS = 30_000;\nconst TEARDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS = 1_000;\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  root: path.resolve(import.meta.dirname),\n  test: {\n    include: ['tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'],\n    // Several script and lifecycle suites mutate shared state (the graph\n    // writer lock, temp project roots). Run files serially for determinism.\n    fileParallelism: false,","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts","text":"// MODULE: deep-loop-runtime Vitest Config\n//\n// Self-contained discovery config so the runtime suite runs from this skill\n// root (npm test) without borrowing the system-spec-kit MCP server config.\n// The system-spec-kit config still discovers these same tests for the\n// combined CI run; this config covers the standalone path.\n\nimport { defineConfig } from 'vitest/config';\nimport path from 'node:path';\n\nconst TEST_TIMEOUT_MS = 30_000;\nconst TEARDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS = 1_000;\n\nexport default defineConfig({\n  root: path.resolve(import.meta.dirname),\n  test: {\n    include: ['tests/**/*.{vitest,test}.ts'],\n    // Several script and lifecycle suites mutate shared state (the graph\n    // writer lock, temp project roots). Run files serially for determinism.\n    fileParallelism: false,\n    globals: true,\n    environment: 'node',\n    testTimeout: TEST_TIMEOUT_MS,\n    teardownTimeout: TEARDOWN_TIMEOUT_MS,\n  },\n});","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":26,"totalLines":26,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/vitest.config.ts","time":{"start":1783487202156,"end":1783487202158}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0f15a2db0dd5f9e0016a4ddae2053c8190a407128af167e1de"}},"id":"prt_f401f036300137U0Q7gKuoC3e5","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f401ede8e001NMk64kEjG57Sry"}}
