pt\",\n    \"framework\",\n    \"scoring\",\n    \"enhancement\",\n    \"clear\"\n  ],\n  \"intent_signals\": [\n    \"improve prompt\",\n    \"enhance prompt\",\n    \"prompt framework\",\n    \"clear score\"\n  ],\n  \"derived\": {\n    \"trigger_phrases\": [\n      \"improve prompt\",\n      \"enhance prompt\",\n      \"prompt framework\",\n      \"clear score\",\n      \"improve this prompt\",\n      \"prompt engineering framework\",\n      \"depth thinking workflow\",\n      \"score prompt quality\",\n      \"sk-prompt\",\n      \"sk improve prompt\",\n      \"prompt-engineering\",\n      \"prompt-improvement\"\n    ],\n    \"key_topics\": [\n      \"prompt\",\n      \"framework\",\n      \"scoring\",\n      \"enhancement\",","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":70,"totalLines":148,"truncated":true}},"title":".opencode/skills/sk-prompt/graph-metadata.json","time":{"start":1783487631305,"end":1783487631313}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44f39502950988016a4ddc8f2c2c8191a496844646fa4116"}},"id":"prt_f40258fc8001k2I4WWVtBdjyae","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40255c13001voTWmO6Se3DE4R"}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1783487631315,"sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_53dMihHp7vUH1wguy5OsXUaK","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/memory-system-spec-kit-only.md","offset":1,"limit":80},"output":"<path>/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/memory-system-spec-kit-only.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: ---\n2: title: \"MEMORY — Spec-Kit System Only\"\n3: importanceTier: constitutional\n4: contextType: decision\n5: last_confirmed: \"2026-05-31\"\n6: last_confirmed_source: \"git-log-last-touch\"\n7: triggerPhrases:\n8:   - save memory\n9:   - save context\n10:   - save to memory\n11:   - remember this\n12:   - remember that\n13:   - claude memory\n14:   - native memory\n15:   - memory save\n16:   - where to save memory\n17:   - which memory system\n18: ---\n19: \n20: # Memory — Spec-Kit System Only\n21: \n22: ## Rule\n23: \n24: Use **only the Spec Kit Memory system** for all memories. Do **NOT** write to Claude Code native file-based memory unless the user, in that request, explicitly asks to save something to Claude memory.\n25: \n26: Native memory = the per-project stores under `~/.claude/projects/<slug>/memory/` and `~/.claude-account2/projects/<slug>/memory/` (their `MEMORY.md` index + per-fact `.md` files).\n27: \n28: ## Why\n29: \n30: The operator standardized on a single memory system (Spec Kit Memory) as the source of truth, and deleted all Claude native per-project memory on 2026-05-31. Two parallel stores drift, duplicate, and create ambiguity about where a fact lives; writing native memory again silently re-establishes the split the operator just removed. (Owner directive, 2026-05-31.)\n31: \n32: ## How to apply\n33: \n34: 1. Any \"save memory\" / \"save context\" / \"remember this\" request → **Spec Kit Memory**:\n35:    - `/memory:save` (or compose JSON → `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`) for normal/critical memories.\n36:    - `/memory:learn` for always-surface constitutional rules (writes `constitutional/*.md`).\n37: 2. **NEVER**, on your own initiative, create or append to `~/.claude/**/memory/*.md` or `~/.claude-account2/**/memory/*.md` — not even a `MEMORY.md` index line.\n38: 3. **ONLY** write Claude native memory when the user's request explicitly says so (e.g. \"save this to claude memory\", \"write it to native memory\"). Native is off by default, opt-in per explicit instruction.\n39: 4. If unsure which system a save belongs in, default to Spec Kit Memory and say so — do not silently choose native.\n40: \n41: ## When this rule does NOT apply\n42: \n43: - The user explicitly directs a save to Claude native memory in the current request.\n44: - Reading existing native memory for context (this rule governs WRITES, not reads).\n\n(End of file - total 44 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"---\ntitle: \"MEMORY — Spec-Kit System Only\"\nimportanceTier: constitutional\ncontextType: decision\nlast_confirmed: \"2026-05-31\"\nlast_confirmed_source: \"git-log-last-touch\"\ntriggerPhrases:\n  - save memory\n  - save context\n  - save to memory\n  - remember this\n  - remember that\n  - claude memory\n  - native memory\n  - memory save\n  - where to save memory\n  - which memory system\n---\n\n# Memory — Spec-Kit System Only","truncated":false,"loaded":[],"display":{"type":"file","path":"/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/memory-system-spec-kit-only.md","text":"---\ntitle: \"MEMORY — Spec-Kit System Only\"\nimportanceTier: constitutional\ncontextType: decision\nlast_confirmed: \"2026-05-31\"\nlast_confirmed_source: \"git-log-last-touch\"\ntriggerPhrases:\n  - save memory\n  - save context\n  - save to memory\n  - remember this\n  - remember that\n  - claude memory\n  - native memory\n  - memory save\n  - where to save memory\n  - which memory system\n---\n\n# Memory — Spec-Kit System Only\n\n## Rule\n\nUse **only the Spec Kit Memory system** for all memories. Do **NOT** write to Claude Code native file-based memory unless the user, in that request, explicitly asks to save something to Claude memory.\n\nNative memory = the per-project stores under `~/.claude/projects/<slug>/memory/` and `~/.claude-account2/projects/<slug>/memory/` (their `MEMORY.md` index + per-fact `.md` files).\n\n## Why\n\nThe operator standardized on a single memory system (Spec Kit Memory) as the source of truth, and deleted all Claude native per-project memory on 2026-05-31. Two parallel stores drift, duplicate, and create ambiguity about where a fact lives; writing native memory again silently re-establishes the split the operator just removed. (Owner directive, 2026-05-31.)\n\n## How to apply\n\n1. Any \"save memory\" / \"save context\" / \"remember this\" request → **Spec Kit Memory**:\n   - `/memory:save` (or compose JSON → `node .opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/scripts/dist/memory/generate-context.js`) for normal/critical memories.\n   - `/memory:learn` for always-surface constitutional rules (writes `constitutional/*.md`).\n2. **NEVER**, on your own initiative, create or append to `~/.claude/**/memory/*.md` or `~/.claude-account2/**/memory/*.md` — not even a `MEMORY.md` index line.\n3. **ONLY** write Claude native memory when the user's request explicitly says so (e.g. \"save this to claude memory\", \"write it to native memory\"). Native is off by default, opt-in per explicit instruction.\n4. If unsure which system a save belongs in, default to Spec Kit Memory and say so — do not silently choose native.\n\n## When this rule does NOT apply\n\n- The user explicitly directs a save to Claude native memory in the current request.\n- Reading existing native memory for context (this rule governs WRITES, not reads).","lineStart":1,"lineEnd":44,"totalLines":44,"truncated":false}},"title":".opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/constitutional/memory-system-spec-kit-only.md","time":{"start":1783487631306,"end":1783487631314}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0c44f39502950988016a4ddc8f2c348191b3196ee085cbb6cb"}},"id":"prt_f40258fc9001vC18jpukCp3rE8","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f40255c13001voTWmO6Se3DE4R"}}
