urate (GLM-5.2 / MiMo are 1M-context). Pure identity\n\n  Line 45:     The 'small' was inaccurate (GLM-5.2 / MiMo are 1M-context). Pure identity\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-007.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-006.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n  Line 11: glm-5.2.md\n\n  Line 13: mimo-v2.5-pro.md\n\n  Line 21: - **profile_ref resolution**: all 5 refs (`deepseek-v4-pro.md`, `kimi-k2.7-code.md`, `minimax-m3.md`, `mimo-v2.5-pro.md`, `glm-5.2.md`) resolve to existing files under `sk-prompt-models/references/models/`.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-004.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-008.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-005.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n  Line 5: \u001b[0m→ \u001b[0mRead .opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/120-glm-5-2-support/001-model-registration/implementation-summary.md\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-002.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n  Line 4: \u001b[0m→ \u001b[0mRead .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\n\n  Line 6: \u001b[0m→ \u001b[0mRead .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/benchmarks/008-glm-5.2-prompt-framework/synthesis.md\n\n  Line 7: \u001b[0m⚙ \u001b[0msequential_thinking_sequentialthinking {\"thought\":\"Let me systematically compare the three files for honesty/overclaim defects.\\n\\n**Synthesis.md core claims:**\\n- Verdict: TIE (inside_noise_floor) on correctness\\n- Top-pair: costar vs tidd-ec, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]\\n- Leaderboard: costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 > rcaf 0.976\\n- Format adherence: costar 1.0, tidd-ec 1.0, cidi 1.0, race 1.0, rcaf 0.889\\n- Words median: costar 13, tidd-ec 38, cidi 94, race 94, rcaf 85\\n- n=9 per framework\\n- 1 saturated fixture (ipv4, date), 1 separable (semver)\\n\\n**Check 1: Per-framework numbers in profile vs synthesis**\\nmodel_profiles.json glm-5.2 evidence sample: \\\"costar 1.0 = tidd-ec 1.0 = cidi 1.0 = race 1.0 (perfect tier) > rcaf 0.976\\\" ✅ matches\\nglm-5.2.md table: costar 1.000/1.000/13, tidd-ec 1.000/1.000/38, cidi 1.000/1.000/94, race 1.000/1.000/94, rcaf 0.976/0.889/85 ✅ matches exactly\\n\\n**Check 2: Description claim \\\"COSTAR as empirical winner\\\"**\\nmodel_profiles.json description (line 237 area): \\\"COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)\\\"\\nglm-5.2.md line 4 description: \\\"COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)\\\"\\nSynthesis says: TIE among 4 frameworks at perfect correctness. COSTAR is ranked #1 only because of token efficiency (13 words vs 38/94/94), NOT because of correctness superiority.\\n\\nIs calling COSTAR \\\"the empirical winner\\\" an overclaim? The synthesis explicitly says \\\"TIE\\\" — the 4 perfect frameworks \\\"cannot be statistically separated.\\\" The profile does explain the tie in §3 and §4, but the frontmatter description and model_profiles.json description call it \\\"empirical\\\" without qualification. The \\\"status: empirical\\\" on the JSON entry at line 295 is also unqualified.\\n\\n**Check 3: \\\"status: empirical\\\" justification**\\nThe status field means \\\"backed by benchmark evidence.\\\" COSTAR IS backed by benchmark 008 — it's in the perfect tier. The status doesn't claim...\n  Line 9: {\"pass\":\"glm-bakeoff-evidence-honesty\",\"findings\":[{\"severity\":\"P1\",\"file\":\".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\"issue\":\"Frontmatter description calls COSTAR 'empirical, benchmark 008' as if it were the unique winner; synthesis says TIE among 4 frameworks at perfect correctness (costar=tidd-ec=cidi=race 1.0, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]). The body §3/§4 honestly disclose the TIE and call it 'best-of-tied + corroborated', but the summary line overclaims.\",\"evidence\":\"line 4: 'COSTAR framework (empirical, benchmark 008; fallback TIDD-EC, avoid RCAF)' vs synthesis.md line 5: 'Verdict: TIE (inside_noise_floor) on ranking key correctness'\"}]}\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-009.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-001.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n  Line 5: \u001b[0m→ \u001b[0mRead .opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\n\n  Line 6: \u001b[0m✱ \u001b[0mGrep \"glm-5\\.2|GLM-5\\.2\"\u001b[90m in .opencode/skills/cli-opencode/SKILL.md · 11 matches\u001b[0m\n\n  Line 12: {\"pass\":\"glm-registration-correctness\",\"findings\":[]}\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/deep-review-findings-registry.json:\n  Line 3:   \"target\": \"session work (157 GLM-5.2 + 158 rename)\",\n\n  Line 4:   \"executor\": \"xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high\",\n\n  Line 10:       \"pass\": \"glm-bakeoff-evidence-honesty\",\n\n  Line 11:       \"file\": \"sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:\n  Line 2: > build · mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-sk-prompt-models-rename/review/review-report.md:\n  Line 1: # Deep Review Report — session work (GLM-5.2 adoption + sk-prompt-models rename)\n\n  Line 5: | **Target** | This session's work: packet 157 (GLM-5.2 adoption) + packet 158 (sk-prompt-small-model → sk-prompt-models rename) |\n\n  Line 6: | **Executor** | MiMo V2.5 Pro Hyperspeed — `cli-opencode → xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed --variant high` (COSTAR prompt-craft) |\n\n  Line 18: | 1 | glm-registration-correctness | clean |\n\n  Line 19: | 2 | glm-bakeoff-evidence-honesty | **1 × P2** (resolved) |\n\n  Line 31: ### F1 — P2 (resolved): frontmatter overclaim in `glm-5.2.md`\n\n  Line 33: - **Issue:** the `glm-5.2.md` frontmatter `description` called COSTAR \"empirical, benchmark 008\" without the *best-of-tied* caveat that the body (§3/§4) and the `_index.md` row both carry — benchmark 008 was a TIE among four frameworks at perfect correctness (costar = tidd-ec = cidi = race, margin 0, 90% CI [0,0]); COSTAR is the best-of-tied pick (tersest + cross-model corroborated), not a decisive sole winner.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:\n  Line 49:   readonly quota_pool: string;\n\n  Line 50:   readonly fallback_target: string | null;\n\n  Line 53:   readonly onFailureTarget?: string | FallbackFailureTargets | null;\n\n  Line 111:   const configuredTarget = failedModel.onFailureTarget;\n\n  Line 132:     target: failedModel.fallback_target,\n\n  Line 185:   if (profile.fallback_target !== null) {\n\n  Line 186:     edges.push({ source: profile, targetId: profile.fallback_target, kind: 'legacy' });\n\n  Line 193:   if (typeof profile.onFailureTarget === 'string') {\n\n  Line 196:       targetId: profile.onFailureTarget,\n\n  Line 200:   } else if (isFailureTargets(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n\n  Line 201:     for (const [failureKind, targetId] of Object.entries(profile.onFailureTarget)) {\n\n  Line 344:  * resolves to a model the caller approved. The configured `fallback_target` is\n\n  Line 381:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, no separate-pool fallback configured for ${failedModel.id}`,\n\n  Line 393:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, configured ${describeTargetKind(selection)} ${selection.target} is not in the registry`,\n\n  Line 400:   if (targetModel.quota_pool === failedModel.quota_pool) {\n\n  Line 404:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} shares the same pool; same-pool fallback rejected`,\n\n  Line 415:         reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, fallback target ${targetModel.id} is not in the caller-approved model set; unapproved substitution rejected`,\n\n  Line 426:       reason: `${failedModel.quota_pool} pool exhausted, routing ${failedModel.id} to separate ${targetModel.quota_pool} pool target ${targetModel.id}`,\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 86:     \"skilled-agent-orchestration/z_archive/101-cli-opencode-mimo-pro-optimization\",\n\n  Line 103:     \"skilled-agent-orchestration/120-glm-5-2-support\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/118-frontmatter-versioning/003-apply-core-skill-docs/implementation-summary.md:\n  Line 8:   - \"mimo audit core docs\"\n\n  Line 76: The engine applied the manifest deterministically and `verify` confirmed every value (exit 0). A read-only MiMo v2.5 Pro audit (dispatched via cli-opencode, `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro`) reviewed a skill's versioned docs as the in-the-loop second pass and confirmed the asset/reference/README values were correct, last-key, and 4-part with trigger_phrases intact. The `gate` mode then caught a real defect that `verify` did not, and the fix was re-applied and re-gated to green.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_research.contract.md:\n  Line 188:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 312:      D) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/118-frontmatter-versioning/003-apply-core-skill-docs/graph-metadata.json:\n  Line 35:       \"mimo\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_ai-council.contract.md:\n  Line 257:     model: \"\"  # optional executor-specific model id (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/commands/deep/assets/compiled/deep_review.contract.md:\n  Line 186:   executor_model: \"\"  # optional, executor-specific (cli-opencode e.g. xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro, minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M2.7-highspeed)\n\n  Line 345:      D) cli-opencode — `opencode run --model X --format json --dangerously-skip-permissions --pure --dir {repo_root} [--variant Y] \"PROMPT\" </dev/null` (no `--agent`: current opencode rejects top-level `--agent general` — default agent runs; required for MiniMax/Xiaomi token-plan models). `reasoningEffort` maps to `--variant`. No service-tier.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/sk-prompt/README.md:\n  Line 195: A: sk-prompt owns the framework definitions, the DEPTH methodology and the CLEAR rubric. It answers \"what is RCAF\" and \"how do I score a prompt.\" `sk-prompt-models` owns the per-model mapping. It answers \"which framework should MiniMax use\" and adds the model-specific scaffold and gotchas. When you dispatch to a small model, `sk-prompt-models` reads sk-prompt's framework set, picks the best fit for that model and layers on the prompt-craft profile.\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/118-frontmatter-versioning/006-fix-deep-review-findings-for-spec-docs/description.json:\n  Line 9:     \"mimo\",\n\n\n/Users/michelkerkmeester/MEGA/Development/Code_Environment/Public/.opencode/skills/cli-opencode/assets/prompt_templates.md:\n  Line 11:   - \"mimo dispatch scaffold\"\n\n  Line 490: **When**: dispatching to the MiniMax Token Plan default `minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3` (pay-per-token alternative `minimax/MiniMax-M3` via the Direct API). The 120/003 benchmark (real MiniMax M2.7 runs) found MiniMax diverges from the cross-model defaults: **TIDD-EC** framework + **dense** pre-planning wins (RCAF + medium is the fallback) — carry this contract forward to M3 until re-benchmarked. `--variant` is omitted by default (unverified). **Omit `--agent`** (rejected on opencode 1.15.13).\n\n  Line 496:   --model minimax-coding-plan/MiniMax-M3 \\\n\n  Line 531: **Why**: TIDD-EC's explicit Do's/Don'ts curb MiniMax's scope/format drift more than RCAF's role anchor (0.767 vs 0.742), and MiniMax uses dense plan structure rather than being slowed by it (0.775 dense vs 0.767 medium) — the opposite of SWE-1.6. Evidence: `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/benchmarks/003-minimax-prompt-framework/eval-loop/synthesis.md`.\n\n  Line 537: **When**: dispatching to MiMo-V2.5-Pro via the Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) — primary slug `xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro` (provider `xiaomi-token-plan-ams`, quota pool `xiaomi-token-plan`) — or via the Xiaomi Direct API — slugs `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro` and the low-latency `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` (provider `xiaomi`, pay-per-token; pick UltraSpeed for latency-sensitive checks/smokes — same COSTAR contract). The 126/004 benchmark (10/10 real `mimo-v2.5-pro` runs) found **COSTAR wins** (RACE is a statistical-tie fallback); use **lean-to-medium** pre-planning. MiMo is frontier-correct already, so frame for format + brevity, **not** guardrails — TIDD-EC/dense ranked LAST, and CIDI is unreliable (it intermittently writes to a file instead of returning inline code). **Always pass `--variant high`** — opencode maps low/medium/high to MiMo's reasoning effort (confirmed accepted on opencode 1.15.13); high is the standing default. **Omit `--agent`** (on opencode 1.15.13 `--agent general` warns and falls back to the default agent). Confirm live model ids with `opencode models xiaomi-token-plan-ams` (Token Plan) or `opencode models xiaomi` (Direct API).\n\n  Line 543:   --model xiaomi-token-plan-ams/mimo-v2.5-pro \\\n\n  Line 551: **Invocation (Direct API — pay-per-token; swap in `xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro-ultraspeed` for the low-latency tier)**:\n\n  Line 555:   --model xiaomi/mimo-v2.5-pro \\\n\n  Line 565: **Why**: MiMo-V2.5-Pro (1M-token context, strongly agentic — 1000+ tool calls, token-efficient; SWE-bench Pro 57.2) is an explicitly-selectable model on the Xiaomi Token Plan (Europe) and the Xiaomi Direct API; the default skill model stays `deepseek/deepseek-v4-pro`. The COSTAR/RACE-lean contract is the empirical 004 finding (10/10 real dispatches; the discriminator was format adherence + token efficiency, not correctness — MiMo solved every fixture under every framework). Evidence: `.opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/benchmarks/004-mimo-prompt-framework/eval/synthesis.md`.\n\n  Line 575: Use this for delegated UI build, redesign, design review, accessibility/readiness review, or design recommendations that may become implementation guidance. The dispatched agent must load `sk-design` with the right mode bundle before any design decision. For MiniMax-M3 or other small-model dispatches, pair this contract with the model profile variant in `../../sk-prompt-models/references/models/minimax-m3.md`.\n\n\n(Results truncated. Consider using a more specific path or pattern.)","metadata":{"matches":100,"truncated":true},"title":"mimo|MiniMax|glm|GLM|fallback_target|onFailureTarget|quota_pool","time":{"start":1783487883787,"end":1783487883804}},"metadata":{"openai":{"itemId":"fc_0710ee419ff88bbf016a4ddd8ba88c81919a764b860d7d9ba9"}},"id":"prt_f402969e6001Kh2fpYxYlTBOzJ","sessionID":"ses_0bfeb66caffeOOxX7Bbz2N0h6m","messageID":"msg_f402949d2001QM2GBozaaPj7Rr"}}
