search\",\"status\":\"complete\",\"focus\":\"Fallback-router wiring decision\",\"focusTrack\":\"runtime\",\"findingsCount\":8,\"newInfoRatio\":0.46,\"noveltyJustification\":\"This pass added the canonical-vs-provider model-id gap and the model-profile conflict with automatic fallback, while confirming the existing optional child 004 scope.\",\"keyQuestions\":[\"Should fallback-router.ts be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\"],\"answeredQuestions\":[\"Do not make fallback-router wiring a blocker for the core system-deep-loop merge or this read-only research phase. Keep it optional/operator-gated. If implemented, amend child 004 to add an explicit fallback registry/mapping surface, attach substitution policy in fanout-run.cjs or through a generic retry-exhausted hook, emit attribution events/labels, and test forced-failure GLM-to-MiMo re-dispatch.\"],\"ruledOut\":[{\"approach\":\"Treat fallback-router wiring as required for structural merge closeout\",\"reason\":\"Parent and child specs mark it optional/operator-gated, and current fanout mechanics already accept retry/salvage/manual re-dispatch for GLM failures.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80-88; .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/spec.md:99-125\"},{\"approach\":\"Hardcode GLM-to-MiMo substitution inside generic fanout-pool.cjs\",\"reason\":\"The generic pool knows retry state, while fanout-run owns model slugs, executor kind, lineage labels, and command construction.\",\"evidence\":\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:618-653; .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343-1375\"}],\"toolsUsed\":[\"Read\",\"Grep\"],\"sourcesQueried\":[\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:57-74\",\".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299-324\",\".op