:66-104\"\n       ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"q-fallback-router\",\n+      \"text\": \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain an offline/reference-only primitive for this phase?\",\n+      \"resolvedAtIteration\": 5,\n+      \"answer\": \"Keep fallback-router wiring optional/operator-gated and non-blocking for the core merge. If implemented, amend child 004 with an explicit fallback registry and canonical-to-provider slug mapping, model-aware substitution in fanout-run.cjs or a generic retry-exhausted hook, attribution events/labels, and forced-failure GLM-to-MiMo integration coverage.\",\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:618-653\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343-1375\",\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:35-62\"\n+      ]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"keyFindings\": [\n     {\n@@ -218,8 +229,49 @@\n         \".opencode/skills/cli-opencode/graph-metadata.json:25-34\",\n         \".opencode/skills/sk-code/graph-metadata.json:24-35\",\n         \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt/graph-metadata.json:20-26\"\n       ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-005-router-ready-zero-caller\",\n+      \"title\": \"fallback-router is ready but has no fanout caller\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The router validates fallback graphs and resolves fallback/fail-fast decisions, but the fanout pool currently retries the same lineage/model and never calls it.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/lib/deep-loop/fallback-router.ts:299-324\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:618-653\"\n+      ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-005-model-id-gap\",\n+      \"title\": \"Real GLM/MiMo fallback needs canonical-to-provider slug mapping\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The planned registry uses canonical ids while live fanout dispatch passes provider-prefixed slugs to opencode, so wiring needs an explicit mapping layer.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/001-reference-research/plan.md:77-92\",\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/plan.md:68-77\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343-1375\"\n+      ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-005-profile-contracts-manual\",\n+      \"title\": \"Current model profiles document no automatic fallback\",\n+      \"summary\": \"GLM-5.2 and MiMo profiles both list null/no automatic fallback; GLM says defer on pool exhaustion, and MiMo direct provider is a manual reroute path.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/glm-5.2.md:139-158\",\n+        \".opencode/skills/sk-prompt-models/references/models/mimo-v2.5-pro.md:154-169\"\n+      ]\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"id\": \"f-005-defer-core-merge\",\n+      \"title\": \"Fallback wiring remains optional for the core merge\",\n+      \"summary\": \"The parent and child specs mark fallback-router wiring as optional/operator-gated behavior work, not a structural merge closeout dependency.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"sources\": [\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80-88\",\n+        \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:35-62\"\n+      ]\n     }\n   ],\n   \"ruledOutDirections\": [\n     {\n@@ -250,13 +302,23 @@\n       \"approach\": \"Rename /deep commands or @agent names during reference migration\",\n       \"reason\": \"The child 003 decision freezes public command and agent surfaces; only skill identity and references migrate.\",\n       \"iteration\": 4,\n       \"evidence\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/003-external-reference-migration/spec.md:143-149\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Treat fallback-router wiring as mandatory merge closeout\",\n+      \"reason\": \"It changes fan-out behavior and is already scoped as optional/operator-gated child 004.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"evidence\": \".opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/spec.md:80-88; .opencode/specs/system-deep-loop/052-deep-loop-unification/004-fallback-router-wiring/spec.md:35-62\"\n+    },\n+    {\n+      \"approach\": \"Hardcode GLM-to-MiMo substitution inside generic fanout-pool.cjs\",\n+      \"reason\": \"The generic pool only knows retry state; model policy belongs in fanout orchestration or an explicit callback seam.\",\n+      \"iteration\": 5,\n+      \"evidence\": \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-pool.cjs:618-653; .opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/scripts/fanout-run.cjs:1343-1375\"\n     }\n   ],\n-  \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [\n-    \"Should fallback-router.ts be wired into real GLM-5.2 to MiMo-v2.5-Pro fallback now, or remain offline/reference-only for this phase?\"\n-  ],\n+  \"carriedForwardOpenQuestions\": [],\n   \"blockedStopHistory\": [],\n   \"rejectedPatterns\": [],\n   \"rejectedPatternIndex\": {\n     \"entries\": [],\n@@ -268,13 +330,13 @@\n   \"promotedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedIdeas\": [],\n   \"suppressedCandidates\": [],\n   \"metrics\": {\n-    \"iterationsCompleted\": 4,\n-    \"openQuestions\": 1,\n-    \"resolvedQuestions\": 4,\n-    \"keyFindings\": 14,\n-    \"convergenceScore\": 0.8,\n+    \"iterationsCompleted\": 5,\n+    \"openQuestions\": 0,\n+    \"resolvedQuestions\": 5,\n+    \"keyFindings\": 18,\n+    \"convergenceScore\": 1,\n     \"coverageBySources\": {\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/SKILL.md\": 3,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-workflows/mode-registry.json\": 2,\n       \".opencode/skills/deep-loop-runtime/README.md\": 3,\n@